{"evaluate-stig":{"version":"1.2604.2"},"title":"Evaluate-STIG_COMBINED","id":"20e0408f-9768-475e-9238-cdde4790d0fc","stigs":[{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:16:00.6545287-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Adobe Acrobat Reader DC Continuous Track Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Adobe Acrobat Reader DC Continuous Track","stig_id":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG","release_info":"Release: 1 Benchmark Date: 23 Jul 2021","version":"2","uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","reference_identifier":"3975","size":26,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-213168","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213168","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213168","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Standalone Application.","rule_id_src":"SV-213168r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213168r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000005","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Standalone Application.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityStandalone\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityStandalone\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bEnhancedSecurityStandalone is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PDFs have evolved from static pages to complex documents with features such as interactive forms, multimedia content, scripting, and other capabilities. These features leave PDFs vulnerable to malicious scripts or actions that can damage the computer or steal data. The Enhanced security feature protects the computer against these threats by blocking or selectively permitting actions for trusted locations and files.\n\nEnhanced Security determines if a PDF is viewed within a standalone application. A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nEnhanced Security “hardens” the application against risky actions: prevents cross domain access, prohibits script and data injection, blocks stream access to XObjects, silent printing, and execution of high privilege JavaScript.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79409","V-64919"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"4f90a8c0-397c-4fef-8a05-3442ecb503aa","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D4BD70F2617540533D7BABBDF2B67DE5B8DC249\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Enhanced Security Standalone' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbEnhancedSecurityStandalone (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213169","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213169","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213169","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Browser.","rule_id_src":"SV-213169r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213169r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000010","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Browser.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser\nType: REG_DWORD \nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD  or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PDFs have evolved from static pages to complex documents with features such as interactive forms, multimedia content, scripting, and other capabilities. These features leave PDFs vulnerable to malicious scripts or actions that can damage the computer or steal data. The Enhanced security feature protects the computer against these threats by blocking or selectively permitting actions for trusted locations and files.\n\nEnhanced Security determines if a PDF is viewed within a browser application. A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nEnhanced Security “hardens” the application against risky actions: prevents cross domain access, prohibits script and data injection, blocks stream access to XObjects, silent printing, and execution of high privilege JavaScript.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79411","V-64921"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"4c76b9a3-c8b4-4e70-a307-173f3655dae8","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 141933A4F8C9E834190D6B90A4DFAA00AA2E5DCF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Enhanced Security In Browser' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbEnhancedSecurityInBrowser (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213170","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213170","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213170","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected Mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-213170r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213170r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000015","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected Mode.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bProtectedMode\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown \n\nValue Name: bProtectedMode\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bProtectedMode is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nProtected mode provides a sandbox capability that prevents malicious PDF files from launching arbitrary executable files, writing to system directories or the Windows registry.\n\nThis isolation of the PDFs reduces the risk of security breaches in areas outside the sandbox.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79413","V-64923"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"9e524e2f-7b7c-4f95-b1aa-1e754514c84d","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F88DDDBA66CDF8B30B15F0E17E69426E83780B9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Protected Mode at startup' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbProtectedMode (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213171","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213171","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213171","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected View.","rule_id_src":"SV-213171r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213171r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000020","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected View.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iProtectedView\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iProtectedView\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2\n\nIf the value for iProtectedView is not set to “2” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nProtected view restricts Adobe Reader DC functionality, within a sandbox, when a PDF is opened from an untrusted source.\n\nThis isolation of the PDFs reduces the risk of security breaches in areas outside the sandbox.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79415","V-64925"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"1e239ba9-a191-4212-a355-24a197572323","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C35A7001F1983CCDB06BF31FD850012334EE5D9D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Protected View: All files' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tiProtectedView (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213172","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213172","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213172","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must Block Websites.","rule_id_src":"SV-213172r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213172r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000025","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must Block Websites.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:\n\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf configuring system to allow access to websites, obtain documented ISSO approvals and risk acceptance and set “iURLPerms” to “0”.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nValue: 0 - only with a documented ISSO risk acceptance\n\nIf the value for “iURLPerms” is set to “0” and a documented ISSO risk acceptance approving access to websites is provided, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value for “iURLPerms” is not set to “1” and “Type” configured to “REG_DWORD” or does not exist, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Clicking any link to the Internet poses a potential security risk. Malicious websites can transfer harmful content or silently gather data. Acrobat Reader documents can connect to websites which can pose a potential threat to DoD systems and that functionality must be blocked. However, PDF document workflows that are trusted (e.g., DoD-created) can benefit from leveraging legitimate website access with minimal risk. Therefore, the ISSO may approve of website access and accept the risk if the access provides benefit and is a trusted site or the risk associated with accessing the site has been mitigated.\n\nAdobe Reader must block access to all websites that are not specifically allowed by ISSO risk acceptance.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79417","V-64927"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"2df0675d-49ea-4226-8125-ca1cf4c8b760","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C3AEF14D94025E491FF85A8DC171DBA31F07C47F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Access to websites: Block PDF files access to all web sites' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\r\nValue Name:\tiURLPerms (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213173","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213173","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213173","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block access to Unknown Websites.","rule_id_src":"SV-213173r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213173r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000030","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block access to Unknown Websites.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iUnknownURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iUnknownURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3\n\nIf the value for iUnknownURLPerms is not set to “3” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Because Internet access is a potential security risk, clicking any unknown website link to the Internet poses a potential security risk.\n\nMalicious websites can transfer harmful content or silently gather data.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79419","V-64929"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"c22c09a9-1504-4524-a98c-3bb19ca815e7","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 49A467B48640B3D8D3D3FE43A6ED3BC9DFCA7266\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Access to unknown websites: Block access' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\r\nValue Name:\tiUnknownURLPerms (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213174","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213174","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213174","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must prevent opening files other than PDF or FDF.","rule_id_src":"SV-213174r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213174r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000035","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must prevent opening files other than PDF or FDF.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iFileAttachmentPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iFileAttachmentPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for iFileAttachmentPerms is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments represent a potential security risk because they can contain malicious content, open other dangerous files, or launch applications. Certainly file types such as .bin, .exe, .bat, and so on will be recognized as threats.\n\nThis feature prevents users from opening or launching file types other than PDF or FDF and disables the menu option.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79421","V-64931"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"968a1007-bca3-4613-847f-651074a468c9","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FD117F85D2AFD5D7ABDB6609D049A1AF9562D1E7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow opening of non-PDF file attachments with external applications' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tiFileAttachmentPerms (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213175","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213175","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213175","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block Flash Content.","rule_id_src":"SV-213175r395811_rule","rule_id":"SV-213175r395811","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000045","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block Flash Content.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnableFlash\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnableFlash\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bEnableFlash is not set to “0” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Flash content is commonly hosted on a web page, but it can also be embedded in PDF and other documents. Flash could be used to surreptitious install malware on the end-users computer.\n\nFlash Content restricts Adobe Reader DC not to play Flash content within a PDF.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79423","V-64933"],"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"49fd90d4-895c-47bf-9193-74702284a226","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A1A5D10989EF9025B6C6269A35BCE3D36B011F21\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Flash' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbEnableFlash (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213176","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213176","title":"SRG-APP-000133","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213176","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to change the Default Handler.","rule_id_src":"SV-213176r395850_rule","rule_id":"SV-213176r395850","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000050","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to change the Default Handler.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing user to make changes to an application case cause a security risk.\n\nWhen the Default PDF Handler is disabled, the end users will not be able to change the default PDF viewer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79425","V-64935"],"ccis":["CCI-001499"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"405d5a97-9b80-458c-b082-c2b0c72b07bb","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1AE4E01A3F52210B360FF0E54E0B1483CB28E2E7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable PDF handler switching' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbDisablePDFHandlerSwitching (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213177","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213177","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213177","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Send and Track plugin for Outlook.","rule_id_src":"SV-213177r766574_rule","rule_id":"SV-213177r766574","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000055","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Send and Track plugin for Outlook.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cCloud\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cCloud\n\nValue Name: bAdobeSendPluginToggle\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration > Administrative Templates > Adobe Reader DC Continuous > Preferences > 'Send and Track plugin' to 'Disabled'.\n\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cCloud\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cCloud\n\nValue Name: bAdobeSendPluginToggle\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bAdobeSendPluginToggle is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.\n\nAdmin Template path: Computer Configuration > Administrative Templates > Adobe Reader DC Continuous > Preferences > 'Send and Track plugin' must be set to 'Disabled'.\n\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When enabled, Adobe Send and Track button appears in Outlook. When an email is composed it enables the ability to send large files as public links through Outlook. The attached files can be uploaded to the Adobe Document Cloud and public links to the files are inserted in the email body.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79427","V-64937"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"179ebfc8-4e2e-4896-8292-624e2829b174","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 34C0849690B7CE652CD8E1EDB25AB7B9E78064F4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Send and Track plugin' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cCloud\r\nValue Name:\tbAdobeSendPluginToggle (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213178","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213178","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213178","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable all service access to Document Cloud Services.","rule_id_src":"SV-213178r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213178r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000060","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable all service access to Document Cloud Services.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeDocumentServices\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeDocumentServices\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleAdobeDocumentServices is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated in Adobe Reader DC. With the integration of Adobe Document Cloud, disabling this feature prevents the risk of additional attack vectors.\n\nWithin Adobe Reader DC, the Adobe Cloud resources require a paid subscription for each service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79429","V-64939"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"2bd14961-0478-4e47-8e28-0ed29179ffb8","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5B5BF8705F4CCBF6E1DDAB7C781FF6E0741C37D4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Service access to Document Cloud Services' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\r\nValue Name:\tbToggleAdobeDocumentServices (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213179","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213179","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213179","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Cloud Synchronization.","rule_id_src":"SV-213179r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213179r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000065","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Cloud Synchronization.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bTogglePrefsSync\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bTogglePrefsSync\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bTogglePrefsSync is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated in Adobe Reader DC. When the Adobe Cloud synchronization is disabled it prevents the synchronization of desktop preferences across devices on which the user is signed in with an Adobe ID (including phones).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79431","V-64941"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"57b5a2a6-c1d8-4b37-b841-86d56396c891","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3959F542BE563690045D94120CA3F38423C0E9E7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Cloud Synchronization' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\r\nValue Name:\tbTogglePrefsSync (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213180","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213180","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213180","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Repair Installation.","rule_id_src":"SV-213180r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213180r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000070","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Repair Installation.","fix_text":"\"Configure the following registry value:\n\nFor 32 bit:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer \n\nFor 64 bit:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nValue Name: DisableMaintenance\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: \n\nFor 32 bit:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nFor 64 bit:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nValue Name: DisableMaintenance\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for DisableMaintenance is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Repair Installation is disabled the user does not have the option (Help Menu) or functional to repair an Adobe Reader DC install.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79433","V-64943"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"bcd91866-3338-47a9-894e-b7c75a1e95db","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E70039157257768AB74240220DD3D12A62085915\r\n~~~~~\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\r\nValue Name:\tDisableMaintenance (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\r\nValue Name:\tDisableMaintenance (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213181","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213181","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213181","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable 3rd Party Web Connectors.","rule_id_src":"SV-213181r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213181r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000075","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable 3rd Party Web Connectors.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleWebConnectors\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleWebConnectors\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleWebConnectors is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When 3rd Party Web Connectors are disabled it prevents the configuration of Adobe Reader DC access to third party services for file storage.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79435","V-64945"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"31e0f3f3-f4c9-4a02-a0db-3f7cf6afd1b3","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 89B9881F4FE720122995853EE2D4E2CEFC2B01A9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Third-party web connectors' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\r\nValue Name:\tbToggleWebConnectors (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213182","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213182","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213182","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Acrobat Upsell.","rule_id_src":"SV-213182r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213182r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000080","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Acrobat Upsell.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\n\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bAcroSuppressUpsell\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following:\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bAcroSuppressUpsell\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1   \n\nIf the value for bAcroSuppressUpsell is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Products that don't provide the full set of features by default provide the user the opportunity to upgrade. Acrobat Upsell displays message which encourage the user to upgrade the product. For example, Reader users can purchase additional tools and features, and Acrobat Reader users can upgrade to Acrobat Professional.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80539","V-66049"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"c1812a16-348b-44c6-9d81-2009617d988c","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8658DEEAFC38A0F3DE63BE9300339CBAC6C079AA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Acrobat Upsell' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbAcroSuppressUpsell (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213183","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213183","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213183","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Adobe Send for Signature.","rule_id_src":"SV-213183r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213183r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000085","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Adobe Send for Signature.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeSign\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeSign\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleAdobeSign is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Adobe Document Cloud sign service allows users to send documents online for signature and sign from anywhere or any device. The signed documents are stored in the Adobe Cloud. The Adobe Document Cloud sign service is a paid subscription.\n\nWhen Adobe Send for Signature is disabled users will not be allowed to utilize the Adobe Document Cloud sign function.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79437","V-64947"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"11891464-a9f9-4fc3-ae20-847ea41bd230","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 62D1C61B8AAD6769BE3BD85C2EDA46182409F30D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Adobe Send for Signature' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\r\nValue Name:\tbToggleAdobeSign (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213184","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213184","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213184","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable access to Webmail.","rule_id_src":"SV-213184r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213184r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000090","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable access to Webmail.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWebmailProfiles\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWebmailProfiles\n\nValue Name: bDisableWebmail\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWebmailProfiles\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWebmailProfiles\n\nValue Name: bDisableWebmail\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableWebmail is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Webmail is disabled the user cannot configure a webmail account to send an open PDF document as an attachment. Users should have the ability to send documents as Microsoft Outlook attachments. The difference is that Outlook must be configured by the administrator on the local machine.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79439","V-64949"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"0195d234-21f3-4520-b255-cbab9d2e3973","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3688E672F0E033A5503F70C1390227DD464A303E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'WebMail' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWebmailProfiles\r\nValue Name:\tbDisableWebmail (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213185","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213185","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213185","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Online SharePoint Access.","rule_id_src":"SV-213185r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213185r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000100","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Online SharePoint Access.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cSharePoint\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cSharePoint\n\nValue Name: bDisableSharePointFeatures\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nIf configured to an approved DoD SharePoint Server, this is NA.\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cSharePoint\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cSharePoint\n\nValue Name: bDisableSharePointFeatures\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableSharePointFeatures is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling SharePoint disables or removes the user’s ability to add a SharePoint account access controls the application's ability to detect that a file came from a SharePoint server, and disables the check-out prompt.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79441","V-64951"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"4c4c5cc7-ddb3-4c85-aad8-9b1a3d43709e","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F0D80A8FB2FA68C5878D30ECBBAB501FB67E7668\r\n~~~~~\r\n'SharePoint and Office 365 access' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cSharePoint\r\nValue Name:\tbDisableSharePointFeatures (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213186","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213186","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213186","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Welcome Screen.","rule_id_src":"SV-213186r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213186r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000115","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Welcome Screen.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWelcomeScreen\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWelcomeScreen\n\nValue Name: bShowWelcomeScreen\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWelcomeScreen\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWelcomeScreen\n\nValue Name: bShowWelcomeScreen\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bShowWelcomeScreen is not set to “0” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Adobe Reader DC Welcome screen can be distracting and also has online links to the Adobe quick tips website, tutorials, blogs and community forums.\n\nWhen the Adobe Reader DC Welcome screen is disabled the Welcome screen will not be populated on application startup.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79443","V-64953"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"10dbc5df-5ff4-4270-b750-2a7b7db043c8","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 00D691DC0D604013E3FAAF7449373C94261277C9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Welcome Screen' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWelcomeScreen\r\nValue Name:\tbShowWelcomeScreen (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213187","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213187","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213187","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Service Upgrades.","rule_id_src":"SV-213187r395853_rule","rule_id":"SV-213187r395853","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000120","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Service Upgrades.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bUpdater\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bUpdater\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bUpdater is not set to “0” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated into Adobe Reader DC. Disabling Service Upgrades disables both updates to the product's web-plugin components as well as all services without exception, including any online sign-in screen.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79445","V-64955"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"c61953b0-9fea-4575-b146-4d00d9c0d763","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FC76DFD3453ECD892F675C168C9A43A5131C5833\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Service Upgrades' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\r\nValue Name:\tbUpdater (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213188","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213188","title":"SRG-APP-000380","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213188","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to add Trusted Files and Folders.","rule_id_src":"SV-213188r400006_rule","rule_id":"SV-213188r400006","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000315","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to add Trusted Files and Folders.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedFolders\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedFolders\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableTrustedFolders is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Privileged Locations allow the user to selectively trust files, folders, and hosts to bypass some security restrictions, such as enhanced security and protected view. By default, the user can create privileged locations through the GUI.\n\nDisabling Trusted Files and Folders disables and locks the end user's ability to add folders and files as a privileged location prevents them from assigning trust and thereby exempting that location from enhanced security restrictions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80157","V-65667"],"ccis":["CCI-001813"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"b95e2442-6be0-4b1a-89f5-6d2de09c281f","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 043394E902307A0086D6732F1E623BFAD8EA03C0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Privileged folder locations' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbDisableTrustedFolders (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213189","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213189","title":"SRG-APP-000380","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213189","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to elevate IE Trusts to Privileged Locations.","rule_id_src":"SV-213189r400006_rule","rule_id":"SV-213189r400006","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000320","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to elevate IE Trusts to Privileged Locations.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedSites\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedSites\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableTrustedSites is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Privileged Locations allow the user to selectively trust files, folders, and hosts to bypass some security restrictions, such as enhanced security and protected view. By default, the user can create privileged locations through the GUI.\n\nDisabling IE Trusts to Privileged Locations disables and locks the end user's ability to treat IE trusted sites as a privileged location prevents them from assigning trust and thereby exempting that location from enhanced security restrictions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80159","V-65669"],"ccis":["CCI-001813"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"36917179-f092-4cfe-b2c9-3466447c2673","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C900785F9EAF6BBD36E3A70E323EE0CAD36808B0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Privileged host locations' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\r\nValue Name:\tbDisableTrustedSites (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213190","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213190","title":"SRG-APP-000427","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213190","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of European certificates.","rule_id_src":"SV-213190r400378_rule","rule_id":"SV-213190r400378","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000330","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of European certificates.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cEUTLDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cEUTLDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bLoadSettingsFromURL is not set to “0” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, the user can update European certificates from an Adobe server through the GUI.\n\nWhen uploading European certificates is disabled, it prevents the automatic download and installation of certificates and disables and locks the end user's ability to upload those certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80163","V-65673"],"ccis":["CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"b1f87a42-14cc-4ffd-a65c-38c5af178c23","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 3523BAB409AFD38B3DD18D3CACE07C781BA0C7B2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Load trusted certificates from an Adobe EUTL server' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\r\nValue Name:\tbLoadSettingsFromURL (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213191","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213191","title":"SRG-APP-000427","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213191","severity":"low","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of Adobe certificates.","rule_id_src":"SV-213191r400378_rule","rule_id":"SV-213191r400378","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000335","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of Adobe certificates.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cAdobeDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cAdobeDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bLoadSettingsFromURL is not set to “0” and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, the user can update Adobe certificates from an Adobe server through the GUI.\n\nWhen uploading Adobe certificates is disabled, it prevents the automatic download and installation of certificates and disables and locks the end user's ability to upload those certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80165","V-65675"],"ccis":["CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"34e3e10c-542b-4a6d-9739-cc9bcefe656b","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 661C86B287D34B0F64DF34E2BDF109B65638F5AF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Load trusted certificates from an Adobe AATL server' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\r\nValue Name:\tbLoadSettingsFromURL (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213192","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213192","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213192","severity":"high","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must have the latest Security-related Software Updates installed.","rule_id_src":"SV-213192r400525_rule","rule_id":"SV-213192r400525","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000340","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must have the latest Security-related Software Updates installed.","fix_text":"Apply the latest security-related software updates to the Adobe Acrobat Reader application.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine the method for doing this (e.g., connection to a WSUS server, local procedure, auto update, etc.).\n\nOpen Adobe Acrobat Reader DC.\n\nNavigate to and click on Help >> About Adobe Acrobat Reader DC.\n\nVerify that the latest security-related software updates by Adobe are being applied.\n\nIf the latest security-related software updates by Adobe are not being applied, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period utilized must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80167","V-65677"],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"45a4d28d-61f5-46a0-8516-2f29256e641b","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: 3DDDAF25C58F8A892FFB6D2332E27A9991C98A52\r\n~~~~~\r\nName:\t\t\tAdobe Reader DC\r\nVersion:\t\t\tDC\r\nTrack:\t\t\tContinuous\r\nDisplayVersion:\t26.001.21691\r\nArchitecture:\t\tx64"},{"group_id_src":"V-213193","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213193","title":"SRG-APP-000514","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213193","severity":"medium","group_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable FIPS mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-213193r400876_rule","rule_id":"SV-213193r400876","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000345","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable FIPS mode.","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"bFIPSMode\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\n\nValue Name: bFIPSMode \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"bFIPSMode\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\n\nValue Name: bFIPSMode \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bFIPSMode is not set to “1” and Type configured to REG_DWORD does not exist, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. The application must implement cryptographic modules adhering to the higher standards approved by the federal government since this provides assurance they have been tested and validated.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-80169","V-65679"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"3975","uuid":"d991af39-3a34-4a55-89bd-a4da7e942cff","stig_uuid":"d3b59b95-7d79-4ca6-8d6c-1293c3a78ddb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-AdobeReaderDCContinuous_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: B192563C2599CD2E0DCE41E4A1D053F4854CF0D0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable FIPS' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\r\nValue Name:\tbFIPSMode (Not found)"}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:16:07.8184919-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows","stig_id":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows","release_info":"Release: 11 Benchmark Date: 02 Jul 2025","version":"2","uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","reference_identifier":"4081","size":46,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-221558","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221558","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221558","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firewall traversal from remote host must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221558r960804_rule","rule_id":"SV-221558r960804","rule_version":"DTBC-0001","rule_title":"Firewall traversal from remote host must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \r\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative\\Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Remote Access\r\n Policy Name: Enable firewall traversal from remote access host\r\n Policy State: Disabled\r\n Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows registry:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.  \n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections should never be allowed that bypass the firewall, as there is no way to verify if they can be trusted. Enables usage of STUN and relay servers when remote clients are trying to establish a connection to this machine. If this setting is enabled, then remote clients can discover and connect to this machine even if they are separated by a firewall. If this setting is disabled and outgoing UDP connections are filtered by the firewall, then this machine will only allow connections from client machines within the local network. If this policy is left not set the setting will be enabled.\t","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57545","V-44711"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"4e76df11-ac5f-480d-ae2e-48e6c5042477","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C6B9596BC9D97E745F62C374F941E86C815FB175\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable firewall traversal from remote access host' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tRemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221559","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221559","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221559","severity":"medium","group_title":"Site tracking users location must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221559r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-221559r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0002","rule_title":"Site tracking users location must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:    \n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\    \n   Policy Name: Default geolocation setting    \n   Policy State: Enabled    \n   Policy Value: Do not allow any site to track the users' physical location\n\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:               \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy             \n   2. If DefaultGeolocationSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultGeolocationSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Website tracking is the practice of gathering information as to which websites were accesses by a browser. The common method of doing this is to have a website create a tracking cookie on the browser.   If the information of what sites are being accessed is made available to unauthorized persons, this violates confidentiality requirements, and over time poses a significant OPSEC issue. This policy setting allows you to set whether websites are allowed to track the user’s physical location. Tracking the user’s physical location can be allowed by default, denied by default or the user can be asked every time a website requests the physical location.\t\n   1 = Allow sites to track the user’s physical location\t\n   2 = Do not allow any site to track the user’s physical location\t\n   3 = Ask whenever a site wants to track the user’s physical location","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57557","V-44723"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"4b4aaf44-0ec2-4b2c-b3cc-10833a9b758d","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 66AA54039CC8EC1995CCD314CBD4250D898BA9CF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default geolocation setting' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow any site to track the users' physical location)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultGeolocationSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221561","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221561","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221561","severity":"medium","group_title":"Sites ability to show pop-ups must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221561r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221561r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0004","rule_title":"Sites ability to show pop-ups must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\\n    Policy Name: Default popups setting\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Do not allow any site to show popups\n\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \r\n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \r\n 2. If DefaultPopupsSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n 1. Start regedit\r\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\r\n 3. If the value name DefaultPopupsSetting does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\r\n\r\nNote:  If AO Approved exceptions to this rule have been enabled, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Chrome allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and pop-ups that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to ‘2’ to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the pop-up windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.  If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.  If this policy is left not set, 'BlockPopups' will be used and the user will be able to change it.    \r\n   1 = Allow all sites to show pop-ups    \r\n   2 = Do not allow any site to show pop-ups","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57553","V-44719"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"0da3a4b5-e542-44bc-8a36-20705ee1bbc8","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E88968BD282F31DFB07CB0B3701D0B198E4787E1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default popups setting' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow any site to show popups)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultPopupsSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221562","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221562","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221562","severity":"medium","group_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","rule_id_src":"SV-221562r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-221562r960879","rule_version":"DTBC-0005","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \r\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\r\n Policy Name: Configure extension installation blocklist\r\n Policy State: Enabled\r\n Policy Value: *","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \r\n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \r\n 2. If ExtensionInstallBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to * under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n 1. Start regedit\r\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\r\n 3. If the a registry value name of 1 does not exist under that key or its value is not set to *, then this is a finding. ","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Extensions are developed by third party sources and are designed to extend Google Chrome's functionality. An extension can be made by anyone, to do and access almost anything on a system; this means they pose a high risk to any system that would allow all extensions to be installed by default. Allows you to specify which extensions the users can NOT install. Extensions already installed will be removed if blocklisted. A blocklist value of '*' means all extensions are blocklisted unless they are explicitly listed in the allowlist. If this policy is left not set the user can install any extension in Google Chrome.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57561","V-44727"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"1b304391-72d0-422b-a89b-3f5e21e24819","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3D6DDE808AA2208AC7BDBC18CF8B65BFC5C77656\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure extension installation blocklist' is NOT Enabled: (*)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\r\nValue Name:\t1 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221563","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221563","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221563","severity":"low","group_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted.","rule_id_src":"SV-221563r1015468_rule","rule_id":"SV-221563r1015468","rule_version":"DTBC-0006","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\r\nPolicy Name: Configure extension installation allowlist\r\nPolicy State: Enabled\r\nPolicy Value: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf\r\n\r\nNote: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdfis the extension ID for scriptno (a commonly used Chrome extension), other extension IDs may vary.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \r\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \r\n2. If ExtensionInstallAllowlist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n1. Start regedit\r\n2. Navigate to the key HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\r\n3. If the ExtensionInstallAllowlist key is not set to 1 and oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator-approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The allowlist should only contain organizationally approved extensions. This is to prevent a user from accidently allowlisitng a malicious extension. This policy allows you to specify which extensions are not subject to the blacklist. A blacklist value of ‘*’ means all extensions are blacklisted and users can only install extensions listed in the allowlist. By default, no extensions are allowlisted. If all extensions have been blacklisted by policy, then the allowlist policy can be used to allow specific extensions to be installed. Administrators should determine which extensions should be allowed to be installed by their users. If no extensions are allowlisted, then no extensions can be installed when combined with blacklisting all extensions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57563","V-44729"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"25d257f4-985a-47c9-98d1-12e19f8fbd0f","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BF4B1204B38416961C0FD67270A7CB7E4DF963AE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure extension installation allowlist' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\r\nValue Name:\t1 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221564","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221564","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221564","severity":"medium","group_title":"The default search providers name must be set.","rule_id_src":"SV-221564r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221564r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0007","rule_title":"The default search providers name must be set.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Default search provider name\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted)\n\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If DefaultSearchProviderName is displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted) under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultSearchProviderName value name does not exist or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted), then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Specifies the name of the default search provider that is to be used, if left empty or not set, the host name specified by the search URL will be used. This policy is only considered if the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled. When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57567","V-44733"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"59dc49a6-979b-4910-ab01-f6e3e0db0636","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E36169FF1A39390332A1DE0B3F5F2F81A3090B45\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default search provider name' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultSearchProviderName (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221565","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221565","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221565","severity":"medium","group_title":"The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.","rule_id_src":"SV-221565r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221565r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0008","rule_title":"The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\r\n\r\nWindows group policy:\r\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\.\r\n- Policy Name: Default search provider search URL\r\n- Policy State: Enabled\r\n- Policy Value: Must be set to an organization-approved encrypted search string \r\n(ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} )","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\r\n\r\nUniversal method: \r\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\r\n2. If DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ) under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n1. Start regedit.\r\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\r\n3. If the DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL value name does not exist or its value data is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ), this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Specifies the URL of the search engine used when doing a default search. The URL should contain the string '{searchTerms}', which will be replaced at query time by the terms the user is searching for. This option must be set when the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled and will only be respected if this is the case.  When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57569","V-44735"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"9aed18e4-de27-44f8-b700-fc484501a03a","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 49899391EBBA7044AAA1F105F7ECF63C77347BDE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default search provider search URL' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultSearchProviderSearchURL (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221566","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221566","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221566","severity":"medium","group_title":"Default search provider must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221566r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221566r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0009","rule_title":"Default search provider must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Enable the default search provider\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A\n\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If DefaultSearchProviderEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the DefaultSearchProviderEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Policy enables the use of a default search provider. If you enable this setting, a default search is performed when the user types text in the omnibox that is not a URL. You can specify the default search provider to be used by setting the rest of the default search policies. If these are left empty, the user can choose the default provider. If you disable this setting, no search is performed when the user enters non-URL text in the omnibox. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, the default search provider is enabled, and the user will be able to set the search provider list.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57571","V-44737"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"29649f01-494a-4644-b826-8608cc465b0d","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 94232B5848C2BFA4DA09CBB3AECF9AC4C5920B29\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable the default search provider' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultSearchProviderEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221567","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221567","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221567","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221567r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221567r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0011","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Password Manager\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Saving Passwords to the Password Manager\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:           \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy           \n   2. If PasswordManagerEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the PasswordManagerEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables saving passwords and using saved passwords in Google Chrome. Malicious sites may take advantage of this feature by using hidden fields gain access to the stored information. If you enable this setting, users can have Google Chrome memorize passwords and provide them automatically the next time they log in to a site. If you disable this setting, users are not able to save passwords or use already saved passwords. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it. ListPassword manager should not be used as it stores passwords locally.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57575","V-44741"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"02b4f71e-002c-4fe4-b5fc-873747ae8b58","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 505EAB67616285301189855739F5B393E81A8617\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Saving Passwords to the Password Manager' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tPasswordManagerEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221570","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221570","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221570","severity":"medium","group_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221570r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-221570r960921","rule_version":"DTBC-0017","rule_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If BackgroundModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column and it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the BackgroundModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Determines whether a Google Chrome process is started on OS login that keeps running when the last browser window is closed, allowing background apps to remain active. The background process displays an icon in the system tray and can always be closed from there. If this policy is set to True, background mode is enabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is set to False, background mode is disabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is left unset, background mode is initially disabled and can be controlled by the user in the browser settings.' - Google Chrome Administrators Policy ListThis setting, if enabled, allows Google Chrome to run at all times. There is two reasons that this is not wanted. First, it can tie up system resources that might otherwise be needed. Second, it does not make it obvious to the user that it is running and poorly written extensions could cause instability on the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57587","V-44753"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"5cb50db1-574c-43c0-9a11-e84df11d9208","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A39C056FB84BE48F5607274733E7C925E7E0DE1A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tBackgroundModeEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221571","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221571","title":"SRG-APP-000047","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221571","severity":"medium","group_title":"Google Data Synchronization must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221571r987620_rule","rule_id":"SV-221571r987620","rule_version":"DTBC-0020","rule_title":"Google Data Synchronization must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable synchronization of data with Google\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n  1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n  2. If SyncDisabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SyncDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disables data synchronization in Google Chrome using Google-hosted synchronization services and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the user will be able to enable Google Sync.  Google Sync is used to sync information between different user devices, this data is then stored on Google owned servers. The synced data may consist of information such as email, calendars, viewing history, etc. This feature must be disabled because the organization does not have control over the servers the data is stored on.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57593","V-44759"],"ccis":["CCI-001374"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"3aef74da-b0db-4fa8-bc49-755831d5e8ad","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8C929751CF809CB5F56BBB6A7E89675115AC55C6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable synchronization of data with Google' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tSyncDisabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221572","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221572","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221572","severity":"medium","group_title":"The URL protocol schema javascript must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221572r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221572r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0021","rule_title":"The URL protocol schema javascript must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc. \r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\r\nPolicy Name: Block access to a list of URLs.\r\n- Policy State: Enabled\r\n- Policy Value 1: javascript://*","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\r\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\r\n2. If URLBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to javascript://* under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n1. Start regedit.\r\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\URLBlocklist.\r\n3. If the URLBlocklist key does not exist, or the does not contain entries 1 set to javascript://*, this is a finding.\r\n\r\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Each access to a URL is handled by the browser according to the URL's \"scheme\". The \"scheme\" of a URL is the section before the \":\". The term \"protocol\" is often mistakenly used for a \"scheme\". The difference is that the scheme is how the browser handles a URL and the protocol is how the browser communicates with a service.  If a scheme or its associated protocol used by a browser is insecure or obsolete, vulnerabilities can be exploited resulting in exposed data or unrestricted access to the browser's system.   The browser must be configured to disable the use of insecure and obsolete schemas (protocols).\r\nThis policy disables the listed protocol schemes in Google Chrome, URLs using a scheme from this list will not load and cannot be navigated to. If this policy is left not set or the list is empty all schemes will be accessible in Google Chrome.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57595","V-44761"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"e034d5c8-53e3-40ac-b9d2-7d148ed7a6cf","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EE15B7E7242F5D890FDBD05E2D2A97EC935D6396\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Block access to a list of URLs' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\URLBlocklist\r\nValue Name:\t1 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221573","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221573","title":"SRG-APP-000047","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221573","severity":"medium","group_title":"Cloud print sharing must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221573r987620_rule","rule_id":"SV-221573r987620","rule_version":"DTBC-0023","rule_title":"Cloud print sharing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \r\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Printing\r\n Policy Name: Enable Google Cloud Print proxy\r\n Policy State: Disabled\r\n Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If CloudPrintProxyEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the CloudPrintProxyEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Policy enables Google Chrome to act as a proxy between Google Cloud Print and legacy printers connected to the machine. If this setting is enabled or not configured, users can enable the cloud print proxy by authentication with their Google account. If this setting is disabled, users cannot enable the proxy, and the machine will not be allowed to share it’s printers with Google Cloud Print. If this policy is not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57599","V-44765"],"ccis":["CCI-001374"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"9cff41c9-5646-460f-86bf-dedc6afac317","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AECE03E13CD349DD85571AFB8E849D0AD726DFC7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Google Cloud Print proxy' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tCloudPrintProxyEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221574","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221574","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221574","severity":"medium","group_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221574r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-221574r961863","rule_version":"DTBC-0025","rule_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable network prediction\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not predict network actions on any network connection","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" is not displayed under the “Policy Name” column or it is not set to \"2\" under the “Policy Value” column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2,\" this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables network prediction in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be disabled but the user will be able to change it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57603","V-44769"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"c78d3caf-3bed-4317-9514-cf8def8db5e9","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5DCF625A35F1E09DC71EC862634F0CF5192D0D59\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable network prediction' is NOT Enabled: (Do not predict network actions on any network connection)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tNetworkPredictionOptions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221575","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221575","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221575","severity":"medium","group_title":"Metrics reporting to Google must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221575r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221575r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0026","rule_title":"Metrics reporting to Google must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable reporting of usage and crash-related data\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If MetricsReportingEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the MetricsReportingEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data about Google Chrome to Google and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is sent to Google. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you disable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is never sent to Google. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the setting will be what the user chose upon installation / first run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57605","V-44771"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"0c9aa8e1-f650-4e41-9a94-befca97adba7","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 862C9B60F9D63C4453E67DB639BEF51D9A210E80\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable reporting of usage and crash-related data' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tMetricsReportingEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221576","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221576","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221576","severity":"medium","group_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221576r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221576r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0027","rule_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable search suggestions\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If SearchSuggestEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SearchSuggestEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Search suggestion should be disabled as it could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made. Enables search suggestions in Google Chrome's omnibox and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, search suggestions are used. If you disable this setting, search suggestions are never used. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57607","V-44773"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"adf65fd4-a26c-4ec9-ab81-307e91b8ba9d","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4250FC0AF427950357A35C777C50D41987D11E0A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable search suggestions' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tSearchSuggestEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221577","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221577","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221577","severity":"medium","group_title":"Importing of saved passwords must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221577r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221577r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0029","rule_title":"Importing of saved passwords must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n   Policy Name: Import saved passwords from default browser on first run\n   Policy State: Disabled\n   Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If ImportSavedPasswords is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the ImportSavedPasswords value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Importing of saved passwords should be disabled as it could lead to unencrypted account passwords stored on the system from another browser to be viewed. This policy forces the saved passwords to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog. If disabled, the saved passwords are not imported. If it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57609","V-44775"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"fbe383ca-af8b-410a-be0e-f2f7ea0613eb","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 09B54A56D74F1F0A594F9C5AFBE6E63F94009045\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Import saved passwords from default browser on first run' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tImportSavedPasswords (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221578","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221578","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221578","severity":"medium","group_title":"Incognito mode must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221578r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-221578r960864","rule_version":"DTBC-0030","rule_title":"Incognito mode must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Incognito mode availability\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Incognito mode disabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If IncognitoModeAvailability is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the IncognitoModeAvailability value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Incognito mode allows the user to browse the Internet without recording their browsing history/activity.  From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable.  Best practice requires that browser history is retained.  The \"IncognitoModeAvailability\" setting controls whether the user may utilize Incognito mode in Google Chrome. If 'Enabled' is selected or the policy is left unset, pages may be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Disabled' is selected, pages may not be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Forced' is selected, pages may be opened ONLY in Incognito mode.   \n   0 = Incognito mode available.    \n   1 = Incognito mode disabled.    \n   2 = Incognito mode forced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57611","V-44777"],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"ff044e9d-d55c-4c2e-86d6-b64c609bce13","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2630BB4FE0A26B460ED70DEAAA335455D4453684\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Incognito mode availability' is NOT Enabled: (Incognito mode disabled)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tIncognitoModeAvailability (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221579","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221579","title":"SRG-APP-000605","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221579","severity":"medium","group_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","rule_id_src":"SV-221579r961893_rule","rule_id":"SV-221579r961893","rule_version":"DTBC-0037","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \r\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\r\n Policy Name: Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\r\n Policy State: Enabled\r\n Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If EnableOnlineRevocationChecks is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the EnableOnlineRevocationChecks value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By setting this policy to true, the previous behavior is restored and online OCSP/CRL checks will be performed. If the policy is not set, or is set to false, then Chrome will not perform online revocation checks. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57623","V-44789"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"f9202595-2f1e-4d53-b03c-77f0c32160d9","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 64DE0C4D32DC87A6CCFDE6E8E8C31124AEE4734C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable online OCSP/CRL checks' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tEnableOnlineRevocationChecks (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221580","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221580","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221580","severity":"medium","group_title":"Safe Browsing must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221580r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-221580r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0038","rule_title":"Safe Browsing must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing Settings\n Policy Name: Safe Browsing Protection Level\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: \"(1) Safe Browsing is active in the standard mode\", or \"(2) Safe Browsing is active in the enhanced mode. This mode provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 or 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1 or 2, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows you to control whether Google Chrome's Safe Browsing feature is enabled and the mode it operates in.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'NoProtection' (value 0), Safe Browsing is never active.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'StandardProtection' (value 1, which is the default), Safe Browsing is always active in the standard mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'EnhancedProtection' (value 2), Safe Browsing is always active in the enhanced mode, which provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57625","V-44791"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"a25caa31-44e4-4b52-a103-862598bf4daa","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F19BE5A1CB532C4F83463CF4B1E3C2DF4565CCF2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Safe Browsing Protection Level' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tSafeBrowsingProtectionLevel (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221581","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221581","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221581","severity":"medium","group_title":"Browser history must be saved.","rule_id_src":"SV-221581r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-221581r961128","rule_version":"DTBC-0039","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable saving browser history\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value:  N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If the policy 'SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled' is not shown or is not set to false, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy disables saving browser history in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If this setting is enabled, browsing history is not saved. If this setting is disabled or not set, browsing history is saved.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57627","V-44793"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"5765fd5b-1cc3-4ce2-977f-ff3ff2f31991","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 336EF2BC4C4627EFDF94B8B6E7257D8F0386BB30\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable saving browser history' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tSavingBrowserHistoryDisabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221584","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221584","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221584","severity":"medium","group_title":"The version of Google Chrome running on the system must be a supported version.","rule_id_src":"SV-221584r961683_rule","rule_id":"SV-221584r961683","rule_version":"DTBC-0050","rule_title":"The version of Google Chrome running on the system must be a supported version.","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Google Chrome.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://settings/help\n2. Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Google Chrome site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available.  As of July 2019, this is 74.x.x.\n3. If the installed version of Chrome is not supported by Google, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Google Chrome is being continually updated by the vendor in order to address identified security vulnerabilities. Running an older version of the browser can introduce security vulnerabilities to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-57639","V-44805"],"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"551bfee9-d1f2-4d25-b88e-69802a56094b","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: AC5FE3D949771826E4EE2AE2725CA279C2CAD016\r\n~~~~~\r\nGoogle Chrome version information:\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome (150.0.7871.128)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221586","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221586","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221586","severity":"medium","group_title":"Deletion of browser history must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221586r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-221586r960879","rule_version":"DTBC-0052","rule_title":"Deletion of browser history must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Enable deleting browser and download history\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If the policy \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not shown or is not set to false, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\",  this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures. Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89845","V-75165"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"5a8a29ac-f513-4a89-a482-c1cc906bb246","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B3AACC957D2208DED19F7040602DE4584F330BB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable deleting browser and download history' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tAllowDeletingBrowserHistory (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221587","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221587","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221587","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prompt for download location must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221587r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-221587r960879","rule_version":"DTBC-0053","rule_title":"Prompt for download location must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path:  Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Ask where to save each file before downloading\n Policy State:  Enabled\n Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome:// policy\n2. If \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"true\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, then this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the policy is enabled, the user will be asked where to save each file before downloading. If the policy is disabled, downloads will start immediately, and the user will not be asked where to save the file. If the policy is not configured, the user will be able to change this setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94633","V-79929"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"c1a97890-a56e-42cd-a617-fa5748b78b51","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 16C6865E9D74A75C4A65A890CEA8E4AD5C187014\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Ask where to save each file before downloading' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tPromptForDownloadLocation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221588","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221588","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221588","severity":"medium","group_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-221588r1106670_rule","rule_id":"SV-221588r1106670","rule_version":"DTBC-0055","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nWindows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow download restrictions\nPolicy State: 1, 2, or 4\nPolicy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nUniversal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DownloadRestrictions\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is set to \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DownloadRestrictions\" value name does not exist or its value data is set to \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Setting the policy means users cannot bypass download security decisions. There are many types of download warnings within Chrome, which roughly break down into these categories:\n- Malicious, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- Uncommon or unwanted, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- A dangerous file type (e.g., all SWF downloads and many EXE downloads).\n\nSetting the policy blocks different subsets of these, depending on its value:\n\n0 = No special restrictions. Default.\n1 = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types.\n2 = Block malicious downloads, uncommon or unwanted downloads, and dangerous file types.\n3 = Block all downloads.\n4 = Block malicious downloads. Recommended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94635","V-79931"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"b8e41dbc-eb47-43af-8702-4e5bc44e2cb8","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C1033D575CB9152A610F94FD24C67DAB7848C1A1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow download restrictions' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDownloadRestrictions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221590","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221590","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221590","severity":"medium","group_title":"Safe Browsing Extended Reporting must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221590r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-221590r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0057","rule_title":"Safe Browsing Extended Reporting must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing settings\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Safe Browsing Extended Reporting\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables Google Chrome's Safe Browsing Extended Reporting and prevents users from changing this setting. Extended Reporting sends some system information and page content to Google servers to help detect dangerous apps and sites.\nIf the setting is set to \"True\", then reports will be created and sent whenever necessary (such as when a security interstitial is shown).\nIf the setting is set to \"False\", reports will never be sent.\nIf this policy is set to \"True\" or \"False\", the user will not be able to modify the setting.\nIf this policy is left unset, the user will be able to change the setting and decide whether to send reports or not.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96299","V-81585"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"3c41da6a-8c44-42e7-8778-8af90872bd3c","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DD6EDCC87CE393F4E6A45AFB5215BE856A0A746\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Safe Browsing Extended Reporting' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tSafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221591","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221591","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221591","severity":"medium","group_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221591r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221591r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0058","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\n Policy Name: Control use of the WebUSB API\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: 2\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allows you to set whether websites are allowed to get access to connected USB devices. Access can be completely blocked, or the user can be asked every time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\nIf this policy is left not set, ”3” will be used, and the user will be able to change it.\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a connected USB device","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96301","V-81587"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"b7fe1cf9-f239-42c0-8f8b-41cd07954353","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F45CE20930912BF6A53D3DDD92F11D2C041FAFA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control use of the WebUSB API' is NOT Enabled: (2)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultWebUsbGuardSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221594","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221594","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221594","severity":"medium","group_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221594r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221594r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0063","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Google Cast\nPolicy Name: Enable Google Cast\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"EnableMediaRouter\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is set to ”True” or is not set, Google Cast will be enabled, and users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the “Cast toolbar” icon.\nIf this policy set to ”False”, Google Cast will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96311","V-81597"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"7f8209c0-08a6-4260-a515-4351cc4d0ace","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 602CA48814C95076F36A31E3BEECCE09E6165682\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Google Cast' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tEnableMediaRouter (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221595","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221595","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221595","severity":"medium","group_title":"Autoplay must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221595r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-221595r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0064","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow media autoplay\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This allows a user to control if videos can play automatically with audio content (without user consent) in Google Chrome.\r\n\r\nIf the policy is set to \"True\", Google Chrome is allowed to autoplay media. If the policy is set to \"False\", Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns. By default, Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96295","V-81581"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"61acf5f0-6bd9-45ca-aaa2-687fdaea8e85","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 04BDFC7EE8ED7761EA0FB8FEB9C9E556C4411B7E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow media autoplay' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tAutoplayAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221596","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221596","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221596","severity":"medium","group_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for Autoplay use.","rule_id_src":"SV-221596r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-221596r961092","rule_version":"DTBC-0065","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for Autoplay use.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\n- Policy Name: Allow media autoplay on a allowlist of URL patterns.\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value 1: [*.]mil\n- Policy Value 2: [*.]gov\n\nNote: Policy values are examples.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If “AutoplayAllowlist” under the “Policy Name” column may be set to a list of administrator-approved URLs under the “Policy Value” column. This requirement is optional.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the “AutoplayAllowlist” key may contain a list of administrator-approved URLs. This requirement is optional.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Controls the allowlist of URL patterns that autoplay will always be enabled on. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"True\" then this policy will have no effect. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"False\", then any URL patterns set in this policy will still be allowed to play.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96303","V-81589"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"a4be911f-0b4d-4c61-828a-16290f330529","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 84A36F5597010EA32A453271DA39DDF2E790AAE4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRegistry key for HKLM:SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\AutoplayAllowlist DOES NOT exist."},{"group_id_src":"V-221597","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221597","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221597","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anonymized data collection must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221597r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-221597r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0066","rule_title":"Anonymized data collection must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" is not displayed under the “Policy Name” column or it is not set to \"0\" under the “Policy Value” column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the “UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection in Google Chrome and prevent users from changing this setting.\nURL-keyed anonymized data collection sends URLs of pages the user visits to Google to make searches and browsing better.\nIf you enable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is always active.\nIf you disable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is never active.\nIf this policy is left not set, URL-keyed anonymized data collection will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-101303","V-91203"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"a69976bc-94e1-4dc9-a18b-8580964b8bb6","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 984214610BE2F96A09CA1A4EFF152E009B280A56\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tUrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221598","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221598","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221598","severity":"medium","group_title":"Collection of WebRTC event logs must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221598r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-221598r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0067","rule_title":"Collection of WebRTC event logs must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow collection of WebRTC event logs from Google services\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" is not displayed under the “Policy Name” column or it is not set to \"0\" under the “Policy Value” column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the policy is set to “true”, Google Chrome is allowed to collect WebRTC event logs from Google services (e.g., Google Meet), and upload those logs to Google.\nIf the policy is set to “false”, or is unset, Google Chrome may not collect nor upload such logs.\nThese logs contain diagnostic information helpful when debugging issues with audio or video calls in Chrome, such as the time and size of sent and received RTP packets, feedback about congestion on the network, and metadata about time and quality of audio and video frames. These logs do not contain audio or video contents from the call.\nThis data collection by Chrome can only be triggered by Google's web services, such as Google Hangouts or Google Meet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-101305","V-91205"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"8ae96b19-9ba8-4f30-aa82-9f462c5ff549","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FEDA408089FC6A9A8A01EC8506ECC203754FD3E0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow collection of WebRTC event logs from Google services' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tWebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-221599","group_tree":[{"id":"V-221599","title":"SRG-APP-000266","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-221599","severity":"low","group_title":"Chrome development tools must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-221599r961167_rule","rule_id":"SV-221599r961167","rule_version":"DTBC-0068","rule_title":"Chrome development tools must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\nPolicy Name: Control where Developer Tools can be used\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Disallow usage of the Developer Tools","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If the policy \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not shown or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the key \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" does not exist or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-106629","V-97525"],"ccis":["CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"549c0f12-bb34-4ed0-8a25-e0afa53b2a07","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E78C0E5178B0A57DB6866D6B28D2207786C1D860\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control where Developer Tools can be used' is NOT Enabled: (Disallow usage of the Developer Tools)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDeveloperToolsAvailability (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-226401","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226401","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226401","severity":"medium","group_title":"Guest Mode must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-226401r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-226401r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0069","rule_title":"Guest Mode must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable guest mode in browser\nPolicy State: Disabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If BrowserGuestModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the BrowserGuestModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is set to true or not configured, Google Chrome will enable guest logins. Guest logins are Google Chrome profiles where all windows are in incognito mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to false, Google Chrome will not allow guest profiles to be started.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111829","V-102867"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"c4311865-2b17-4b67-8f10-0ec571cb7ddc","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DCA9C1CC209AD4F1014C57C37ADF914072CCB95A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable guest mode in browser' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tBrowserGuestModeEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-226402","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226402","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226402","severity":"medium","group_title":"AutoFill for credit cards must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-226402r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-226402r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0070","rule_title":"AutoFill for credit cards must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for credit cards\nPolicy State: Disabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillCreditCardEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillCreditCardEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for credit cards in the UI.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111831","V-102869"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"a62fa05e-8411-424d-91cc-e2dd5e4b1b61","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 04D93BAB14AEEE74AE0E7D67338F1495DC9939CB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable AutoFill for credit cards' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tAutofillCreditCardEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-226403","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226403","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226403","severity":"medium","group_title":"AutoFill for addresses must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-226403r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-226403r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0071","rule_title":"AutoFill for addresses must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for addresses\nPolicy State: Disabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillAddressEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillAddressEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill address information, nor will it save additional address information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for addresses in the UI.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111833","V-102871"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"0b9183d8-ec9c-4eac-99ab-11b419451248","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 714D91380E06045A0B6A476952E4230F6DFA1C32\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable AutoFill for addresses' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tAutofillAddressEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-226404","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226404","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226404","severity":"medium","group_title":"Import AutoFill form data must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-226404r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-226404r961083","rule_version":"DTBC-0072","rule_title":"Import AutoFill form data must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Import autofill form data from default browser on first run\nPolicy State: Disabled","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If ImportAutofillFormData is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the ImportAutofillFormData value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy forces the autofill form data to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog.\nIf disabled, the autofill form data is not imported.\n\nIf it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111835","V-102873"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"a1476645-9a80-4064-a677-4bbb3ee13e1f","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 739F9EB1984B2A453DEFB79504E57D20C84390AD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Import autofill form data from default browser on first run' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tImportAutofillFormData (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-241787","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241787","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241787","severity":"medium","group_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-241787r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-241787r960963","rule_version":"DTBC-0073","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc\r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\r\n Policy Name: Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\r\n Policy State: Enabled\r\n Policy Value: Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \r\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \r\n2. If DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWindows method:\r\n 1. Start regedit\r\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\r\n 3. If the DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Setting the policy to 3 lets websites ask for access to nearby Bluetooth devices. Setting the policy to 2 denies access to nearby Bluetooth devices.\r\n\r\nLeaving the policy unset lets sites ask for access, but users can change this setting.\r\n\r\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\r\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-34246","V-26961"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"f913dd2a-68f7-43e9-b843-301b5ee4b756","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F1D966A6950D75D1D6A02FBFE4F8C3379AB9719\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control use of the Web Bluetooth API' is NOT Enabled (Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-245538","group_tree":[{"id":"V-245538","title":"SRG-APP-000383","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-245538","severity":"medium","group_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-245538r961470_rule","rule_id":"SV-245538r961470","rule_version":"DTBC-0074","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the “group policy editor” tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google Chrome.\n- Policy Name: Allow QUIC protocol\n- Policy State: Disabled\n- Policy Value: N/A","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If QuicAllowed is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to False under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\n3. If the QuicAllowed value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Chrome web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nSetting the policy to Enabled or leaving it unset allows the use of QUIC protocol in Google Chrome.\n\nSetting the policy to Disabled disallows the use of QUIC protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"9b6c1e21-071d-4711-a733-305ff13c618e","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F33C682943DE781629247FC2401CF4A3E389EBC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow QUIC protocol' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tQuicAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-245539","group_tree":[{"id":"V-245539","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-245539","severity":"medium","group_title":"Session only based cookies must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-245539r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-245539r960864","rule_version":"DTBC-0045","rule_title":"Session only based cookies must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings.\n- Policy Name: Default cookies setting\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value: Keep cookies for the duration of the session","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy\n2. If the policy \"DefaultCookiesSetting\" is not shown or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultCookiesSetting.\n3. If this key does not exist, or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the CookiesAllowedForUrls policy setting, but is not a requirement.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"c90c6213-1e02-4db8-b2cc-af8ebbacd76e","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1A8141B3026A2A76D801E0BC3F6D4C47B590CB0A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default cookies setting' is NOT Enabled: (Keep cookies for the duration of the session)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultCookiesSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275780","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275780","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275780","severity":"medium","group_title":"Create Themes with AI must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275780r1106603_rule","rule_id":"SV-275780r1106603","rule_version":"DTBC-0075","rule_title":"Create Themes with AI must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for Create Themes with AI\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Create Themes","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"CreateThemesSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"CreateThemesSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Create Themes with AI lets users create custom themes/wallpapers by preselecting from a list of options.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"9018a716-0da6-42f4-9194-42c6d3813aa1","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3B90B91704A6247F488E09F8C3451768BD094041\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Generative AI' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow Create Themes)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tCreateThemesSettings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275781","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275781","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275781","severity":"medium","group_title":"DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275781r1106671_rule","rule_id":"SV-275781r1106671","rule_version":"DTBC-0076","rule_title":"DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for DevTools Generative AI Features\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow DevTools Generative AI Features","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"These features in Google Chrome's DevTools employ generative AI models to provide additional debugging information. To use these features, Google Chrome collects data such as error messages, stack traces, code snippets, and network requests and sends them to a server owned by Google, which runs a generative AI model. Response body or authentication and cookie headers in network requests are not included in the data sent to the server.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"8c444820-1bfc-4175-98d0-a0dc2a37a380","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E42C3836276B5F6EE575F667D57F08870F1164B0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Settings for DevTools Generative AI Features' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow DevTools Generative AI Features)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tDevToolsGenAiSettings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275782","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275782","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275782","severity":"medium","group_title":"GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275782r1106672_rule","rule_id":"SV-275782r1106672","rule_version":"DTBC-0077","rule_title":"GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for GenAI local foundational model\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not download model","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"1\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configure how Google Chrome downloads the foundational GenAI model and uses it for inference locally.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Allowed (0) or not set, the model is downloaded automatically, and used for inference.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Disabled (1), the model will not be downloaded.\n\nModel downloading can also be disabled by ComponentUpdatesEnabled.\n\n0 = Downloads model automatically\n1 = Do not download model","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"d57764ca-d2a4-41a7-b0ac-5e6b7aab11b8","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 130A67732E99CFBA0ACD0B2352EFA2E05481F5E3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Settings for GenAI local foundational model' is NOT Enabled: (Do not download model)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tGenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275783","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275783","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275783","severity":"medium","group_title":"Help Me Write must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275783r1106612_rule","rule_id":"SV-275783r1106612","rule_version":"DTBC-0078","rule_title":"Help Me Write must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings forSettings for Help Me Write\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Help Me Write","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Help Me Write is an AI-based writing assistant for short-form content on the web. Suggested content is based on prompts entered by the user and the content of the web page.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"ffb99316-06e2-475c-9cb7-2c4cde36fc95","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B543F73FEE7FCBC5B9914664721A4DF60E323CD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Settings forSettings for Help Me Write' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow Help Me Write)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tHelpMeWriteSettings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275784","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275784","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275784","severity":"medium","group_title":"AI-powered History Search must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275784r1106615_rule","rule_id":"SV-275784r1106615","rule_version":"DTBC-0079","rule_title":"AI-powered History Search must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for AI-powered History Search\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow AI History Search","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HistorySearchSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HistorySearchSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"AI History Search is a feature that allows users to search their browsing history and receive generated answers based on page contents and not just the page title and URL.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"661a1d26-eb16-4a7a-bc61-bdac8cdf4539","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C0C663B621D19FC631BA54C585E1C7F1BBCD2CE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Settings for AI-powered History Search' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow AI History Search)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tHistorySearchSettings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-275785","group_tree":[{"id":"V-275785","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-275785","severity":"medium","group_title":"Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-275785r1106673_rule","rule_id":"SV-275785r1106673","rule_version":"DTBC-0080","rule_title":"Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Tab Compare settings\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Tab Compare","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"TabCompareSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"TabCompareSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Tab Compare is an AI-powered tool for comparing information across a user's tabs. For example, the feature can be offered to the user when multiple tabs with products in a similar category are open.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4081","uuid":"edb4177c-8ecf-4599-8837-75cb4919fbaa","stig_uuid":"3466ecf1-3965-400a-868f-b5da0fd059f3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-GoogleChrome_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B906ECDBA84403FEF3B90B18F51CCBE06AB47BB2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Tab Compare settings' is NOT Enabled: (Do not allow Tab Compare)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\r\nValue Name:\tTabCompareSettings (Not found)"}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:16:16.4125231-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus","stig_id":"MS_Defender_Antivirus","release_info":"Release: 8 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","reference_identifier":"3985","size":67,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-213426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213426","title":"SRG-APP-000279","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213426","severity":"high","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block the Potentially Unwanted Application (PUA) feature.","rule_id_src":"SV-213426r961197_rule","rule_id":"SV-213426r961197","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000001","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block the Potentially Unwanted Application (PUA) feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Configure Detection for Potentially Unwanted Applications\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Configure detection for potentially unwanted applications\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"After enabling this feature, PUA protection blocking takes effect on endpoint clients after the next signature update or computer restart. Signature updates take place daily under typical circumstances. PUA will be blocked and automatically quarantined.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89827","V-75147"],"ccis":["CCI-001243"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"137828a7-75a6-4744-9fe4-e8f11f47c6b9","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C7FC06565FEA810294E41A9022EDB35C5ACF5CAF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Detection for Potentially Unwanted Applications' is NOT Enabled: (Block)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tPUAProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213427","title":"SRG-APP-000279","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213427","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to automatically take action on all detected tasks.","rule_id_src":"SV-213427r961197_rule","rule_id":"SV-213427r961197","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000003","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to automatically take action on all detected tasks.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off routine remediation\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off routine remediation\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRoutinelyTakingAction\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows Microsoft Defender configuration to automatically take action on all detected threats. The action to be taken on a particular threat is determined by the combination of the policy-defined action user-defined action and the signature-defined action. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender does not automatically take action on the detected threats but prompts users to choose from the actions available for each threat. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender automatically takes action on all detected threats after a nonconfigurable delay of approximately five seconds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89831","V-75151"],"ccis":["CCI-001243"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"4615aaf1-afe8-4a36-947a-41f7f3490e59","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ABDB93559511DC25B0CA77F5904ED48AD2C425D7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off routine remediation' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tDisableRoutinelyTakingAction (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213428","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213428","severity":"high","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to run and scan for malware and other potentially unwanted software.","rule_id_src":"SV-213428r1190706_rule","rule_id":"SV-213428r1190706","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000004","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to run and scan for malware and other potentially unwanted software.","fix_text":"For Windows 10: Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus \"Turn off Microsoft Defender Antivirus\" to \"Not Configured\". \n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> \"Turn off Windows Defender Antivirus\" is set to “Not Configured”.\n\nFor Windows 10:\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAntiSpyware\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off Microsoft Defender Antivirus. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus does not run and computers are not scanned for malware or other potentially unwanted software. \n\nWhen the setting is disabled and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, the two applications can both simultaneously try to protect the system. The two AV solutions both attempt to quarantine the same threat and will fight for access to delete the file. Users will see conflicts and the system may lock up until the two solutions finish processing. \n\nWhen the setting is not configured and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, both applications coexist on the system without conflicts. Defender Antivirus will automatically disable itself and will enable if the third-party solution stops functioning. When the setting is not configured and Defender Antivirus is the only AV solution, Defender AV will run (default state) and receive definition updates. An administrator account is needed to turn off the service. A standard user cannot disable the service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89833","V-75153"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"51cce027-485f-4d50-a196-366fe8ad818d","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 78186B5BF154B089D6C1DF68308701B7215A0A3A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Microsoft Defender Antivirus' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tDisableAntiSpyware (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213429","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213429","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files for scanning.","rule_id_src":"SV-213429r1190707_rule","rule_id":"SV-213429r1190707","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000005","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files for scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Path Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Path Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured.\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n \nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Paths\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for files under the paths specified or for the fully qualified resources specified. Paths should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of a path or a fully qualified resource name. As an example, a path might be defined as: \"c:\\Windows\" to exclude all files in this directory. A fully qualified resource name might be defined as: \"C:\\Windows\\App.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.\n\nExceptions can be made to allow file/folders that are impacting enterprise applications to be excluded from being scanned. All exclusions should be documented and approved.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89835","V-75155"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"00269346-7af0-4b44-8aa7-74ab28d85de9","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FAE20D21FC17E8B9435F62A2F6023FA99C176B72\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Path Exclusions' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\r\nValue Name:\tExclusions_Paths (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213430","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213430","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213430","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files opened by specified processes.","rule_id_src":"SV-213430r1190710_rule","rule_id":"SV-213430r1190710","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000006","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files opened by specified processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Process Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Process Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Processes\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for any file opened by any of the specified processes. The process itself will not be excluded. To exclude the process, use the Path exclusion. Processes should be added under the options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of the path to the process image. Note that only executables can be excluded. For example, a process might be defined as: \"c:\\windows\\app.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89837","V-75157"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"9d2a1d81-cfbe-4275-a65e-0039a030c0d9","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9946AF5745006B487E7684CFFCC608CFF33570B3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Process Exclusions' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\r\nValue Name:\tExclusions_Processes (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213431","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213431","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable the Automatic Exclusions feature.","rule_id_src":"SV-213431r1190712_rule","rule_id":"SV-213431r1190712","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000007","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable the Automatic Exclusions feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Exclusions >> \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAutoExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows an administrator to specify if Automatic Exclusions feature for Server SKUs should be turned off.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89839","V-75159"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"91a852a4-3b18-49e4-bec0-aee4038a835c","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: C2E8C99880C04B3C1B8C2162EA89891E717EAB8E\r\n~~~~~\r\nUnable to access HKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\r\nMost likely due to V-278658 being configured which, by design of the group policy setting, prevents access to this registry path."},{"group_id_src":"V-213432","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213432","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213432","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to disable local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS.","rule_id_src":"SV-213432r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213432r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000008","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to disable local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideSpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to join Microsoft MAPS. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89841","V-75161"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"99a048ee-cfa9-4dfe-bfd7-222c28f42eec","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7CC150E5C81F0F0FDED11CFEECA839B936981054\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideSpynetReporting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213433","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213433","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check in real time with MAPS before content is run or accessed.","rule_id_src":"SV-213433r1190715_rule","rule_id":"SV-213433r1190715","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000009","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check in real time with MAPS before content is run or accessed.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBlockAtFirstSeen\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature ensures the device checks in real time with the Microsoft Active Protection Service (MAPS) before allowing certain content to be run or accessed. If this feature is disabled, the check will not occur, which will lower the protection state of the device. \n\nEnabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned on. \nDisabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned off. \n\nThis feature requires these Group Policy settings to be set as follows: \nMAPS >> The \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nMAPS >> The \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" should be set to 1 (Send safe samples) or 3 (Send all samples). Setting to 0 (Always Prompt) will lower the protection state of the device. Setting to 2 (Never send) means the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection >> The \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" policy must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection >> Do not enable the \"Turn off real-time protection\" policy or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89843","V-75163"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"d6301b51-83fe-4dac-aadd-f6d2dd7bff51","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 619644F56D474A517A1FA0FDF55E13BC6ABFD1D4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\r\nValue Name:\tDisableBlockAtFirstSeen (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213434","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213434","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must join Microsoft MAPS.","rule_id_src":"SV-213434r1134051_rule","rule_id":"SV-213434r1134051","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000010","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must join Microsoft MAPS.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is Not Applicable.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Basic MAPS\" or \"Advanced MAPS\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems, this is Not Applicable.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Advanced MAPS\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, or REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows joining Microsoft MAPS. Microsoft MAPS is the online community that helps in choosing how to respond to potential threats. The community also helps stop the spread of new malicious software infections. You can choose to send basic or additional information about detected software. Additional information helps Microsoft create new definitions and protect your computer. This information can include things like location of detected items on your computer if harmful software was removed. The information will be automatically collected and sent. In some instances personal information might unintentionally be sent to Microsoft. However Microsoft will not use this information to identify you or contact you. \n\nPossible options are: \n(0x0) Disabled (default) \n(0x1) Basic membership \n(0x2) Advanced membership \n\nBasic membership will send basic information to Microsoft about software that has been detected, including where the software came from, the actions that you apply or that are applied automatically, and whether the actions were successful. Advanced membership will send, in addition to basic information, more information to Microsoft about malicious software spyware and potentially unwanted software, including the location of the software file names, how the software operates, and how it has impacted your computer. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, you will join Microsoft MAPS with the membership specified. If this setting is disabled or do not configured, you will not join Microsoft MAPS. In Windows 10, Basic membership is no longer available, so setting the value to 1 or 2 enrolls the device into Advanced membership.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89847","V-75167"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"f3346f9b-f085-4063-a5c6-17c470ce9b07","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B530A98C879AF7CBFAF04B206FD23AD52B2915DB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Join Microsoft MAPS' is NOT Enabled: (Basic MAPS or Advanced MAPS)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\r\nValue Name:\tSpynetReporting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213435","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213435","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to only send safe samples for MAPS telemetry.","rule_id_src":"SV-213435r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213435r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000011","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to only send safe samples for MAPS telemetry.","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Send safe samples\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MAPS >> \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Send safe samples\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SubmitSamplesConsent\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures behavior of samples submission when opt-in for MAPS telemetry is set. Possible options are:  \n(0x0) Always prompt\n(0x1) Send safe samples automatically \n(0x2) Never send  \n(0x3) Send all samples automatically","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89887","V-75207"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"e939807b-69d9-4fa2-a7b0-2410ff671da8","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B1B97BE9C141FFA7DC821B2489E41CD603524EC2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Send file samples when further analysis is required' is NOT Enabled: (Send safe samples)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\r\nValue Name:\tSubmitSamplesConsent (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213436","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213436","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for protocol recognition for network protection.","rule_id_src":"SV-213436r1190716_rule","rule_id":"SV-213436r1190716","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000012","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for protocol recognition for network protection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> \"Turn on protocol recognition\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> \"Turn on protocol recognition\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableProtocolRecognition\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of protocol recognition for network protection against exploits of known vulnerabilities. If this setting is enabled or not configured, protocol recognition will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, protocol recognition will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89889","V-75209"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"baef5086-48ea-4638-8b2b-49dd0558c015","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B99D18DB86085030F4ABB95900F2E3BC02A7EB1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on protocol recognition' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\r\nValue Name:\tDisableProtocolRecognition (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213437","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213437","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow local override of monitoring for file and program activity.","rule_id_src":"SV-213437r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-213437r960921","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000013","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow local override of monitoring for file and program activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for file and program activity on your computer. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89891","V-75211"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"a2907a1f-e1f1-4420-8a2f-9608d3ad6446","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 02AC4D8747858C096703B2C573FFB4BF656EFB27\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideDisableOnAccessProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213438","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213438","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity.","rule_id_src":"SV-213438r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-213438r960921","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000014","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideRealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89893","V-75213"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"58b42d53-051a-4b5b-bb09-d9316d381e67","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7352BA464FDA92944310A151DC4806EA957F6B3D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideRealtimeScanDirection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213439","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213439","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of scanning for downloaded files and attachments.","rule_id_src":"SV-213439r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-213439r961089","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000015","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of scanning for downloaded files and attachments.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89895","V-75215"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"e46c6e54-7540-4c37-9e67-0456d5339dc3","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0AB80E9A9B50F0F135FA68DABED11ECE2064F969\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideDisableIOAVProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213440","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213440","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of behavior monitoring.","rule_id_src":"SV-213440r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213440r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000016","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of behavior monitoring.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of behavior monitoring. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89897","V-75217"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"cb835f86-0b4d-468a-85dc-82649b08f458","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AC8D482B0B109A76B373FB22A8755E9E9DF27C09\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideDisableBehaviorMonitoring (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213441","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213441","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV Group Policy settings must take priority over the local preference settings.","rule_id_src":"SV-213441r1190717_rule","rule_id":"SV-213441r1190717","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000017","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV Group Policy settings must take priority over the local preference settings.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to turn on real-time protection. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89899","V-75219"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"0e0ef60d-0ac5-4902-9b7d-18b2fc2605de","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 29B605991C03D3AC1F711A99E9452AA8F257C7A8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tLocalSettingOverrideDisableRealtimeMonitoring (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213442","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213442","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must monitor for incoming and outgoing files.","rule_id_src":"SV-213442r1190718_rule","rule_id":"SV-213442r1190718","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000018","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must monitor for incoming and outgoing files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" is set to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1 or 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing files without having to turn off monitoring entirely. It is recommended for use on servers that have a lot of incoming and outgoing file activity but for performance reasons need to have scanning disabled for a particular scan direction. The appropriate configuration should be evaluated based on the server role. Note that this configuration is only honored for NTFS volumes. For any other file system type, full monitoring of file and program activity will be present on those volumes. \n\nThe options for this setting are mutually exclusive: \n0 = Scan incoming and outgoing files (default) \n1 = Scan incoming files only \n2 = Scan outgoing files only \n\nAny other value, or if the value does not exist, resolves to the default (0). If this setting is enabled, the specified type of monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, monitoring for incoming and outgoing files will be enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89901","V-75221"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"22263bf7-b48b-4dee-a683-a4dc7f0e4118","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 12D8055BF62D810CB7010818C3860B3C889B9BD9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tRealtimeScanDirection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213443","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213443","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to monitor for file and program activity.","rule_id_src":"SV-213443r1190719_rule","rule_id":"SV-213443r1190719","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000019","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to monitor for file and program activity.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer to be scanned\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of monitoring for file and program activity. If this setting is enabled or not configured, monitoring for file and program activity will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, monitoring for file and program activity will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89903","V-75223"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"21fc8d4d-df8b-404a-8787-496bfbb3d85c","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9AAD86CBCA15C4267CDB3B6C8EDF7678577FCED2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Monitor file and program activity on your computer' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableOnAccessProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213444","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213444","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan all downloaded files and attachments.","rule_id_src":"SV-213444r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-213444r961089","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000020","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan all downloaded files and attachments.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. If this setting is enabled or not configured, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89905","V-75225"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"ca32b7a8-b698-4ba2-99f7-727b405804c9","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F5FD6FE65A8D71BB280D04B5D524B15EBDC72F4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scan all downloaded files and attachments' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableIOAVProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213445","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213445","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.","rule_id_src":"SV-213445r1190720_rule","rule_id":"SV-213445r1190720","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000021","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn off real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn off real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off real-time protection prompts for known malware detection. Microsoft Defender Antivirus alerts when malware or potentially unwanted software attempts to install itself or to run on a user's computer. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will not prompt users to take actions on malware detections. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will prompt users to take actions on malware detections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89907","V-75227"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"4697a773-44dc-4ba0-8780-9cfcf3105286","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 34493A84041496FB0F8C481394EFF0D780FB65F4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off real-time protection' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableRealtimeMonitoring (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213446","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213446","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.","rule_id_src":"SV-213446r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213446r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000022","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of behavior monitoring. If this setting is enabled or not configured, behavior monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, behavior monitoring will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89909","V-75229"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"8545fd78-b4bc-4b2d-a6ab-be16a0c0d065","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 82F45363713D9D87885D2BEA10DEBC1A2F4595BA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on behavior monitoring' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableBehaviorMonitoring (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213447","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213447","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-213447r1190721_rule","rule_id":"SV-213447r1190721","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000023","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of process scanning when real-time protection is turned on. This helps to catch malware, which could start when real-time protection is turned off. If this setting is enabled or not configured, a process scan will be initiated when real-time protection is turned on. If this setting is disabled, a process scan will not be initiated when real-time protection is turned on.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89911","V-75231"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"f975a183-b27a-4c42-bb06-cd010a491608","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 18F1A071AFD31C43536ADA100FA376942633793C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableScanOnRealtimeEnable (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213448","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213448","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.","rule_id_src":"SV-213448r1190722_rule","rule_id":"SV-213448r1190722","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000024","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan archive files\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan archive files\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableArchiveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of scans for malicious software and unwanted software in archive files such as .ZIP or .CAB files. If this setting is enabled or not configured, archive files will be scanned. If this setting is disabled, archive files will not be scanned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89913","V-75233"],"ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"a942c831-69ec-438f-afe9-1940b2216ac8","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4726957B2F3AC7BD524B428E1090CF015CDC6721\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scan archive files' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tDisableArchiveScanning (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213449","title":"SRG-APP-000073","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213449","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.","rule_id_src":"SV-213449r960852_rule","rule_id":"SV-213449r960852","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000025","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan removable drives\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Scan removable drives\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRemovableDriveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether or not to scan for malicious software and unwanted software in the contents of removable drives such as USB flash drives when running a full scan. If this setting is enabled, removable drives will be scanned during any type of scan. If this setting is disabled or not configured, removable drives will not be scanned during a full scan. Removable drives may still be scanned during quick scan and custom scan.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89915","V-75235"],"ccis":["CCI-000870"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"fd3a63c2-7898-4a93-9d96-5462d37991de","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 612C48357821EC187286B1EEC07B71A7C47F3F22\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scan removable drives' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tDisableRemovableDriveScanning (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213450","title":"SRG-APP-000277","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213450","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.","rule_id_src":"SV-213450r961191_rule","rule_id":"SV-213450r961191","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000026","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" to \"Enabled \" and select anything other than \"Never\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" is set to \"Enabled\" and anything other than \"Never\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0x8, this is a finding.\n\nValues of 0x0 through 0x7 are acceptable and not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to perform a scheduled scan. The scan can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day  \n(0x1) Sunday  \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never (default)  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, a scheduled scan will run at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, a scheduled scan will run at a default frequency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89917","V-75237"],"ccis":["CCI-001241"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"13614985-20f0-41cd-9724-8cc3993fc09d","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 77440735D612AC4CD488D1812D0187BAF38ECBF1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan' is NOT Enabled: (Anything other than 'Never')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tScheduleDay (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213451","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213451","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.","rule_id_src":"SV-213451r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213451r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000027","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableEmailScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of e-mail scanning. When e-mail scanning is enabled, the engine will parse the mailbox and mail files according to their specific format in order to analyze the mail bodies and attachments. Several e-mail formats are currently supported, for example: pst (Outlook), dbx mbx mime (Outlook Express), binhex (Mac). If this setting is enabled, e-mail scanning will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, e-mail scanning will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89919","V-75239"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"61115956-7a92-4901-8259-b2a145e04b7b","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 35D6CDCB54D0D4BCCFAFBD8EBED8EDC36F69B7F2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on e-mail scanning' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tDisableEmailScanning (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213452","title":"SRG-APP-000276","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213452","severity":"high","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.","rule_id_src":"SV-213452r1190723_rule","rule_id":"SV-213452r1190723","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000028","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Define the number of days before spyware security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antispyware is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender AV spyware age requirement will be NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ASSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before spyware definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89921","V-75241"],"ccis":["CCI-004964"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"8f20de20-58b0-477d-8866-68fade4a9eb3","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 78872193AD2CB9B3156F2214D764ECDA5754C7D0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date' is NOT Enabled: (7 or less but not 0)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\r\nValue Name:\tASSignatureDue (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213453","title":"SRG-APP-000276","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213453","severity":"high","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.","rule_id_src":"SV-213453r1190724_rule","rule_id":"SV-213453r1190724","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000029","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >>Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Define the number of days before virus security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antivirus protection is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender Antivirus age requirement is NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AVSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before virus definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default, this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89923","V-75243"],"ccis":["CCI-004964"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"cea2a302-4050-46a6-8fd9-cccade28d423","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ECC9F98B0A39AB93823E6E8FEBC6B55DB186729E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date' is NOT Enabled: (7 or less but not 0)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\r\nValue Name:\tAVSignatureDue (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213454","title":"SRG-APP-000261","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213454","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.","rule_id_src":"SV-213454r961161_rule","rule_id":"SV-213454r961161","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000030","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Signature Updates >> \"Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Every Day\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Security Intelligence Updates >> \"Specify the day of the week to check for security intelligence updates\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Every Day\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to check for definition updates. The check can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day (default)  \n(0x1) Sunday   \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, the check for definition updates will occur at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, the check for definition updates will occur at a default frequency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89925","V-75245"],"ccis":["CCI-001308"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"ecb31deb-49ad-4359-b63d-a0706aa51a4e","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B65049F950030E4B813F2F6BC04F87DDAC53CBD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates' is NOT Enabled: (Every Day)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\r\nValue Name:\tScheduleDay (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213455","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213455","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.","rule_id_src":"SV-213455r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213455r961086","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000031","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Show…\" option box and enter \"5\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the “Show…” box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"5\" and the \"Value\" field  contains \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89927","V-75247"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"538f00e3-7eaf-405a-924b-644ecf9f6d7b","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D6F5B375CD6B32E639F826A783002733C6E12F89\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected' is NOT Enabled: (5 in Value Name and 2 or 3 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\r\nValue Name:\t5 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213456","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213456","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.","rule_id_src":"SV-213456r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213456r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000032","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled”.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule blocks the following file types from being run or launched from an email seen in either Microsoft Outlook or webmail (such as Gmail.com or Outlook.com):\nExecutable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr)\nScript files (such as a PowerShell .ps, VisualBasic .vbs, or JavaScript .js file)\nScript archive files","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92661","V-77965"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"faec899f-6743-4234-bff2-c4772bfc1365","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1679E3F532BE08A005D0367B55CD1689BF9261C2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550 in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\tBE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213457","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213457","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.","rule_id_src":"SV-213457r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213457r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000033","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled”.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word or Excel, will not be allowed to create child processes. This is a typical malware behavior, especially for macro-based attacks that attempt to use Office apps to launch or download malicious executables.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92663","V-77967"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"8ff9bf3f-3e17-41f7-838e-dfc99d3e5aac","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1EB8D12A0A10D83B6F1BBDCCDCE98D276FCB8E9E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\tD4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213458","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213458","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.","rule_id_src":"SV-213458r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213458r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000034","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled”.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\nValue:  1\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule targets typical behaviors used by suspicious and malicious add-ons and scripts (extensions) that create or launch executable files. This is a typical malware technique. Extensions will be blocked from being used by Office apps. Typically these extensions use the Windows Scripting Host (.wsh files) to run scripts that automate certain tasks or provide user-created add-on features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92665","V-77969"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"9e301d93-5db7-4de4-803f-c2f15c301064","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 22ACA506FCBB88473C2175B323ECBB107073C1F4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899 in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213459","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213459","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.","rule_id_src":"SV-213459r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213459r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000035","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled”.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word, Excel, or PowerPoint, will not be able to inject code into other processes. This is typically used by malware to run malicious code in an attempt to hide the activity from antivirus scanning engines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92667","V-77971"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"3b1dc641-c489-4280-813a-f0007872347a","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E5EA0CC762F217A5BBEDD9DBF62DF45E9C66DF6B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84 in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213460","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213460","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.","rule_id_src":"SV-213460r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213460r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000036","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D \nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript and VBScript scripts can be used by malware to launch other malicious apps. This rule prevents these scripts from being allowed to launch apps, thus preventing malicious use of the scripts to spread malware and infect machines.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92669","V-77973"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"9a0ad0a6-bb29-4772-aae1-89704952d398","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5882616CDE2A8E08542595621BB7CE93EFEB2F21\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\tD3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213461","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213461","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.","rule_id_src":"SV-213461r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213461r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000037","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled”.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malware and other threats can attempt to obfuscate or hide their malicious code in some script files. This rule prevents scripts that appear to be obfuscated from running. It uses the AntiMalwareScanInterface (AMSI) to determine if a script is potentially obfuscated and then blocks such a script or blocks scripts when an attempt is made to access them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92671","V-77975"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"7d8cbf0a-b0fd-49ff-bbc2-44933a80832c","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4FFE559AA4D25D9D1FFBF1DFF5D6754FA8F26123\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213462","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213462","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.","rule_id_src":"SV-213462r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213462r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000038","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" and the Value to \"1\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This rule blocks potentially malicious behavior by not allowing macro code to execute routines in the Win 32 dynamic link library (DLL).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92673","V-77977"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"888751c0-d51e-4484-80b1-c762a66ef47d","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C125401687EA471C8E09FA02BE4216DC5A761E1D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B in Value Name and 1 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213463","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213463","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.","rule_id_src":"SV-213463r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-213463r961092","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000039","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Windows Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Block\" in the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10, it is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" is set to \"Enabled” and \"Block\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableNetworkProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard network protection to prevent employees from using any application to access dangerous domains that may host phishing scams, exploit-hosting sites, and other malicious content on the internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92675","V-77979"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"0b0830d5-f76b-45c0-95f7-22ddf5a83059","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 79D963D665050721792CB67DC8947014A0C53C4B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites' is NOT Enabled: (Block)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\r\nValue Name:\tEnableNetworkProtection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213464","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213464","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213464","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.","rule_id_src":"SV-213464r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213464r961086","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000040","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Show…\" option box and enter \"4\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Show…\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"4\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"4\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94669","V-79965"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"6608d7ca-fd80-465a-ac3c-136e651bbe6d","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B69E0EB853487067955AEED3EADE9ED7B4D76023\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected' is NOT Enabled: (4 in Value Name and 2 or 3 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\r\nValue Name:\t4 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213465","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213465","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.","rule_id_src":"SV-213465r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213465r961086","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000041","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Show…\" option box and enter \"2\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Show…\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"2\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"2\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94671","V-79967"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"f8fd2f38-6038-4860-a1ff-b188ea28a55d","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EDB3CC9ED3A457609C7044F5B75789C016ECD8DE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected' is NOT Enabled: (2 in Value Name and 2 or 3 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\r\nValue Name:\t2 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-213466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-213466","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-213466","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Low.","rule_id_src":"SV-213466r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-213466r961086","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000042","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Low.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Show…\" option box and enter \"1\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Threats >> \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the \"Show…\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"1\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"1\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94675","V-79971"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"c009dc51-697e-4169-a6f5-a0059a879c3e","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 90D3CD8573A71518F7BB96300306422139F211FB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected' is NOT Enabled: (1 in Value Name and 2 or 3 in Value)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\r\nValue Name:\t1 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278647","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278647","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278647","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.","rule_id_src":"SV-278647r1190726_rule","rule_id":"SV-278647r1190726","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000043","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Adobe Reader from launching other processes, which can help mitigate security risks associated with malicious PDF files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"382b077e-287e-4c4e-b359-d38434a38e21","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3CBE6091AF7FAAE5507A4B394DA680E370B0DA3A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name '7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278648","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278648","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278648","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.","rule_id_src":"SV-278648r1190728_rule","rule_id":"SV-278648r1190728","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000044","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevent credential stealing by locking down Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS). ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"28ff1327-320c-481e-8695-ba8252bdde73","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C4D92AE2F92B08B7AB86A417916902686E73A1A4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name '9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278649","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278649","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278649","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.","rule_id_src":"SV-278649r1190730_rule","rule_id":"SV-278649r1190730","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000045","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevents unsigned or untrusted executable files from running from USB removable drives, including SD cards. Blocked file types include executable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr). ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"711c05ce-0db0-42e6-a552-2389a4312195","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 77D6BC32E175AC61FA9723DF19CBF01954305672\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name 'b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\tb2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278650","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278650","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278650","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.","rule_id_src":"SV-278650r1190732_rule","rule_id":"SV-278650r1190732","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000046","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting provides an extra layer of protection against ransomware. It uses both client and cloud heuristics to determine whether a file resembles ransomware. This rule does not block files that have one or more of the following characteristics:\n\n- The file is found to be unharmful in the Microsoft cloud.\n- The file is a valid signed file.\n- The file is prevalent enough to not be considered as ransomware.\n- The rule tends to err on the side of caution to prevent ransomware.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"65582c60-a916-41c7-925a-2489d9d57a04","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 51F72D7733CB413BA052A47EA7988140E38DEE7C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name 'c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\tc1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278651","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278651","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278651","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.","rule_id_src":"SV-278651r1190734_rule","rule_id":"SV-278651r1190734","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000047","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting blocks processes created through PsExec and WMI from running. Both PsExec and WMI can remotely execute code. There is a risk of malware abusing functionality of PsExec and WMI for command and control purposes, or to spread an infection throughout an organization's network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"f7f50f17-b1e3-47ff-bc2a-dfae8914a302","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 87A5326D17DBF95D45F1ABDEB822F34887DD40A1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name 'd1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c' and Value '2')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\td1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278652","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278652","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278652","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit persistence through WMI event subscription.","rule_id_src":"SV-278652r1190736_rule","rule_id":"SV-278652r1190736","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000048","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit persistence through WMI event subscription.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents malware from abusing WMI to attain persistence on a device.\n\nFileless threats employ various tactics to stay hidden, to avoid being seen in the file system, and to gain periodic execution control. Some threats can abuse the WMI repository and event model to stay hidden.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"b93e9484-f7d7-4ca4-9848-2541b2f5e8c7","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B0A62E0998C24FB209EE59360D26CE07B075379D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name 'e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b' and Value '2')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\te6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278653","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278653","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278653","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit executable files from running unless they meet a prevalence, age, or trusted list criterion.","rule_id_src":"SV-278653r1190738_rule","rule_id":"SV-278653r1190738","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000049","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must audit executable files from running unless they meet a prevalence, age, or trusted list criterion.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting blocks executable files, such as .exe, .dll, or .scr, from launching. Thus, launching untrusted or unknown executable files can be risky, as it might not be initially clear if the files are malicious.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"0a5ac46d-65a4-4f48-90ae-c810a01fb831","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CE6CE315B48DDC7851C5F831FC9656D8CB7764EB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name '01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278654","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278654","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278654","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.","rule_id_src":"SV-278654r1190740_rule","rule_id":"SV-278654r1190740","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000050","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Outlook from creating child processes while still allowing legitimate Outlook functions. This rule protects against social engineering attacks and prevents exploiting code from abusing vulnerabilities in Outlook. It also protects against Outlook rules and forms exploits that attackers can use when a user's credentials are compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"b1786122-9a2f-4b7d-92cc-233d95ef889b","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4361D4C2804736B5F17F2BA6B6BE297F3D93F520\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name '26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278655","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278655","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278655","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.","rule_id_src":"SV-278655r1190742_rule","rule_id":"SV-278655r1190742","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000051","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Attack Surface Reduction >> Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents an application from writing a vulnerable signed driver to disk. Vulnerable signed drivers can be exploited by local applications that have sufficient privileges to gain access to the kernel. Vulnerable signed drivers enable attackers to disable or circumvent security solutions, eventually leading to system compromise.\n\nThe Block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers rule does not block a driver already existing on the system from being loaded.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"f8120692-63a2-4f4e-a094-6b9f37783a53","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D13DC9B90DC8CDEDF506060786685AF6774B536\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules' is NOT Enabled: (Rule: Value Name '56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5' and Value '1')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\r\nValue Name:\t56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278656","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278656","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278656","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.","rule_id_src":"SV-278656r1190744_rule","rule_id":"SV-278656r1190744","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000052","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists is set to \"Enabled\". Otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableLocalAdminMerge\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures how locally defined lists are combined or merged with globally defined lists. This setting applies to exclusion lists, specified remediation lists, and attack surface reduction.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"89514271-2e6b-47c0-b060-0e8de3f2ed39","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3BDE8BAC486A353DB9834FC610D561F0B4B0C30E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tDisableLocalAdminMerge (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278658","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278658","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278658","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.","rule_id_src":"SV-278658r1190746_rule","rule_id":"SV-278658r1190746","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000054","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is \"0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabled (Default): If this setting is not configured or disabled, local admins can see exclusions in the Windows Security App or via PowerShell.\n\nEnabled: If this setting is enabled, local admins no longer see the exclusion list in Windows Security App or via PowerShell.O13.\n\nNote: Applying this setting will not remove exclusions, it only prevents them from being visible to local admins. This is reflected in?Get-MpPreference.I13.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"1adcd21b-d20c-4f3b-986a-fe94a60c74b1","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D62E1A0642FF73C70A318566B1B9CE8908CBAA1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tHideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278659","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278659","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278659","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must randomize scheduled task times.","rule_id_src":"SV-278659r1190748_rule","rule_id":"SV-278659r1190748","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000055","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must randomize scheduled task times.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Randomize scheduled task times to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Randomize scheduled task times is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RandomizeScheduleTaskTimes\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, randomize the start time of the scan to any interval from 0 to 23 hours. By default, scheduled tasks begin at a random time within four hours of the time specified in Task Scheduler.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"30d4866a-a22a-4fc0-8031-60cd477971f0","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D8D093556E1FE1A1915ED83CABE31D4B8122FDB9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Randomize scheduled task times' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\r\nValue Name:\tRandomizeScheduleTaskTimes (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278660","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278660","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278660","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must hide the Family options area.","rule_id_src":"SV-278660r1190750_rule","rule_id":"SV-278660r1190750","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000056","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must hide the Family options area.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Security >> Family Options >> Hide the Family options area to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Security >> Family Options >> Hide the Family options area is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\Family options\n\nCriteria: If the value \"UILockdown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Family options section contains links to settings and further information for parents of a Windows PC. It is not intended for enterprise or business environments.\n\nThis section can be hidden from users of the machine. This option can be useful if you do not want users in the organization to see or have access to this section.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"86249029-9a67-477b-9bce-08e5dd52e286","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B684153AFF743E8791FE7A962F047897A75BC4E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Hide the Family options area' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\Family options\r\nValue Name:\tUILockdown (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278661","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278661","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278661","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable the file hash computation feature.","rule_id_src":"SV-278661r1190752_rule","rule_id":"SV-278661r1190752","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000057","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable the file hash computation feature.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >>Enable file hash computation feature to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Enable file hash computation feature is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableFileHashComputation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy drives the ability to enforce Indicators of Compromise (IoC) by using file hash allow/block indicators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"82a8c97f-e090-4e1b-82df-928952a4400a","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1AE775AFC4C0D736355AB0C2DD5871B789A605CD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable file hash computation feature' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\r\nValue Name:\tEnableFileHashComputation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278662","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278662","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278662","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable extended cloud check.","rule_id_src":"SV-278662r1190754_rule","rule_id":"SV-278662r1190754","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000058","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable extended cloud check.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Configure extended cloud check to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Configure extended cloud check is set to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpBafsExtendedTimeout\" is REG_DWORD = 50, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 50, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Microsoft Defender Antivirus finds a suspicious file, it can prevent the file from running while it queries the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.\n\nThe default period that the file is blocked is 10 seconds. Extending the cloud block timeout period can help ensure there is enough time to receive a proper determination from the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"89416754-2c9b-47fa-b58e-1730d62609c7","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B899FA748FFF89CCA7726BEFE86B12EEEF045BE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure extended cloud check' is NOT Enabled: (50)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\r\nValue Name:\tMpBafsExtendedTimeout (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278668","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278668","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278668","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable script scanning.","rule_id_src":"SV-278668r1190756_rule","rule_id":"SV-278668r1190756","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000064","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable script scanning.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Turn on script scanning to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Turn on script scanning is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScriptScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"3e63a6c9-5e95-4895-8612-b3745790d85f","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5BED640ED30268549E87C51451B29677CA1CE675\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on script scanning' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDisableScriptScanning (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278669","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278669","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278669","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE.","rule_id_src":"SV-278669r1190758_rule","rule_id":"SV-278669r1190758","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000065","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Real-time Protection >> Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"OobeEnableRtpAndSigUpdate\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"ec9a4bed-37e8-408b-8895-bfe5ed1f3145","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 10E395F20DD2B983DF5D462AD1B9F1459108BD6C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\r\nValue Name:\tOobeEnableRtpAndSigUpdate (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278672","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278672","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278672","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable network protection to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server.","rule_id_src":"SV-278672r1190761_rule","rule_id":"SV-278672r1190761","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000068","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable network protection to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: This requirement is not applicable to desktops.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard >> Network Protection >> This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowNetworkProtectionOnWinServer\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft's Exploit Guard comprises several techniques to defend against phishing attacks and malware. These include controlled folder access, attack surface reduction, and network protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"8de59537-6e62-4e84-8b62-33efaec5d1dd","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-278674","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278674","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278674","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable EDR in block mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-278674r1190763_rule","rule_id":"SV-278674r1190763","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000070","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable EDR in block mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Features >> Enable EDR in block mode to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Features >> Enable EDR in block mode is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Features\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PassiveRemediation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"EDR in block mode allows Microsoft Defender Antivirus to take actions on post-breach, behavioral EDR detections. EDR in block mode is integrated with threat and vulnerability management capabilities. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"ba69857d-96fd-4ac1-9ee4-9cbedf8d4601","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 42A340F7A7C7CB9F381071E4A01577049452B0A1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable EDR in block mode' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Features\r\nValue Name:\tPassiveRemediation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278675","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278675","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278675","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must report Dynamic Signature dropped events.","rule_id_src":"SV-278675r1190765_rule","rule_id":"SV-278675r1190765","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000071","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must report Dynamic Signature dropped events.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Reporting >> Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Reporting >> Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Reporting\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus logs \"Dynamic Signature dropped\" events when it blocks or removes a file based on a dynamically updated signature, but the signature itself is dropped, meaning it was not fully processed or applied. This can indicate a potential issue with signature updates or the system's ability to handle them.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"186860f5-2666-4516-84cf-8705d14f8ab4","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6E5BF51C8179F7A33E59C2ECC81514CC9C895798\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Reporting\r\nValue Name:\tEnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278676","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278676","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278676","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan excluded files and directories during quick scans.","rule_id_src":"SV-278676r1190767_rule","rule_id":"SV-278676r1190767","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000072","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan excluded files and directories during quick scans.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"QuickScanIncludeExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, when an exclusion for a file or folder is created, it will generally be skipped during both real-time protection and on-demand scans (including quick scans and full scans). However, with newer releases, the option exists to configure quick scans to include files and directories that are otherwise excluded from real-time protection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"daeab7ae-aa9f-4945-93d6-4d8590e08859","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 882CCED8379D33FDDA7FCA9B908BD360F377E93F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans' is NOT Enabled: (1)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tQuickScanIncludeExclusions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278677","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278677","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278677","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must convert warn verdict to block.","rule_id_src":"SV-278677r1190769_rule","rule_id":"SV-278677r1190769","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000074","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must convert warn verdict to block.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Convert warn verdict to block to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Convert warn verdict to block is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableConvertWarnToBlock\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a site URL has an unknown or uncertain reputation, a toast notification presents the user with the following options:\n\n- Ok: The toast notification is released (removed), and the attempt to access the site is ended.\n\n- Unblock: The user has access to the site for 24 hours, at which point the block is reenabled. The user can continue to use Unblock to access the site until such time that the administrator prohibits (blocks) the site, thus removing the option to Unblock.\n\n- Feedback: The toast notification presents the user with a link to submit a ticket, which the user can use to submit feedback to the administrator in an attempt to justify access to the site.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"c0bc37d8-3d80-422f-a676-3b8293b012ab","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F15C4B48B6DAE9DBF79DBCB74B8920E64E28291A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Convert warn verdict to block' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\r\nValue Name:\tEnableConvertWarnToBlock (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278678","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278678","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278678","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable asynchronous inspection.","rule_id_src":"SV-278678r1190771_rule","rule_id":"SV-278678r1190771","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000075","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable asynchronous inspection.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Turn on asynchronous inspection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Network Inspection System >> Turn on asynchronous inspection is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowSwitchToAsyncInspection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Network protection includes performance optimization that allows block mode to asynchronously inspect long-lived connections, which might provide a performance improvement. This optimization can also help with app compatibility problems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"d5a8373a-c5b9-49a1-bcd8-3b5ef5ad8dc0","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C7B40158F6FED11EEAAD3DD6B82D2275C4C95AF7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on asynchronous inspection' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\r\nValue Name:\tAllowSwitchToAsyncInspection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278679","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278679","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278679","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan packed executables.","rule_id_src":"SV-278679r1190773_rule","rule_id":"SV-278679r1190773","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000076","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan packed executables.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan packed executables to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Scan packed executables is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisablePackedExeScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting manages whether Microsoft Defender Antivirus scans packed executables. Packed executables are executable files that contain compressed code.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"8b192123-5744-451a-861c-fad253ef4c50","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8D8CB26C98C38F7B4C87655DB51B53DF5FB8BA6E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scan packed executables' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tDisablePackedExeScanning (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278680","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278680","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278680","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable heuristics.","rule_id_src":"SV-278680r1190775_rule","rule_id":"SV-278680r1190775","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000077","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable heuristics.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Turn on heuristics to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> Scan >> Turn on heuristics is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableHeuristics\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002624"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"4fdbf9e0-2f0f-4994-ab79-37414a918548","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 322F83E7BFB7FFD538468D73F2F75EAA48134437\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on heuristics' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\r\nValue Name:\tDisableHeuristics (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-278863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278863","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278863","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must set cloud protection level to High.","rule_id_src":"SV-278863r1190777_rule","rule_id":"SV-278863r1190777","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000073","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must set cloud protection level to High.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Select cloud protection level to \"Enabled\".\n\nSet policy value \"Select cloud blocking level\" to \"High blocking level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Microsoft Defender Antivirus >> MpEngine >> Select cloud protection level is set to \"Enabled\". Verify the policy value for \"Select cloud blocking level\" is set to \"High blocking level\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpCloudBlockLevel\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Defender_Antivirus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cloud protection in Microsoft Defender Antivirus delivers accurate, real-time, and intelligent protection. Cloud protection should be enabled by default.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"3985","uuid":"3c19366c-f53a-4ca4-bb41-f3a4d284325e","stig_uuid":"cdad41fd-1e45-40a4-b294-f031ef6d1cd1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftDefenderAntivirus_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F48A4E1C3DD3789783BD60169D5B2CDE654BCDAF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Select cloud protection level' is NOT Enabled: (High)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\r\nValue Name:\tMpCloudBlockLevel (Not found)"}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:16:30.3660995-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-NETFramework4_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft DotNet Framework 4.0 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft DotNet Framework 4.0","stig_id":"MS_Dot_Net_Framework","release_info":"Release: 8 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","reference_identifier":"4213","size":16,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-225223","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225223","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225223","severity":"medium","group_title":"Digital signatures assigned to strongly named assemblies must be verified.","rule_id_src":"SV-225223r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-225223r961038","rule_version":"APPNET0031","rule_title":"Digital signatures assigned to strongly named assemblies must be verified.","fix_text":"Use regedit to remove the values stored in Windows registry key HKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification. There should be no assemblies or hash values listed under this registry key.\n\nAll assemblies must require strong name verification in a production environment.\n\nStrong name assemblies that do not require verification in a development or test environment must have documented approvals from the IAO.\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use regedit to review the Windows registry key \nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification. \nThere should be no assemblies or hash values listed under this registry key. If the StrongName\\Verification key does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf there are assemblies or hash values listed in this key, each value represents a distinct application assembly that does not have the application strong name verified.  \n\nIf any assemblies are listed as omitting strong name verification in a production environment, this is a finding.\n\nIf any assemblies are listed as omitting strong name verification in a development or test environment and the IAO has not provided documented approvals, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A strong name consists of the assembly's identity, simple text name, version number, and culture information (if provided)—plus a public key and a digital signature.  Strong names serve to identify the author of the code.  If digital signatures used to sign strong name assemblies are not verified, any self signed code can be impersonated.  This can lead to a loss of system integrity. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7438","V-7055"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"65bedf52-6c7e-40aa-bf28-a94c2a8b26a9","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DC31B1F7DD7B008A4968735BB8083B31F09F747D\r\n~~~~~\r\nHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification exists but no values were found within."},{"group_id_src":"V-225224","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225224","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225224","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Trust Providers Software Publishing State must be set to 0x23C00.","rule_id_src":"SV-225224r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-225224r961038","rule_version":"APPNET0046","rule_title":"The Trust Providers Software Publishing State must be set to 0x23C00.","fix_text":"This fix must be performed for each user on the system.\n\nUsing regedit, change the hexadecimal value of the \"HKEY_USER\\[UNIQUE USER SID VALUE]\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\\State\" registry key to 0x23C00.\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system or application being reviewed is SIPR based, this finding is NA.\n\nThis check must be performed for each user on the system. \n\nUse regedit to locate \"HKEY_USER\\[UNIQUE USER SID VALUE]\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\\State\".  \n\nIf the State value for any user is not set to the hexadecimal value of 0x23C00, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Windows operating systems provide a feature called Authenticode.  Authenticode technology and its underlying code signing mechanisms serve to provide a structure to identify software publishers and ensure that software applications have not been tampered with.  Authenticode technology relies on digital certificates and is based on Public Key Cryptography Standards (PKCS) #7 (encrypted key specification), PKCS #10 (certificate request formats), X.509 (certificate specification), and Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA) and MD5 hash algorithms.\n\nThe manner in which the Authenticode technology validates a certificate and determines what is considered a valid certificate can be modified to meet the mission of the Microsoft Windows system.  Each facade of certificate validation is controlled through the bits that makeup the hexadecimal value for the Authenticode setting.  An improper setting will allow non-valid certificates to be accepted and can put the integrity of the system into jeopardy.\n\nThe hexadecimal value of 0x23C00 will implement the following certificate enforcement policy:\n- Trust the Test Root = FALSE\n- Use expiration date on certificates = TRUE\n- Check the revocation list = TRUE\n- Offline revocation server OK (Individual) = TRUE\n- Offline revocation server OK (Commercial) = TRUE\n- Java offline revocation server OK (Individual) = TRUE\n- Java offline revocation server OK (Commercial) = TRUE\n- Invalidate version 1 signed objects = FALSE\n- Check the revocation list on Time Stamp Signer = FALSE\n- Only trust items found in the Trust DB = FALSE","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7444","V-7061"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"af195d75-c467-4ef2-96f7-2b290eae22b1","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 76CBF5A7C87686EA51FA77410808A92FDB3A947F\r\n~~~~~\r\nAll user profiles have State configured to 0x00023c00"},{"group_id_src":"V-225225","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225225","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225225","severity":"medium","group_title":"Developer certificates used with the .NET Publisher Membership Condition must be approved by the ISSO.","rule_id_src":"SV-225225r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-225225r961038","rule_version":"APPNET0048","rule_title":"Developer certificates used with the .NET Publisher Membership Condition must be approved by the ISSO.","fix_text":"Trust must be established when utilizing Publishers Membership Condition. All publisher's certificates must have documented approvals from the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x. \r\n\r\nThis requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\r\n\r\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\r\n\r\nCaspol.exe is a Microsoft tool used for working with .Net policy. Use caspol.exe to list the code groups and any publisher membership conditions.\r\n\r\nThe location of the caspol utility is dependent upon the system architecture of the system running .Net.\r\n\r\nFor 32 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319.\r\n \r\nFor 64 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\ncd %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\r\n\r\nTo check code groups for the machine, run the following command:\r\n\r\ncaspol.exe -m -lg\r\n\r\nSample Results:\r\nMicrosoft (R) .NET Framework CasPol 4.0.30319.1\r\nCopyright (c) Microsoft Corporation.  All rights reserved.\r\n\r\nPolicy change prompt is ON\r\n\r\nLevel = Machine\r\n\r\nCode Groups:\r\n\r\n1.  All code: Nothing\r\n   1.1.  Zone - MyComputer: FullTrust (LevelFinal)\r\n      1.1.1.  StrongName - : FullTrust\r\n      1.1.2.  StrongName - 00000000000000000400000000000000: FullTrust\r\n   1.2.  Zone - Intranet: LocalIntranet\r\n      1.2.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n      1.2.2.  All code: Same directory FileIO - 'Read, PathDiscovery'\r\n   1.3.  Zone - Internet: Internet\r\n      1.3.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n   1.4.  Zone - Untrusted: Nothing\r\n   1.5.  (First Match) Zone - Trusted: Internet\r\n      1.5.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n   1.6.  Publisher - 30818902818100E47B359ACC061D70C237B572FA276C9854CFABD469DFB74E77D026630BEE2A0C2F8170A823AE69FDEB65704D7FD446DEFEF1F6BA12B6ACBDB1BFA7B9B595AB9A40636467CFF7C73F198B53A9A7CF177F6E7896EBC591DD3003C5992A266C0AD9FBEE4E2A056BE7F7ED154D806F7965F83B0AED616C192C6416CFCB46FC2F5CFD0203010001: FullTrust\r\nSuccess\r\n\r\nSection 1.6 above indicates the presence of a publisher's key that meets the Publisher's Membership Condition and is also given full trust.\r\n\r\nIf the Publisher Membership Condition is used on a nondefault Code Group and the use of that publisher's certificate is not documented and approved by the ISSO, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A .Net assembly will satisfy the Publisher Membership Condition if it is signed with a software publisher’s Authenticode X.509v3 digital certificate that can be verified by the Windows operating system as having a chain of trust that leads to a trusted root certificate stored in the user’s certificate store. The Publisher Membership Condition can be used to identify an organization, developer, vendor, or other entity as the ultimate source of the assembly, even if the code itself was obtained from a third party, such as a mirror site. Access to system resources, such as file systems or printers, may then be granted to the assembly based on the trust relationship with the identified entity.\n\nCertificates used to sign assemblies so the Publisher Member Condition may be applied must originate from a trusted source. Using a certificate that is not from a trusted source could potentially violate system integrity and confidentiality.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7446","V-7063"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"49d9b44a-5d61-4fc9-9934-daf86290a524","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A65FFE8F900670E06138916C565D0B06CF5A07E\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled .NET version is '4.8.1 or later'.  This check only applies to .NET version 4.0 specifically so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-225226","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225226","title":"SRG-APP-000176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225226","severity":"medium","group_title":"Encryption keys used for the .NET Strong Name Membership Condition must be protected.","rule_id_src":"SV-225226r961041_rule","rule_id":"SV-225226r961041","rule_version":"APPNET0052","rule_title":"Encryption keys used for the .NET Strong Name Membership Condition must be protected.","fix_text":"Ask the Systems Programmer how the private keys used to sign the assembly are protected.\n\nPrivate keys are simply values stored as strings of data. Keys can be stored in files on the file system or in a centralized data repository. \n\nAdequate protection methods include, but are not limited to:\n- utilizing centralized key management;\n- using strict file permissions to limit access; and\n- tying strong pass phrases to the key.\n\nThe private key(s) used to sign the assembly must be protected. Utilize centralized key management or strict file permissions along with strong pass phrases and/or other well-established industry practices for managing and controlling access to private keys.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the application is a COTS product, this requirement is Not Applicable (NA).\r\n\r\nThe infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x.\r\n\r\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\r\n\r\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\r\n\r\nCaspol.exe is a Microsoft tool used for working with .Net policy. Use caspol.exe to list the code groups and any publisher membership conditions.\r\n\r\nThe location of the caspol utility is dependent upon the system architecture of the system running .Net.\r\n\r\nFor 32 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319.\r\n \r\nFor 64 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\ncd %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\r\n\r\nTo check code groups, run the following command:\r\n\r\ncaspol.exe -all -lg\r\n\r\nSample response:\r\nMicrosoft (R) .NET Framework CasPol 4.0.30319.1\r\n\r\nSecurity is ON\r\nExecution checking is ON\r\nPolicy change prompt is ON\r\n\r\nLevel = Machine\r\n\r\nCode Groups:\r\n\r\n1.  All code: Nothing\r\n   1.1.  Zone - MyComputer: FullTrust (LevelFinal)\r\n      1.1.1.  StrongName - : FullTrust\r\n      1.1.2.  StrongName - 00000000000000000400000000000000: FullTrust\r\n   1.2.  Zone - Intranet: LocalIntranet\r\n      1.2.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n      1.2.2.  All code: Same directory FileIO - 'Read, PathDiscovery'\r\n   1.3.  Zone - Internet: Internet\r\n      1.3.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n   1.4.  Zone - Untrusted: Nothing\r\n   1.5.  (First Match) Zone - Trusted: Internet\r\n      1.5.1.  All code: Same site Web\r\n   1.6.  Publisher - 30818902818100E47B359ACC061D70C237B572FA276C9854CFABD469DFB74E77D026630BEE2A0C2F8170A823AE69FDEB65704D7FD446DEFEF1F6BA12B6ACBDB1BFA7B9B595AB9A40636467CFF7C73F198B53A9A7CF177F6E7896EBC591DD3003C5992A266C0AD9FBEE4E2A056BE7F7ED154D806F7965F83B0AED616C192C6416CFCB46FC2F5CFD0203010001: FullTrust\r\nSuccess\r\n\r\nAn assembly will satisfy the StrongNameMembershipCondition if its metadata contains the strongly identifying data associated with the specified strong name. At the least, this means it has been digitally signed with the private key associated with the public key recorded in the policy.\r\n\r\nThe presence of the encryption key values in the StrongName field indicates the use of StrongNameMembershipCondition. \r\n\r\nIf a Strong Name Membership Condition is assigned to a non-default Code Group the private key must be adequately protected by the software developer or the entity responsible for signing the assemblies. \r\n\r\nAsk the Systems Programmer how the private keys are protected. \r\n\r\nPrivate keys are simply values stored as strings of data.  Keys can be stored in files on the file system or in a centralized data repository. \r\n\r\nAdequate protection methods include, but are not limited to:\r\n- utilizing centralized key management;\r\n- using strict file permissions to limit access; and\r\n- tying strong pass phrases to the key.\r\n\r\nIf the private key used to sign the assembly is not adequately protected, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Strong Name Membership condition requires that member assemblies be defined with Strong Names. A strong name consists of the assembly's identity, simple text name, version number, and culture information (if provided) — plus a public key and a digital signature. If assemblies do not have a strong name assigned, the assembly cannot be unique and the author of the code cannot be uniquely identified. In order to create the strong name, the developer must use a cryptographic key pair to sign the assembly. If the developer does not protect the key, the key can be stolen and used to sign any application, including malware applications. This could adversely affect application integrity and confidentiality.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7450","V-7067"],"ccis":["CCI-000186"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"26662ee6-13e5-46af-be48-12f3a77e5857","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A65FFE8F900670E06138916C565D0B06CF5A07E\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled .NET version is '4.8.1 or later'.  This check only applies to .NET version 4.0 specifically so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-225227","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225227","title":"SRG-APP-000120","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225227","severity":"medium","group_title":"CAS and policy configuration files must be backed up.","rule_id_src":"SV-225227r960936_rule","rule_id":"SV-225227r960936","rule_version":"APPNET0055","rule_title":"CAS and policy configuration files must be backed up.","fix_text":"All CAS policy and policy configuration files must be included in the system backup. \n\nAll CAS policy and policy configuration files must be backed up prior to migration, deployment, and reconfiguration.\n\nCAS policy configuration files must be included in disaster recovery plan documentation.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x.\r\n\r\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\r\n\r\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\r\n\r\nAsk the System Administrator if all CAS policy and policy configuration files are included in the system backup. If they are not, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nAsk the System Administrator if the policy and configuration files are backed up prior to migration, deployment, and reconfiguration. If they are not, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nAsk the System Administrator for documentation that shows CAS Policy configuration files are backed up as part of a disaster recovery plan. If they have no documentation proving the files are backed up, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A successful disaster recovery plan requires that CAS policy and CAS policy configuration files are identified and included in systems disaster backup and recovery events. Documentation regarding the location of system and application specific CAS policy configuration files and the frequency in which backups occur is required. If these files are not identified and the information is not documented, there is the potential that critical application configuration files may not be included in disaster recovery events which could lead to an availability risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7452","V-7069"],"ccis":["CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"24847c9e-1bea-4fa4-ad3b-a284a182cd16","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A65FFE8F900670E06138916C565D0B06CF5A07E\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled .NET version is '4.8.1 or later'.  This check only applies to .NET version 4.0 specifically so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-225228","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225228","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225228","severity":"medium","group_title":"Remoting Services HTTP channels must utilize authentication and encryption.","rule_id_src":"SV-225228r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-225228r1043178","rule_version":"APPNET0060","rule_title":"Remoting Services HTTP channels must utilize authentication and encryption.","fix_text":"If .NET remoting with HTTP channel is not used, this fix is Not Applicable.\r\n\r\nEnsure encryption and message integrity are used for HTTP remoting channels.\r\n\r\nThe HTTP channel only supports encryption and message integrity when the remote object is hosted in Internet Information Services (IIS) using TLS.\r\n\r\nHTTP channels are protected via TLS (HTTPS). \r\n<channels> \r\n   <channel ref=“http server” port=“443”/> \r\n</channels> \r\n\r\nChange the channel ref parameter to utilize a TLS port and leverage TLS on the remote IIS server.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If .NET remoting with HTTP channel is not used, this check is Not Applicable.\r\n\r\nReview the machine.config file and the [application name].exe.config file.\r\n\r\nFor 32-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder: %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\Config \r\n\r\nFor 64-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder: %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\Config.\r\n\r\nMicrosoft specifies locating the [application].config file in the same folder as the application executable (.exe) file. However, the developer does have the capability to specify a different location when the application is compiled.  Therefore, if the file is not found in the application home folder, a search of the system is required. If the [application name].exe.config file is not found on the system, then only a check of the machine.config file is required.\r\n\r\nSample machine/application config file:\r\n\r\n<application name=“remoteserver”> \r\n  <service> \r\n    <activated type=“sample.my.object, myobjects”/> \r\n  </service> \r\n  <channels> \r\n    <channel ref=“http server” port=“80”/> \r\n  </channels> \r\n</application>\r\n\r\n<serverProviders>\r\n  <provider ref=\"wsdl\" />\r\n  <formatter ref=\"soap\" typeFilterLevel=\"Low\" /> \r\n  <formatter ref=\"binary\" typeFilterLevel=\"Low\" /> \r\n</serverProviders> \r\n\r\nMicrosoft provides three \"channels\" that are used for remoting connectivity. They are the HTTP, TCP, and IPC channels. The channel that is used is specified via the <channels> element in the config file.  \r\n\r\nHTTP channel example:\r\n<channel ref=“http server” port=“80”/> \r\n\r\nThe HTTP channel only supports encryption and message integrity when the remote object is hosted in Internet Information Services (IIS) using TLS.\r\n\r\nThe above example shows the well-known TLS port of 443 is not being used. \r\n\r\nIf the HTTP remoting channel is not configured to protect the channel by using TLS encryption, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Note: Microsoft recommends using the Windows Communication Framework (WCF) rather than using .Net remoting. New development projects should refrain from using .Net remoting capabilities whenever possible.\r\n\r\n.NET remoting provides the capability to build widely distributed applications. The application components may reside all on one computer or they may be spread out across the enclave. .NET client applications can make remoting calls to use objects in other processes on the same computer or on any other computer that is reachable over the network. .NET remoting can also be used to communicate with other application domains within the same process. Remoting is achieved via the exposure of endpoints that can be used to establish remote connectivity.\r\n\r\nNormally when application code attempts to access a protected resource, a stack walk is performed to ensure that all stack frames have permission to access the resource. However, with .Net 4.0, when a call is made on a remote object, this stack walk is not performed across the remoting boundary. The .Net remoting infrastructure requires FullTrust permission to execute on either the client or the server. \r\n\r\nDue to the fact that FullTrust permission is required, Remoting endpoints should be authenticated and encrypted in order to protect the system and the data. \r\n\r\nMicrosoft provides three different \"channels\" that are used for remoting. They are HTTP, TCP, and IPC.\r\n\r\nAny unauthorized use of a remoting application provides unauthorized access with FullTrust permissions to the system. This can potentially result in a loss of system integrity or confidentiality.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7453","V-7070"],"ccis":["CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"cdca6bd7-a0a4-426c-85fc-91696afcbb9b","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EF49AA5F570B34CF4548CC05BBB50C0709AC76F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nNo machine.config or *.exe.config files found using .NET remoting with HTTP channel so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-225229","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225229","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225229","severity":"medium","group_title":".Net Framework versions installed on the system must be supported.","rule_id_src":"SV-225229r1188309_rule","rule_id":"SV-225229r1188309","rule_version":"APPNET0061","rule_title":".Net Framework versions installed on the system must be supported.","fix_text":"Remove unsupported versions of the .NET Framework and upgrade legacy applications that utilize unsupported versions of the .NET framework.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine which versions of the .NET Framework are installed by opening the directory %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET.\r\n\r\nThe folder named \"%systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\" contains .NET files for 32 bit systems. The folder named \"%systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\" contains .NET files for 64 bit systems. 64 bit systems will have both the 32 bit and the 64 bit folders. 32 bit systems do not have a Framework64 folder.\r\n\r\nWithin each of the folders are the individual folder names that contain the corresponding versions of the .NET Framework:\r\n\r\nv4.0.30319\r\nv3.5\r\nv3.0\r\nv2.0.50727\r\nv1.1.4322\r\nv1.0.3705\r\n\r\nSearch for all the Mscorlib.dll files in the %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework folder and the %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64 folder if the folder exists. Click on each of the files, view properties, and click the version tab to determine the version installed.  If there is no Mscorlib.dll, there is no installed version of .Net Framework in that directory.\r\n\r\nMore specific information on determining versions of .Net Framework installed can be found at the following link. http://support.microsoft.com/kb/318785\r\n\r\nVerify extended support is available for the installed versions of .Net Framework.\r\n\r\nVerify the .Net Framework support dates with Microsoft Product Lifecycle Search link.\r\nhttp://support.microsoft.com/lifecycle/search/?sort=PN&alpha=.NET+Framework\r\n\r\nBeginning with .NET 3.5 SP1, the .NET Framework is considered a Component of the Windows OS. Components follow the Support Lifecycle policy of their parent product or platform.\r\n\r\n .NET Framework 3.5 cannot function without the .NET Framework 2.0 and the .NET Framework 3.0, because there is no common language runtime (CLR) in the .NET Framework 3.5 layer. Therefore, when the .NET Framework 3.5 product is installed, the .NET Framework 2.0 and the .NET Framework 3.0 SP products are also installed. Installation of .NET 2.0 and 3.0 SP products as part of .NET Framework 3.5 is Not a Finding. (https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/topic/clarification-on-the-support-life-cycle-for-the-net-framework-3-5-the-net-framework-3-0-and-the-net-framework-2-0-28621c7b-226c-7682-27f5-2e2a42db39c3)\r\n \r\nIf any versions of the .Net Framework are installed and support is no longer available, this is a finding.\r\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsupported software introduces risks and violates DOD policy.  Applications utilizing unsupported versions of .NET introduce substantial risk to the host, network, and the enclave because they leverage an architecture that is no longer updated by the vendor.  This introduces potential application integrity, availability, or confidentiality issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-55642","V-18395"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"76c4820c-28a6-48c2-a1f1-0daca748b90f","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ABAA50CEF24084BF874ED435E6C350E563C15342\r\n~~~~~\r\nOperating system:\r\n---------------------------------\r\nName:\tMicrosoft Windows 11 Pro [25H2]\r\nVersion:\t10.0.26200\r\n\r\nEnabled .NET Windows features:\r\n---------------------------------\r\nNetFx3\r\nNetFx4-AdvSrvs\r\n\r\nLibrary files:\r\n---------------------------------\r\nFile Path:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v2.0.50727\\mscorlib.dll\r\nVersion:\t\t\t2.0.50727.9179\r\nSupport Ends:\t\t01/09/2029\r\n\r\nFile Path:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\mscorlib.dll\r\nVersion:\t\t\t4.8.9337.0\r\n\r\nFile Path:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v2.0.50727\\mscorlib.dll\r\nVersion:\t\t\t2.0.50727.9179\r\nSupport Ends:\t\t01/09/2029\r\n\r\nFile Path:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\mscorlib.dll\r\nVersion:\t\t\t4.8.9337.0\r\n\r\nRef - https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/lifecycle/products/microsoft-net-framework\r\n\r\nRef - https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/topic/clarification-on-the-support-life-cycle-for-the-net-framework-3-5-the-net-framework-3-0-and-the-net-framework-2-0-28621c7b-226c-7682-27f5-2e2a42db39c3"},{"group_id_src":"V-225230","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225230","title":"SRG-APP-000635","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225230","severity":"medium","group_title":"The .NET CLR must be configured to use FIPS approved encryption modules.","rule_id_src":"SV-225230r1117185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225230r1117185","rule_version":"APPNET0062","rule_title":"The .NET CLR must be configured to use FIPS approved encryption modules.","fix_text":"Examine the .NET CLR configuration files to find the runtime element and then the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element.\n\nExample:\n<configuration> \n  <runtime> \n                <enforceFIPSPolicy enabled=\"true|false\" />\n  </runtime>\n</configuration>\n\nDelete the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" runtime element, change the setting to \"true\" or there must be documented IAO approvals for the FIPS setting.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"\nExamine the .NET CLR configuration files from the vulnerability discussion to find the runtime element and then the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element.\n\nExample:\n<configuration> \n  <runtime> \n                <enforceFIPSPolicy enabled=\"true|false\" />\n  </runtime>\n</configuration>\n\nBy default, the .NET \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element is set to \"true\".\n\nIf the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element does not exist within the \"runtime\" element of the CLR configuration, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element exists and is set to \"false\", and the IAO has not accepted the risk and documented the risk acceptance, this is a finding. \n\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"FIPS encryption is configured via .NET configuration files.  There are numerous configuration files that affect different aspects of .Net behavior.  The .NET config files are described below.\n \nMachine Configuration Files:\nThe machine configuration file, Machine.config, contains settings that apply to an entire computer. This file is located in the %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\Config directory for 32 bit .NET 4 installations and %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\Config for 64 bit systems.   Machine.config contains configuration settings for machine-wide assembly binding, built-in remoting channels, and ASP.NET.\n\nApplication Configuration Files:\nApplication configuration files contain settings specific to an application. If checking these files, a .NET review of a specific .NET application is most likely being conducted. These files contain configuration settings that the Common Language Runtime reads (such as assembly binding policy, remoting objects, and so on), and settings that the application can read. \n\nThe name and location of the application configuration file depends on the application's host, which can be one of the following: \n\nExecutable–hosted application configuration files. \n\nThe configuration file for an application hosted by the executable host is in the same directory as the application. The name of the configuration file is the name of the application with a .config extension. For example, an application called myApp.exe can be associated with a configuration file called myApp.exe.config. \n\nInternet Explorer-hosted application configuration files. \n\nIf an application hosted in Internet Explorer has a configuration file, the location of this file is specified in a <link> tag with the following syntax.\n\n<link rel=\"ConfigurationFileName\" href=\"location\">\n\nIn this tag, \"location\" represents a URL that point to the configuration file. This sets the application base. The configuration file must be located on the same web site as the application. \n\n.NET 4.0 allows the CLR runtime to be configured to ignore FIPS encryption requirements.  If the CLR is not configured to use FIPS encryption modules, insecure encryption modules might be employed which could introduce an application confidentiality or integrity issue.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40966","V-30926"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"f0a89d2f-5fc0-486c-be31-9d280c3b958a","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 576428381117AB5ACD39A82EA04F76ED84B31819\r\n~~~~~\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.55\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tenforceFIPSPolicy\r\nEnabled:\tfalse\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.57\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tenforceFIPSPolicy\r\nEnabled:\tfalse\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.61\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tenforceFIPSPolicy\r\nEnabled:\tfalse\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\sunst\\OneDrive\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.45\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tenforceFIPSPolicy\r\nEnabled:\tfalse"},{"group_id_src":"V-225231","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225231","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225231","severity":"medium","group_title":".NET must be configured to validate strong names on full-trust assemblies.","rule_id_src":"SV-225231r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-225231r961038","rule_version":"APPNET0063","rule_title":".NET must be configured to validate strong names on full-trust assemblies.","fix_text":"For 32 bit production systems: \nSet “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\AllowStrongNameBypass\" to a “DWORD” value of “0”.\nOn 64-bit production systems:\nSet “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\ AllowStrongNameBypass” and “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\ AllowStrongNameBypass” to a “DWORD” value of “0”.\nOr, obtain documented ISSO risk acceptance for each .Net application installed on the system. \n\nApproval documentation will include complete list of all installed .Net applications, application versions, and acknowledgement of ISSO trust of each installed application.\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If there is documented ISSO risk acceptance for development systems, this is not a finding.\nFor 32 bit production systems: \nUse regedit to examine the “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework” key.  \nOn 64-bit production systems:\nUse regedit to examine both the “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework” and “HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework” keys.\nIf the \"AllowStrongNameBypass\" value does not exist, or if the “DWORD” value is set to “1”, this is a finding.\n\nDocumentation must include a complete list of installed .Net applications, application versions, and acknowledgement that ISSO trusts each installed application.\n\nIf application versions installed on the system do not match approval documentation, this is a finding.\n\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"bypassTrustedAppStrongNames\" setting specifies whether the bypass feature that avoids validating strong names for full-trust assemblies is enabled. By default the bypass feature is enabled in .Net 4, therefore strong names are not validated for correctness when the assembly/program is loaded. Not validating strong names provides a faster application load time but at the expense of performing certificate validation. \n\nFull trust assemblies are .Net applications launched from the local host. Strong names are digital signatures tied to .Net applications/assemblies.  .Net 4 considers applications installed locally to be fully trusted by default and grants these applications full permissions to access host resources. \n\nThe bypass feature applies to any assembly signed with a strong name and having the following characteristics:\n\n    Fully trusted without the StrongName evidence (for example, has MyComputer zone evidence).\n\n    Loaded into a fully trusted AppDomain.\n\n    Loaded from a location under the ApplicationBase property of that AppDomain.\n\n    Not delay-signed.\n\nNot validating the certificates used to sign strong name assemblies will provide a faster application load time, but falsely assumes that signatures used to sign the application are to be implicitly trusted.  Not validating strong name certificates introduces an integrity risk to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40977","V-30935"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"f62d2203-a9db-4131-8d85-57e6271223da","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B321101F0CDF4E94F69C02147A8A79349F020F71\r\n~~~~~\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\r\nValue Name:\tAllowStrongNameBypass (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\r\nValue Name:\tAllowStrongNameBypass (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-225232","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225232","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225232","severity":"low","group_title":".Net applications that invoke NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy must apply previous versions of .NET STIG guidance.","rule_id_src":"SV-225232r1050651_rule","rule_id":"SV-225232r1050651","rule_version":"APPNET0064","rule_title":".Net applications that invoke NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy must apply previous versions of .NET STIG guidance.","fix_text":"The infrastructure to enable CAS exists only in .NET Framework 2.x - 4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework > 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nApply the .NET Framework Security Checklist for .Net versions 1 through 3.5 when using the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x - 4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework > 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nOpen Windows explorer and search for all *.exe.config files. This requirement does not apply to the caspol.exe assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nTo find relevant files, run the FINDSTR command from an elevated (admin) command prompt: \nFINDSTR /i /s \"NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy\" c:\\*.exe.config \n\nThis command will search all .\"exe.config\" files on the c: drive partition for the \"LegacySecurityPolicy\" setting. Repeat the command for each drive partition on the system.\n\nIf the .NET application configuration file uses the legacy policy element, and .NET STIG guidance that covers these legacy versions has not been applied, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"CAS policy is .NET runtime version-specific.  In .NET Framework version 4, CAS policy is disabled by default however; it can be re-enabled by using the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting on a per application basis. Caspol.exe is provided by Microsoft to set security policy on .Net applications prior to version 4.0. This requirement does not apply to the caspol.exe assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nWhen invoking the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting in .NET 4, earlier versions of the .NET Framework CAS policy will become active therefore previous .NET STIG guidance that applies to the reactivated versions must also be applied. \n\nFailure to apply applicable versions of STIG guidance can result in the loss of system confidentiality, integrity or availability.  ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40979","V-30937"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"3b97e4fd-2030-4068-ab76-fea8c3caedb3","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A65FFE8F900670E06138916C565D0B06CF5A07E\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled .NET version is '4.8.1 or later'.  This check only applies to .NET version 4.0 specifically so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-225233","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225233","title":"SRG-APP-000431","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225233","severity":"medium","group_title":"Trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4.","rule_id_src":"SV-225233r1117179_rule","rule_id":"SV-225233r1117179","rule_version":"APPNET0065","rule_title":"Trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4.","fix_text":".Net application code loaded from a remote source must be run in a controlled environment.  \n\nA controlled environment consists of a sandbox, such as running in an Internet Explorer host environment or employing OS based software access controls, such as AppLocker or Software Security Policies, when application design permits.  \n\nObtain documented IAO approvals for all remotely loaded code.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for *.exe.config.\n\nSearch each config file found for the \"loadFromRemoteSources\" element.\n\nIf the loadFromRemoteSources element is enabled  \n(\"loadFromRemoteSources enabled = true\"), and the remotely loaded application is not run in a sandboxed environment, or if OS based software controls, such as AppLocker or Software Security Policies, are not utilized, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In the .NET Framework version 3.5 and earlier versions, if an application assembly loaded code/objects from a remote location, that assembly would run partially trusted with a permissions grant set that depended on the zone in which it was loaded. For example, if an assembly was loaded from a web site, it was loaded into the Internet zone and granted the Internet permission set. In other words, it was executed in an Internet sandbox.\n\nIf the same program is run in the .NET Framework version 4, an exception is thrown which effectively states; either explicitly create a sandbox for the assembly or run it in full trust.\n\nThe <loadFromRemoteSources> element specifies the assemblies that run partially trusted in earlier versions of the .NET Framework will be run fully trusted in the .NET Framework 4.\n\nIf loadFromRemoteSources is set to true, the remotely loaded application code is granted full trust.  This could create an integrity vulnerability on the system.  The required method to address this is to explicitly create a sandboxed environment for the remotely loaded code to run in rather than allowing remotely loaded code to run with full trust.\n\nThe appropriate level of trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4 applications and that code must be run in a controlled environment.  The following is an example of the use of loadFromRemoteSources.\n\n<configuration>\n<runtime>\n    <loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"true\" \"https://my.dodorg.gov\" />\n    <loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"true\" \"https://192.168.0.*\" />\n    <loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"false\" \"*\" />\n</runtime>\n</configuration>","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41010","V-30968"],"ccis":["CCI-002530"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"6fba814c-f8db-478a-a843-9ebf2c5983ce","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: 7D727B83D2F2C09A54939594159F21B4A1EA5739\r\n~~~~~\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.55\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tloadFromRemoteSources\r\nEnabled:\ttrue\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.57\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tloadFromRemoteSources\r\nEnabled:\ttrue\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\rich\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.61\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tloadFromRemoteSources\r\nEnabled:\ttrue\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\sunst\\OneDrive\\Portable Apps\\KeePass-2.45\\KeePass.exe.config\r\nName:\tloadFromRemoteSources\r\nEnabled:\ttrue"},{"group_id_src":"V-225234","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225234","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225234","severity":"low","group_title":".NET default proxy settings must be reviewed and approved.","rule_id_src":"SV-225234r1188289_rule","rule_id":"SV-225234r1188289","rule_version":"APPNET0066","rule_title":".NET default proxy settings must be reviewed and approved.","fix_text":"Open Windows explorer and search for all \"*.exe.config\" and \"machine.config\" files.\n\nSearch each file for the \"defaultProxy\" element.\n\nClear the values contained in the \"defaultProxy\" element, and the \"bypasslist\", \"module\", and \"proxy\" child elements.\n\nThe IAO must provide documented approvals of any non-default proxy servers.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for all \"*.exe.config\" and \"machine.config\" files.\n\nThe referenced file is in the WinSxS directory (original source component file used when the Windows component was installed).\n\nIf the files under WinSxS are read-only and cannot be modified, this is not a finding.\n\nSearch each file for the \"defaultProxy\" element.\n\n<defaultProxy\n  enabled=\"true|false\"\n  useDefaultCredentials=\"true|false\"\n  <bypasslist> … </bypasslist>\n  <proxy> … </proxy>\n  <module> … </module>\n/>\n\nIf the \"defaultProxy\" setting \"enabled=false\" or if the \"bypasslist\", \"module\", or \"proxy\" child elements have configuration entries and there are no documented approvals from the authorizing official (AO), this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"defaultProxy\" element is empty or if \"useSystemDefault =True” then the framework is using default browser settings, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The .Net framework can be configured to utilize a different proxy or altogether bypass the default proxy settings in the client's browser.  This may lead to the framework using a proxy that is not approved for use.  If the proxy is malicious, this could lead to a loss of application integrity and confidentiality.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41014","V-30972"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"dca9278d-10b2-4014-a4b2-296e7113bb27","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D494EFC0B5BFFA0F47A4414E95B31461DB797F2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nNo machine.config or *.exe.config files found with 'defaultProxy enabled=false' or with 'bypasslist', 'module', or 'proxy' elements."},{"group_id_src":"V-225235","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225235","title":"SRG-APP-000095","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225235","severity":"medium","group_title":"Event tracing for Windows (ETW) for Common Language Runtime events must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-225235r960891_rule","rule_id":"SV-225235r960891","rule_version":"APPNET0067","rule_title":"Event tracing for Windows (ETW) for Common Language Runtime events must be enabled.","fix_text":"Open Windows explorer and search for all .NET config files including application config files (*.exe.config).\n\nExamine the configuration settings for \n<etwEnable enabled=\"false\" />.\n\nEnable ETW Tracing by setting the etwEnable flag to \"true\" or obtain documented IAO approvals.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for all .NET config files including application config files (*.exe.config)\n\nNOTE:\nBeginning with Windows Vista and Windows Server 2008, ETW Tracing is enabled by default and the \"etwEnable\" setting is not required in order for Event Tracing to be enabled.  An etwEnable setting of \"true\" IS required in earlier versions of Windows as ETW is disabled by default. \n\nExamine the configuration settings for \n<etwEnable enabled=\"false\" />.\n\nIf the \"etwEnable\" element is set to \"true\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf the \"etwEnable\" element is set to \"false\" and documented approvals by the IAO are not provided, this is a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Event tracing captures information about applications utilizing the .NET CLR and the .NET CLR itself. This includes security oriented information, such as Strong Name and Authenticode verification.  \n\nBeginning with Windows Vista, ETW is enabled by default however, the .Net CLR and .Net applications can be configured to not utilize Event Tracing. If ETW event tracing is disabled, critical events that occurred within the runtime will not be captured in event logs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41075","V-31026"],"ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"d152d70f-d5d5-4f29-808a-fb81fe11ea0c","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 337EA4CB8826346C79B61FFD2C48107B8F2246C3\r\n~~~~~\r\nNo machine.config or *.exe.config files found with 'etwEnable enabled=false'."},{"group_id_src":"V-225236","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225236","title":"SRG-APP-000431","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225236","severity":"medium","group_title":"Software utilizing .Net 4.0 must be identified and relevant access controls configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-225236r1117179_rule","rule_id":"SV-225236r1117179","rule_version":"APPNET0070","rule_title":"Software utilizing .Net 4.0 must be identified and relevant access controls configured.","fix_text":"Document the existence of all .Net 4.0 applications that are not provided by the host Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nDocument the corresponding runtime hosts that are used to invoke the applications.\n\nDocument the applications security control requirements (restricting application access to resources or user access to the application).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement does not apply to the \"caspol.exe\" assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\r\n\r\nAsk the system administrator to provide documentation that identifies:\r\n\r\n- Each .Net 4.0 application run on the system.\r\n- The .Net runtime host that invokes the application. \r\n- The security measures employed to control application access to system resources or user access to application.\r\n\r\nFor additional insight run: tasklist /fi \"modules eq mscoree.dll\"\r\n\r\nIf all .Net applications, runtime hosts and security protections have been documented or if there are no .Net 4.0 applications existing on the system, this is not a finding.\r\n\r\nIf there is no documentation that identifies the existence of .NET 4.0 applications or the lack thereof, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nIf the runtime hosts have not been identified, this is a finding.\r\n\r\nIf the security protections have not been identified, this is a finding.\r\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_DotNet_Framework_4-0_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"With the advent of .Net 4.0, the .Net framework no longer directly configures or enforces security policy for .Net applications.  This task is now relegated to the operating system layer and the security protections built-in to .Net application \"runtime hosts\" that run on the O.S. \r\n\r\nExamples of these .Net \"runtime hosts\" include; Internet Explorer, Windows Shell, ASP.NET, Database Engines or any other \"runtime hosts\" that utilize .Net and load the .Net CLR.\r\n\r\nSecurity protections include utilizing runtime host security controls such as sandboxing to restrict or control application behavior as designed or required.  \r\n\r\nTo compensate for these design changes, Windows provides native solutions such as Software Security Policies (SSP) and Application Locker (AL) which are technologies that can be implemented via Group Policy (GPO).  SSP, AL and similar third party solutions serve to restrict execution of applications, scripts and libraries based upon cryptographic hash, security zones, path and certificate values that are associated with the application files.  Additionally, application developers will utilize \"sandboxing\" techniques within their code in order to isolate 3rd party code libraries from critical system resources.\r\n\r\nIn order to assign protections to .Net 4.0 applications, the applications must first be identified and the appropriate hosting security mechanisms configured to accomplish that task.  \r\n\r\n.Net STIG guidance cannot be applied if .Net applications are not identified and documented.  The lack of an application inventory introduces confidentiality, availability and integrity vulnerabilities to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41030","V-30986"],"ccis":["CCI-002530"],"reference_identifier":"4213","uuid":"5b454c9c-32d5-445c-b5c5-5aa6992b6f5e","stig_uuid":"50efaff6-0076-48af-af01-31fee0aebeff","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-NETFramework4_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: 045B3F3E1649751F2E8181E9165AF0F7AADDB20F\r\n~~~~~\r\nC:\\ProgramData\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Containers\\Layers\\696f82a1-3739-4d1b-94fb-14dbbadaa636\\Files\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\assembly\\GAC_32\\MSBuild\\v4.0_4.0.0.0__b03f5f7f11d50a3a\\msbuild.exe\r\nFailed: The file C:\\ProgramData\\Microsoft\\Windows\\