playAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy sets the media autoplay policy for websites.\n\nThe default setting \"Not configured\" respects the current media autoplay settings and lets users configure their autoplay settings.\n\nSetting to \"Enabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Allow\". All websites are allowed to autoplay media. Users cannot override this policy.\n\nSetting to \"Disabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Limit\". This limits websites that are allowed to autoplay media to webpages with high media engagement and active WebRTC streams. Prior to Microsoft Edge version 92, this would set media autoplay to \"Block\". Users cannot override this policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"e9441ed4-5a0f-40fb-b7fb-c613b3209c47","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 89DD6A890CB9B70F18C84CC1A72C69F31A2868E4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow media autoplay for websites' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAutoplayAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235742","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235742","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235742","severity":"medium","group_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235742r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235742r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000025","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" to enabled\" and select \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set whether websites can access connected USB devices. Access can be blocked completely or the user asked each time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\n\nOverride this policy for specific URL patterns by using the WebUsbAskForUrls and WebUsbBlockedForUrls policies.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, sites can ask users whether they can access the connected USB devices ('AskWebUsb') by default, and users can change this setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"812766a3-e7fc-4315-acef-57329eee82f7","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 10E3EA8A5F92A36C77098CF39C81ACCE9C5D05B7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control use of the WebUSB API' is NOT Enabled with 'Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultWebUsbGuardSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235743","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235743","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235743","severity":"medium","group_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235743r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235743r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000026","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable this policy to enable Google Cast. Users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the Cast toolbar icon.\n\nDisable this policy to disable Google Cast.\n\nBy default, Google Cast is enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"07f76692-72ad-4795-9d33-5f9d7b47c302","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6F64C448CE0764F75C5391DB69AD9C2E43B238F1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Google Cast' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tEnableMediaRouter (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235744","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235744","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235744","severity":"medium","group_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235744r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235744r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000027","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control whether websites can access nearby Bluetooth devices. Access can be blocked completely or the site required to ask the user each time it wants to access a Bluetooth device.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is not configured, the default value ('AskWebBluetooth', meaning users are asked each time) is used and users can change it.\r\n\r\nPolicy options mapping:\r\n- BlockWebBluetooth (2) = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.\r\n- AskWebBluetooth (3) = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"b4ac35bb-5304-4292-8a05-4f34a50a784f","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F138CD3F85F02A841E8671AFFDC6CF927864FE6C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control use of the Web Bluetooth API' is NOT Enabled with 'Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235745","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235745","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235745","severity":"medium","group_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235745r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235745r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000028","rule_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillCreditCardEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables the Microsoft Edge AutoFill feature and lets users auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for credit cards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"3dd8f314-46d3-4f8b-ab95-ef34d4f435ef","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F62F62423F74EAFAD0B7B379C75F88855A6F6660\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable AutoFill for credit cards' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAutofillCreditCardEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235746","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235746","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235746","severity":"medium","group_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235746r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235746r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000029","rule_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillAddressEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enables the AutoFill feature and allows users to auto-complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for addresses in the user interface.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"7eb1703e-7584-4090-a433-720ef22aae97","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C471614BC50BE2D95686CEB583DE950DA76EBC06\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable AutoFill for addresses' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAutofillAddressEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235747","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235747","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235747","severity":"medium","group_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","rule_id_src":"SV-235747r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-235747r961038","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000030","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableOnlineRevocationChecks\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If you enable this policy, Microsoft Edge will perform soft-fail, online OCSP/CRL checks. \"Soft fail\" means that if the revocation server can't be reached, the certificate will be considered valid.\n\nIf you disable the policy or don't configure it, Microsoft Edge won't perform online revocation checks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"7d45628f-d9db-4b6f-b30c-1a6635b50dc1","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 12E45BF22EA5A74B3C4A8AB5D8DABC060B992935\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable online OCSP/CRL checks' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tEnableOnlineRevocationChecks (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235748","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235748","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235748","severity":"medium","group_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235748r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235748r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000031","rule_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PersonalizationReportingEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy prevents Microsoft from collecting a user's Microsoft Edge browsing history to be used for personalizing advertising, search, news and other Microsoft services.\n\nThis setting is only available for users with a Microsoft account. This setting is not available for child accounts or enterprise accounts.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot change or override the setting. If this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge will default to the user's preference.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"7fc65e11-a5e5-4c36-8523-4fe6b347594d","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FF2817F38AFA83F6DEFDD655F57F18540A49102F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tPersonalizationReportingEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235749","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235749","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235749","severity":"medium","group_title":"Site tracking of a user’s location must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235749r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235749r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000032","rule_title":"Site tracking of a user’s location must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultGeolocationSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set whether websites can track users' physical locations. Tracking can be allowed by default (\"AllowGeolocation\") or denied by default (\"BlockGeolocation\"), or the user can be asked each time a website requests their location (\"AskGeolocation\").\n\nIf this policy is not configured, \"AskGeolocation\" is used and the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowGeolocation (1) = Allow sites to track users' physical location.\n- BlockGeolocation (2) = Do not allow any site to track users' physical location.\n- AskGeolocation (3) = Ask whenever a site wants to track users' physical location.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"e6cc4b06-fc15-4eaa-b5a0-3e6cf4638dfd","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EAD8EC6450A35CCFB9100A49F09687CEF809D611\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting' is NOT Enabled with 'Don't allow any site to track users' physical location'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultGeolocationSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235750","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235750","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235750","severity":"medium","group_title":"Browser history must be saved.","rule_id_src":"SV-235750r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-235750r960864","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000033","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting disables deleting browser history and download history and prevents users from changing this setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"3c01dbd1-0087-455c-9c01-d6d52dd6bd90","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D632A5B241A726871D65825EC616221F6ECCE7F3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAllowDeletingBrowserHistory (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235751","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235751","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235751","severity":"low","group_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235751r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235751r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000034","rule_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application-related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc., may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"e0d3c864-23a6-4926-b2a6-1f8b48d4ac2d","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 04DBBCE1970B85932B51D5C8779CB0C18F0EDA00\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used' is NOT Enabled with 'Don't allow using the developer tools'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDeveloperToolsAvailability (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235752","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235752","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235752","severity":"low","group_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-235752r1156563_rule","rule_id":"SV-235752r1156563","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000036","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" to \"Enabled\" and select one of the following: \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", \"BlockAllDownloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\". The more restrictive option, \"Block all downloads\", is also acceptable.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DownloadRestrictions\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This configures the type of downloads that Microsoft Edge completely blocks without allowing users to override the security decision.\n\nSet \"BlockDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known dangerous downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockAllDownloads\" to block all downloads.\n\nSet \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known malicious downloads.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or the \"DefaultDownloadSecurity\" option is not set, the downloads go through the usual security restrictions based on Microsoft Defender SmartScreen analysis results.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nDefaultDownloadSecurity (0) = No special restrictions\n\nBlockDangerousDownloads (1) = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads (2) = Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockAllDownloads (3) = Block all downloads\n\nBlockMaliciousDownloads (4) = Block malicious downloads","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"6ca48ee0-c6ec-46cc-b5dd-70423ba003fe","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AB5DA76E362AC2A37BABA908B5C4B305D7B42E76\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow download restrictions' is NOT Enabled with (1)'BlockDangerousDownloads' or (2)'Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads' or (3)'Block all downloads' or (4) 'Block malicious downloads'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDownloadRestrictions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235753","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235753","title":"SRG-APP-000378","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235753","severity":"low","group_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","rule_id_src":"SV-235753r1015297_rule","rule_id":"SV-235753r1015297","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000039","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" to \"Enabled\". A list of allowlisted URLs may be specified here.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"PopupsAllowedForUrls\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Edge allows pop-ups may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns that can open pop-up windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001812","CCI-003980"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"6a257333-f465-44a0-9ec6-aacecf8810fb","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B528B7B185C465C815A5E31DBA11687B1E614E6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow pop-up windows on specific sites' is Not Configured in Group Policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\r\nValue Name:\t (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235754","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235754","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235754","severity":"medium","group_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","rule_id_src":"SV-235754r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235754r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000041","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" to \"Enabled\". A list of blocklisted extensions may then be specified.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1\n\nIf the value for \"1\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = *\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"List specific extensions that users cannot install in Microsoft Edge. When this policy is deployed, any extensions on this list that were previously installed will be disabled, and the user will not be able to enable them. If an item is removed from the list of blocked extensions, the extension is automatically reenabled anywhere it was previously installed.\n\nUse \"*\" to block all extensions that are not explicitly listed in the allow list.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can install any extension in Microsoft Edge.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"6426e1b2-b37a-43e5-a7f5-b14b1d9b6e46","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1304D27CE162EE84554318D935BABA37A423B2B6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control which extensions cannot be installed' is NOT Enabled (With '*' added to the list)\r\n\r\nHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist does not exist."},{"group_id_src":"V-235755","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235755","title":"SRG-APP-000386","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235755","severity":"low","group_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","rule_id_src":"SV-235755r961479_rule","rule_id":"SV-235755r961479","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000042","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" to \"Enabled\".  A list of allowlisted extensions may then be specified.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow specific extensions to be installed\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"ExtensionInstallAllowlist\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1 = \"extension_id1\"\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\2 = \"extension_id2\"\n\nIf configured, the list of extensions for which Microsoft Edge allows to be installed may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"By default, all extensions are allowed. However, if all extensions are blocked by setting the \"ExtensionInstallBlockList\" policy to \"*,\" users can only install extensions defined in this policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"5e0da08d-764f-4690-8f6e-adee05fabca6","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7285442A029EFEE39BC8FB5DA1724C1D11DCC91F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow specific extensions to be installed' is Not Configured in Group Policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\r\nValue Name:\t (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235756","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235756","title":"SRG-APP-000400","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235756","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235756r961521_rule","rule_id":"SV-235756r961521","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000043","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Edge to save user passwords.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users can save their passwords in Microsoft Edge. The next time the user visits the site, Microsoft Edge will enter the password automatically.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002007"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"8b637f83-a90a-4f37-b9a8-e2f9ddd0ed5f","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 166B5A950A9B58050B3EBDA1D2FBED54FEC8AECA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable saving passwords to the password manager' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tPasswordManagerEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235758","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235758","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235758","severity":"high","group_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","rule_id_src":"SV-235758r1117151_rule","rule_id":"SV-235758r1117151","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000045","rule_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Edge.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Microsoft Edge site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available. \n\nIf the installed version of Edge is not supported by Microsoft, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously. \n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw). \n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications themselves that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"25e9749e-a925-4015-b236-cfeb65618e84","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: A13CC9E473F4731F7CBA0920DA92AC28C48B3E95\r\n~~~~~\r\nMicrosoft Edge Version: 150.0.4078.83"},{"group_id_src":"V-235760","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235760","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235760","severity":"medium","group_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235760r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235760r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000047","rule_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" to \"enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SitePerProcess\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"SitePerProcess\" policy can be used to prevent users from opting out of the default behavior of isolating all sites. The \"IsolateOrigins\" policy can be used to isolate additional, finer-grained origins.\n\nEnabling this policy prevents users from opting out of the default behavior where each site runs in its own process.\n\nIf this policy is not disabled or configured, a user can opt out of site isolation (e.g., by using \"Disable site isolation\" entry in edge://flags.) Disabling the policy or not configuring the policy does not turn off Site Isolation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"c3d46766-84a6-425d-9ecc-1fd8079d6b84","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 67185994747B145906E06D5028FCD25CF3D135EC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable site isolation for every site' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tSitePerProcess (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235761","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235761","title":"SRG-APP-000142","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235761","severity":"medium","group_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-235761r1043177_rule","rule_id":"SV-235761r1043177","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000048","rule_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" to \"ntlm,negotiate\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" must be set to  \"ntlm,negotiate\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AuthSchemes\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = ntlm,negotiate\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting specifies which HTTP authentication schemes are supported.\n\nThe policy can be configured by using these values: \"basic\", \"digest\", \"ntlm\", and \"negotiate\". Separate multiple values with commas.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, all four schemes are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"ad05f3fa-da25-4c66-8495-07f98dc51f84","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E9D2A58340DF69C2A15A91167668C33E76FFDA69\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Supported authentication schemes' is NOT Enabled with 'ntlm,negotiate'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAuthSchemes (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235763","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235763","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235763","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235763r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235763r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000050","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SmartScreenEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures Microsoft Defender SmartScreen, which provides warning messages to help protect  users from potential phishing scams and malicious software. By default, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"45bdd518-3b9b-470d-b760-bffe5095d2d5","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 24D8F0A50DF115939D734F2935385E2C9876039F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tSmartScreenEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235764","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235764","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235764","severity":"medium","group_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","rule_id_src":"SV-235764r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235764r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000051","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for SmartScreenPuaEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting configures blocking for potentially unwanted apps with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen provides warning messages to help protect users from adware, coin miners, bundleware, and other low-reputation apps that are hosted by websites. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off by default.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"8c79f781-b445-4c59-983a-784e0be2e634","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 45E8AC2DC45911E71DDDDFD8C2B6D942514311F9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tSmartScreenPuaEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235765","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235765","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235765","severity":"low","group_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-235765r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235765r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000052","rule_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" to \"enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting provides positive feedback before a download starts, limiting the possibility of inadvertent downloads without notifying the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"4a6f4133-ef5d-4f07-8632-8086cb3a6ac7","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 243E2114C12AE3AFF16925CCFABFB117EF4A135F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Ask where to save downloaded files' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tPromptForDownloadLocation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235766","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235766","title":"SRG-APP-000148","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235766","severity":"medium","group_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235766r1051115_rule","rule_id":"SV-235766r1051115","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000054","rule_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"TrackingPrevention\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\" or \"REG_DWORD = 3\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The setting allows websites to be blocked from tracking users' web-browsing activity.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or is not configured, users can set their own level of tracking prevention.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- TrackingPreventionOff (0) = Off (no tracking prevention)\n- TrackingPreventionBasic (1) = Basic (blocks harmful trackers; content and ads will be personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionBalanced (2) = Balanced (blocks harmful trackers and trackers from sites user has not visited; content and ads will be less personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionStrict (3) = Strict (blocks harmful trackers and majority of trackers from all sites; content and ads will have minimal personalization; some parts of sites might not work)","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000388"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"a8037708-0283-4c3e-a386-e4c2caf232e6","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6DF1CB15F77BA1E6E11CCCFE288ECD666029C13E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tTrackingPrevention (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235767","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235767","title":"SRG-APP-000149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235767","severity":"medium","group_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235767r960972_rule","rule_id":"SV-235767r960972","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000055","rule_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for PaymentMethodQueryEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting determines whether websites can check if the user has payment methods saved.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is disabled, websites that use \"PaymentRequest.canMakePayment\" or \"PaymentRequest.hasEnrolledInstrument\" API will be informed that no payment methods are available.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is enabled or is not set, websites can check to determine if the user has payment methods saved.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"6ff13ea9-04a1-44d0-acc7-02b569c1e4b6","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 41786B64DB603865B781DD5ACF91201D201CE0FC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow websites to query for available payment methods' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tPaymentMethodQueryEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235768","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235768","title":"SRG-APP-000151","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235768","severity":"medium","group_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235768r1015298_rule","rule_id":"SV-235768r1015298","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000056","rule_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for AlternateErrorPagesEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows Microsoft Edge to issue a connection to a web service to generate URL and search suggestions for connectivity issues such as DNS errors.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, a web service is used to generate URL and search suggestions for network errors.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, no calls to the web service are made and a standard error page is shown.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Microsoft Edge respects the user preference that is set under Services at edge://settings/privacy. Specifically, there is a \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" toggle, which the user can switch on or off. \n\nNote that if this policy has been enabled (AlternateErrorPagesEnabled), the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found setting\" is turned on, but the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle. \n\nIf this policy is disabled, the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" setting is turned off, and the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-000767"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"2fba7768-b1dd-49b3-b565-b46cfdc2627c","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 788D22661B85BBAEF11B2FB1153258DA6DA6C1E0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tAlternateErrorPagesEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235769","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235769","title":"SRG-APP-000152","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235769","severity":"medium","group_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235769r960981_rule","rule_id":"SV-235769r960981","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000057","rule_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for UserFeedbackAllowed is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Edge uses the Edge Feedback feature (enabled by default) to allow users to send feedback, suggestions, or customer surveys and to report any issues with the browser. By default, users cannot disable (turn off) the Edge Feedback feature.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can invoke Edge Feedback.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot invoke Edge Feedback.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"c7a043ef-825b-469c-8bcd-6b8b1f498b1e","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AD0EAF769A7F3BF87AC2939A701918BB9C3ED51D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow user feedback' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tUserFeedbackAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235770","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235770","title":"SRG-APP-000153","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235770","severity":"medium","group_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235770r960984_rule","rule_id":"SV-235770r960984","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000058","rule_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EdgeCollectionsEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting allows users to access the Collections feature, where they can collect, organize, share, and export content more efficiently and with Office integration.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can access and use the Collections feature in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot access and use Collections in Microsoft Edge.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"1179b861-d4f9-4abe-9776-8411bf7fb92c","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F363272F2B864D88A890824DD156861846A331C9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable the Collections feature' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tEdgeCollectionsEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235771","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235771","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235771","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235771r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235771r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000059","rule_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureShare\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this policy is set to \"ShareAllowed\" (the default), users will be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience from the Settings and More menu in Microsoft Edge to share with other apps on the system.\n\nIf this policy is set to \"ShareDisallowed\", users will not be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience. If the Share button is on the toolbar, it will also be hidden.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- ShareAllowed (0) = Allow using the Share experience.\n- ShareDisallowed (1) = Do not allow using the Share experience.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"58d2056b-6cac-490e-b717-6237fe267f1b","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B108C7B3CE4572EFB44CDB66E4FDA56FD528382\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure the Share experience' is NOT Enabled with 'Don't allow using the Share experience'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tConfigureShare (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235772","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235772","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235772","severity":"medium","group_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235772r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-235772r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000060","rule_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BrowserGuestModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling Guest mode allows the use of guest profiles in Microsoft Edge. In a guest profile, the browser does not import browsing data from existing profiles, and it deletes browsing data when all guest profiles are closed.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge lets users browse in guest profiles.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Microsoft Edge does not let users browse in guest profiles.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"8b57beb7-d885-4ef7-9eec-d13e41259eea","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 99C36A6C2AAB2102D3E0254B92D975C4E10F1550\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable guest mode' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tBrowserGuestModeEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235773","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235773","title":"SRG-APP-000156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235773","severity":"medium","group_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","rule_id_src":"SV-235773r960993_rule","rule_id":"SV-235773r960993","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000061","rule_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" web-browsing activity to \"Required\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Required\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"RelaunchNotification\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users must be required to restart the browser to finish installation of pending updates and prevent users from continually using an old/vulnerable browser version.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"36c09e86-4668-4958-a214-2b52897b8ec7","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 43736EAE68AFFDEF19BE6548649A70593CE12127\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates' is NOT Enabled with 'Required'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tRelaunchNotification (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-235774","group_tree":[{"id":"V-235774","title":"SRG-APP-000157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-235774","severity":"medium","group_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-235774r1015299_rule","rule_id":"SV-235774r1015299","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000062","rule_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BuiltInDnsClientEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls whether to use the built-in DNS client.\n\nThis does not affect which DNS servers are used; it only controls the software stack that is used to communicate with them. For example, if the operating system is configured to use an enterprise DNS server, that same server would be used by the built-in DNS client. However, it is however possible that the built-in DNS client will address servers in different ways by using more modern DNS-related protocols such as DNS-over-TLS.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the built-in DNS client is used if it is available.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the client is never used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"d9b1396c-1868-4f80-968c-dec853b229bd","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FF49FFF7AB8B1D9A8747B913C8C57ABB8FD2680A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Use built-in DNS client' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tBuiltInDnsClientEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-246736","group_tree":[{"id":"V-246736","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-246736","severity":"medium","group_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-246736r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-246736r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000063","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\n\r\nIf the value for \"QuicAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Edge web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\r\n\r\nIf you enable this policy or don't configure it, the QUIC protocol is allowed.\r\n\r\nIf you disable this policy, the QUIC protocol is blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"a1e8855b-356f-4a01-8ab1-1cc09eeb8855","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B829C13FF9DE84EC102E17366344BB132F3A974D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow QUIC protocol' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tQuicAllowed (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251694","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251694","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251694","severity":"low","group_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","rule_id_src":"SV-251694r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251694r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000064","rule_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\r\n\r\nThis requirement for \"AutoplayAllowlist\" is not required; this is optional.\r\n\r\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\n\r\nAutoplayAllowlist may be set as follows:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\1 = mydomain.com\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\2 = myagency.mil\r\n\r\nIf configured, the list of domains for which autoplay is allowed may be allowlisted.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns, that are allowed to autoplay media.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is not configured, the global default value from the AutoplayAllowed policy (if set) or the user's personal configuration is used for all sites.\r\n\r\nEDGE-00-000024 disables the AutoplayAllowed policy. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"9b03d6e6-1696-4775-8eb2-fe833c6882b5","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DCE0AA2DA6434C6BEFA1804EDE7FFF2042786B7F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow media autoplay on specific sites' is Not Configured in Group Policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\r\nValue Name:\t (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-260465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260465","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260465","severity":"medium","group_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-260465r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-260465r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000065","rule_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" is set to \"Disabled\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\n\r\nIf the value for \"VisualSearchEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Visual Search allows for quick exploration of more related content about entities in an image.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Visual Search will be enabled via image hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is disabled, Visual Search will be disabled and more information about images will not be available via hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"cf3e09ba-05f8-42bb-bdd1-2c7277644a06","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6AFECCFC20D6F2023BDA4BEE7855675CB8CC2A56\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Visual search enabled' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tVisualSearchEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-260466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260466","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260466","severity":"medium","group_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-260466r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-260466r960963","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000066","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" is set to \"Disabled\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\n\r\nIf the value for \"HubsSidebarEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Sidebar is a launcher bar on the right side of Microsoft Edge's screen.\r\n\r\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, the Sidebar will be shown. If this policy is disabled, the Sidebar will never be shown.\r\n\r\nDisabling Sidebar will disable Copilot.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"f2478cfe-3d24-48ac-b2c3-a80df512315b","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2EB312CC9C40B13695DA47E1C64E05D2AF826FC3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Show Hubs Sidebar' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tHubsSidebarEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-260467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-260467","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-260467","severity":"medium","group_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-260467r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-260467r960864","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000067","rule_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" is set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\n\r\nIf the value for “DefaultCookiesSetting” is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 4\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \r\n\r\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the \"CookiesAllowedForUrls\" or \"SaveCookiesOnExit\" policy settings, but these are not requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"94d3defb-9eba-438a-9d1a-65128e848b6d","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EAB94BC66871E774DCEAAE22EA4E0316A96C53D2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure cookies' is NOT Enabled: (Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultCookiesSetting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-266981","group_tree":[{"id":"V-266981","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-266981","severity":"medium","group_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-266981r1169858_rule","rule_id":"SV-266981r1169858","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000068","rule_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft EdgeConfigure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" to \"enabled\" and select \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\"","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If FriendlyURLs are enabled, Microsoft Edge will compute additional representations of the URL and place them on the clipboard.\n\nThis policy configures what format will be pasted when the user pastes in external applications, or inside Microsoft Edge without the \"Paste As\" context menu item.\n\nIf configured, this policy makes a choice on behalf of the user. The options in edge://settings/shareCopyPaste will be grayed out, and the options in the \"Paste As\" context menu will not be available.\n\nNot configured = The user will be able to choose their preferred paste format. By default, this is set to the friendly URL format. The \"Paste As\" menu will be available in Microsoft Edge.\n\n1 = No additional formats will be stored on the clipboard. There will be no \"Paste as\" context menu item in Microsoft Edge and the only format available to paste will be the plain text URL format. Effectively, the friendly URL feature will be disabled.\n\n3 = The user will get a friendly URL whenever they paste into surfaces that accept rich text. The plain URL will still be available for non-rich surfaces. There will be no \"Paste As\" menu in Microsoft Edge.\n\n4 = (Not currently used)\n\nThe richer formats may not be well-supported in some paste destinations and/or websites. In these scenarios, the plain URL option is recommended when configuring this policy.\n\nThe recommended policy is available in Microsoft Edge 105 or later.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nPlainText (1) = The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\n\nTitledHyperlink (3) = Titled Hyperlink: A hyperlink that points to the copied URL, but whose visible text is the title of the destination page. This is the Friendly URL format.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"68e077c2-7170-4f9c-b17c-683d3008354e","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8FDBE357925EFE024C6219E94206BC8688B28BB5\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users' is NOT Enabled: (The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title.)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tConfigureFriendlyURLFormat (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-279940","group_tree":[{"id":"V-279940","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-279940","severity":"medium","group_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-279940r1156561_rule","rule_id":"SV-279940r1156561","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000069","rule_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" to \"disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ComposeInlineEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy controls whether users can use writing support features in Microsoft Edge for Business, such as Rewrite, which utilizes Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"3b7fa25c-691e-4e22-8f42-39aabf1049ee","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2279DF9A2A4969191F9BE318E228C9B0D7221FDB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tComposeInlineEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-283439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-283439","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-283439","severity":"medium","group_title":"Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-283439r1192850_rule","rule_id":"SV-283439r1192850","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000070","rule_title":"Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for MicrosoftEditorProofingEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Edge_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Microsoft Editor service provides enhanced spell and grammar checking for editable text fields on web pages.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or incorrectly configured, Microsoft Editor spell check can be used for eligible text fields.\n\nIf you disable this policy, spell check can only be provided by local engines that use platform or Hunspell services. The results from these engines might be less informative than the results Microsoft Editor can provide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5280","uuid":"c923c6a2-28a1-448e-a34b-13322b5b9dd7","stig_uuid":"dfe3f216-ed6b-4fdf-8f52-fddf7eadd2aa","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MicrosoftEdge_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EF14503EB98EF1D5909CDBFD68B9C812221A06B4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Spell checking provided by Microsoft Editor' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\r\nValue Name:\tMicrosoftEditorProofingEnabled (Not found)"}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:18:34.9070615-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-IE11_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11","stig_id":"IE_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"2","uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","reference_identifier":"4095","size":137,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-223015","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223015","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223015","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223015r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223015r961863","rule_version":"DTBI015-IE11","rule_title":"The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' to 'Enabled'.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"WarnOnBadCertRecving\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter warns users if the certificate being presented by the website is invalid. Since server certificates are used to validate the identity of the web server it is critical to warn the user of a potential issue with the certificate being presented by the web server. This setting aids to prevent spoofing attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59339","V-46475"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"ffdddc24-0c55-4726-ada2-0e1baa535f47","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F130DE9E33D61F104538EDD649BDFBFC7FABAA5\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tWarnOnBadCertRecving (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223016","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223016","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223016","severity":"low","group_title":"Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223016r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-223016r961038","rule_version":"DTBI018-IE11","rule_title":"Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and select the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box.\n\nNote: Manual entry in the registry key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Current Version\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing for the value \"State\", set to \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", may first be required.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab, from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and verify the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box is selected.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing Criteria\n\nIf the value \"State\" is \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Check for publisher's certificate revocation options should be enforced to ensure all PKI signed objects are validated.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59341","V-46477"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"03f2bef8-9de0-4f88-a101-610ba4eeb4c7","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 757E01250E8EAC514BF9BB8064AB552E42F56EB0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Check for publisher's certificate revocation' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\r\nValue Name:\tState\r\nValue:\t\t0x00023c00 (146432)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-223017","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223017","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223017","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223017r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223017r961089","rule_version":"DTBI022-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active X controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download signed ActiveX controls from a page in the zone. If you enable this policy, users can download signed controls without user intervention. If you select Prompt in the drop-down box, users are queried whether to download controls signed by untrusted publishers. Code signed by trusted publishers is silently downloaded. If you disable the policy setting, signed controls cannot be downloaded.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59345","V-46481"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"c25d23bb-dd9c-4b28-920a-dadc1905a430","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 308DF38C46A6B8F5D20BAE5D89EA592C9A39EC68\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Download signed ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1001 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223018","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223018","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223018","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223018r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223018r961089","rule_version":"DTBI023-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download unsigned ActiveX controls from the zone. If you enable this policy setting, users can run unsigned controls without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow the unsigned control to run. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59347","V-46483"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"f5ad1582-d4f4-485f-814d-a3d4312fc006","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 15741470EA703D9F4CDB1EF62EEDD62DBFDE4B64\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1004 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223019","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223019","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223019","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223019r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223019r961092","rule_version":"DTBI024-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59365","V-46501"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"3af108ef-88d1-42ee-85f8-b44fe6108ad3","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CF61E9E9DA066A171CA9603669C5B171520A1034\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1201 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223020","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223020","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223020","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Java permissions must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223020r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223020r960963","rule_version":"DTBI031-IE11","rule_title":"The Java permissions must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59371","V-46507"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"5f376a06-c19b-4a79-9105-8ca197856da2","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A26FF47135444C8B10B1704091D708ACAF6C48A0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223021","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223021","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223021","severity":"medium","group_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223021r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223021r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI032-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. Access to data sources across multiple domains must be controlled based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59373","V-46509"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"f65ddea5-ad96-42d4-8bd1-f38580a4c8e6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F8503C332AF982D1CDAB03D6474CCD0E8F4D3EF9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Access data sources across domains' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1406 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223022","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223022","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223022","severity":"medium","group_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223022r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223022r960963","rule_version":"DTBI036-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value for \"1802\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Internet zone are likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59375","V-46511"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a2b0f0d5-c895-43c0-aab3-d2fcfa64eff2","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 289FD18746DA6C8138255341386AEC052C2E79FF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1802 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223023","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223023","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223023","severity":"medium","group_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223023r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223023r960963","rule_version":"DTBI038-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59377","V-46513"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"338e2cb8-8c11-4221-a772-35618a12c462","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0339B247B030C1BA88C32E5D9F8E8F52929DB35D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1804 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223024","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223024","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223024","severity":"medium","group_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223024r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223024r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI039-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\InternetSettings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Frames that navigate across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59379","V-46515"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"767852aa-b3f6-4437-a8e3-1344c8457c0d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FC534A5A6109B2B08480BBB4C0DE24D9B3BA8516\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1607 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223025","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223025","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223025","severity":"medium","group_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223025r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223025r961128","rule_version":"DTBI042-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. It is possible for sites hosting malicious content to exploit this feature as part of an attack against visitors browsing the site. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59381","V-46517"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"9003e7aa-6c5a-4f71-a8e6-76d9b7392925","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 23FC7719833C3C3691ACEA427089DD5AE92BEA86\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Userdata persistence' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1606 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223026","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223026","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223026","severity":"medium","group_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223026r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223026r960963","rule_version":"DTBI044-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59385","V-46521"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"62c9d118-5afc-4914-8171-7de4a7ab82e1","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3F7900A834A2ADBAF4CAC7E272DF9DE678DB8087\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1407 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223027","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223027","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223027","severity":"medium","group_title":"Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223027r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223027r1043178","rule_version":"DTBI046-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt for user name and password' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt for user name and password' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. “Anonymous logon” disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. “Prompt for user name and password” queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone” queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. “Automatic logon with current user name and password” attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone”. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone”. The most secure option is to configure this setting to “Enabled”; “Anonymous logon”, but configuring this setting to “Enabled”; “Prompt for user name and password”, provides a reasonable balance between security and usability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59387","V-46523"],"ccis":["CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"fecbd889-6348-48b2-9971-eeb62f14750f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C2DCD0BF117B6596A5A51B2C08DD60815DE2954E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Logon options' is NOT Enabled: (Prompt for user name and password)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1A00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223028","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223028","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223028","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223028r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223028r960963","rule_version":"DTBI061-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59389","V-46525"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"dfcf28e5-7358-4ff8-97fa-5cf4cf39bae8","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 41596FE8FBE7AEFC08D38921B96747AB90E6414A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (High Safety)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223029","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223029","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223029","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223029r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223029r961086","rule_version":"DTBI062-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59865","V-46999"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"97e8757e-f54e-4a4c-bc0a-852d77b3fd4b","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 51AE4EB5D0CF057D84AE0C48E65AC67E1B5F8886\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\r\nValue Name:\t270C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223030","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223030","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223030","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223030r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223030r960963","rule_version":"DTBI091-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59407","V-46543"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"4069a3fd-e39f-495b-a2aa-eb9f394e788d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 530FDA4B03D1EAEB624BB351F0478B9017A25EC8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (High Safety)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223031","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223031","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223031","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223031r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223031r961086","rule_version":"DTBI092-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59875","V-47009"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"7c2d6808-0462-4b2e-ab72-a4cfd1789dcb","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D82D54A4C683BD8C368B7C6A8268E3CB4451FD04\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\r\nValue Name:\t270C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223032","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223032","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223032","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223032r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223032r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI1000-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59409","V-46545"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"9c944025-238c-43b9-b8fc-63fae00cba80","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DCA235321EB8CD4F6C4B85EEE4A7113671A7495\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2708 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223033","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223033","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223033","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223033r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223033r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI1005-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you enable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59411","V-46547"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"827d7b3d-f5a5-453e-a594-21dd2c5a2e0f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0BBFE888927DE60AFECDD7D214BC8528A6D22B91\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2709 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223034","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223034","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223034","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223034r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223034r960921","rule_version":"DTBI1010-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59413","V-46549"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"3b08dc7a-7f72-43dd-8198-c753d7c17ce5","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BB7C7697C57CF9B0EDA25F2E3F8D934E96A016CB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223035","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223035","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223035","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223035r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223035r960921","rule_version":"DTBI1020-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59417","V-46553"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"61282fff-a529-4981-9e14-302df60a5c89","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CE3E425E2EFEECF4FC43B68A6A40A8972F14FD7B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223036","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223036","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223036","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223036r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223036r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI1025-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59419","V-46555"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"e26e44ff-7b88-496c-ba24-92366e280461","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B2F2A0C107A0715BD235DB85F47EF0409D72DAE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2708 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223037","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223037","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223037","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223037r961086","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59863","V-46997"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"e0b57f6d-4d84-4e85-bb4f-a9ad505848b6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1A9E0DC0EDFA2D9B3CBE6D751D03389570FA9DD0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t270C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223038","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223038","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223038","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223038r961086","rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59871","V-47005"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"6ab72f67-84a5-4082-8735-5bca4875b550","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7FFF1C6DFB1C5BA1CF7DFF1EC6DD42F65B5989FA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t270C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223039","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223039","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223039","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings” to ”Enabled”.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings” must be ”Enabled”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"46f346e0-421d-4638-a10b-546c10776ce3","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8656EA05D96BE8765F36C2BCA5646AC15C1B559F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\r\nValue Name:\tPreventOverride (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223040","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223040","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223040","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet” to ”Enabled”.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet” must be ”Enabled”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"c7349c1a-e12a-4972-8ac2-95514599dbe0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 35AA34F6FCE3C0E78702BDE0922F3D505F42FE3A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\r\nValue Name:\tPreventOverrideAppRepUnknown (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223041","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223041","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223041","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092","rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls” to ”Enabled”.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> ”Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls” must be ”Enabled”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"c1313ea3-5eeb-4d01-95ea-fb848850f018","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E4951A8A23215C1FC9782AFF071DB538CB712B8D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\r\nValue Name:\tBlockNonAdminActiveXInstall (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223042","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223042","title":"SRG-APP-000427","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223042","severity":"medium","group_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> ”Prevent ignoring certificate errors” to ”Enabled”.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> ”Prevent ignoring certificate errors” must be ”Enabled”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as “expired”, “revoked”, or “name mismatch” errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"ccis":["CCI-001954"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"074324d2-9ff3-47f2-a153-1d606708d783","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5AFC5ED728050D1ADEE1B0F2876C750B4D15B076\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent ignoring certificate errors' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tPreventIgnoreCertErrors (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223043","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223043","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223043","severity":"medium","group_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> ”Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan” to ”Enabled”, and select ”Enable” from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> ”Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan” must be ”Enabled” and ”Enable” selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"94e0fd4e-be03-4264-a297-c864547a1a01","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B4BE65691F106CDA3A68B0C5E6B06F50CCF770D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2301 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223044","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223044","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223044","severity":"medium","group_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> ”Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan” to ”Enabled”, and select ”Enable” from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> ”Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan” must be ”Enabled” and ”Enable” selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a0dac68c-2c6e-477b-adb9-8a8879218475","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 832FCF28580DFD41F4ADAB15E4C310C94265640B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2301 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223045","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223045","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223045","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Intranet Zone >> ”Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe” to ”Enabled”, and select ”Disable” from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Intranet Zone >> ”Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe” must be ”Enabled” and ”Disable” selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"69e0cc09-4dee-4458-b00e-bfd042ac5adf","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2542C05428DEF046C946D52289772579787EB340\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\r\nValue Name:\t1201 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223046","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223046","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223046","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Trusted Sites Zone >> ”Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe” to ”Enabled”, and select ”Disable” from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Trusted Sites Zone >> ”Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe” must be ”Enabled” and ”Disable” selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"4e0d2acd-6ede-49f4-89af-3dd215550916","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1F814C6DDE75E900499905A626945B25A0635E84\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\r\nValue Name:\t1201 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223048","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223048","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223048","severity":"medium","group_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to “Enabled”. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"95e5a52c-1d4b-48ad-a601-033a14763e2d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E601CE68E31B217443F43060113CE5AB0DD52DD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\r\nValue Name:\tRunThisTimeEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223049","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223049","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223049","severity":"medium","group_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to “Disabled”. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"947d130c-6390-4180-afcf-fe4dc53c29b9","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BE41B04516B4D2ECDED1684F18953B55CA0BDD9B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\r\nValue Name:\tVersionCheckEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223050","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223050","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223050","severity":"medium","group_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223050r960963","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Pane >> Security Page >> Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to “Enabled”. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the “Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is “Enabled”. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the “Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to “Enable”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = “3”, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"67a4cef9-f21e-40a7-837b-2f05faae769a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3A9773FA064B65134AA447ADAAC99AEF51618621\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control' is NOT Enabled: (Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t120c (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223051","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223051","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223051","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"233bd6f5-3c64-4523-8926-8c01eba0d895","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 82E15B792E84953AF64DA17E63B9145382C8A68A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Download signed ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1001 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223052","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223052","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223052","severity":"medium","group_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223052r960963","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to “Enabled”.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the “Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is “Enabled”. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the “Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to “Enable”. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = “3”, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users won’t be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"0ece1949-00c9-43d4-98bf-5b6af88cdb7f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 11216BA36EFD92641D59EBC907896C4A644AD36C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control' is NOT Enabled: (Only allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t120c (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223053","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223053","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223053","severity":"medium","group_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Internet Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"c8992259-26ac-4904-8864-1fcafc003855","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B61A05A7AB399DB0979BD1B6699339A9B05AAB1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t140C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223054","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223054","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223054","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"708292c4-4f90-4713-ba6f-81b3754e68f3","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FB6F75FB9EACB7E11E074F855B2133CA63BED048\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1004 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223055","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223055","title":"SRG-APP-000209","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223055","severity":"medium","group_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Security Page >> Restricted Sites Zone >> \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"ccis":["CCI-001169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"fd4aa9e1-4cab-44eb-885b-85d50b540dbd","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E713CC39F02EB2548B8620CAAA35D5E2D93622FC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t140C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223056","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223056","title":"SRG-APP-000266","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223056","severity":"low","group_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Toolbars >> “Turn off Developer Tools” to “Enabled”.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Toolbars >> “Turn off Developer Tools” must be “Enabled”. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"ccis":["CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"90b59c6b-8292-4984-a0e4-efbd7deef5a6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C28FA0DB64E7570EF550306ECE2D8E14634D3397\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Developer Tools' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\r\nValue Name:\tDisabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223057","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223057","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223057","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223057r961092","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"168e2cf0-b63c-4854-a8cb-269b69347802","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3468E13B3BCF296C92FFA2B7EA40334E0C640A90\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1201 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223058","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223058","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223058","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"af005625-1e38-4690-a385-c0c92f3ca733","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A397177AF88234AA2066D6A740F1D8C4583EF742\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1200 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223059","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223059","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223059","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223059r961092","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"048da4c2-a663-45e6-af6b-e7cb09bdf1ba","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E960B53C38D8751D5EF5ECC34E67B64B0668F1AB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1405 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223060","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223060","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223060","severity":"medium","group_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"4ccdcb8e-cc95-4933-8b68-6eecb5ccf472","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AE0FADF6515FA7C0E48D73256D04C08E254D654\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow file downloads' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1803 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223061","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223061","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223061","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"fb34e087-195b-47cc-a06e-72862489d1f9","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 40A65F7553588C1A2519FD52948F02B33E6D03DB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223062","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223062","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223062","severity":"medium","group_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1c98994e-06ba-4794-8215-202937b58f92","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 38A30DEF24F4941E6E335C53B06F31CB850FC266\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Access data sources across domains' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1406 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223063","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223063","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223063","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863","rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"bb7df8e1-03d6-4c17-ab31-4665110f4b13","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 97DF379B8E45F74A271E2F1847C0DE562DE07394\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow META REFRESH' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1608 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223064","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223064","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223064","severity":"medium","group_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223064r960963","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a486097b-57ea-4b9f-bd17-ad8f6ae0819e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 82BC5E58810263CC18389EEFD411978B536B330B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1802 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223065","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223065","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223065","severity":"medium","group_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223065r960963","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"d34f55c8-dec5-4c74-9bd7-73bf827dcb59","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C55060F53768FF746AD82A7FA97CE56B4600131\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1804 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223066","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223066","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223066","severity":"medium","group_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a19b9dcd-d7f5-4567-938a-9010e302d78e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F7547DD38332F1B360A88EBB67146082DAEBA05E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1607 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223067","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223067","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223067","severity":"medium","group_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223067r961128","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"4f37886e-b3f3-4472-9b5b-578381726314","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 964D6998E2AEFA7AA4B854C364B1C4AE7836FE74\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Userdata persistence' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1606 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223068","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223068","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223068","severity":"medium","group_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963","rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"5f138d76-0a09-4bbc-a26e-4cc2a5c30c91","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DACEDBE349C8F7039E1E6A9FA90ADBECA7E21527\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow active scripting' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1400 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223069","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223069","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223069","severity":"medium","group_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"24d58f14-a4ed-432f-bf5c-92e4e941f19e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 43A0FD625FCD702B561BD81E8EC298CA984739B9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1407 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223070","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223070","title":"SRG-APP-000219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223070","severity":"medium","group_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178","rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. “Anonymous logon” disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. “Prompt for user name and password” queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone” queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. “Automatic logon with current user name and password” attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone”. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to “Automatic logon only in Intranet zone”. The most secure option is to configure this setting to “Enabled”; “Anonymous logon”. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"ccis":["CCI-001184"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"e8e4f5ca-719d-4bdd-bbea-8bb1a1e6537b","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7570061F55BBD3A704F07E0146DADBBB40217128\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Logon options' is NOT Enabled: (Anonymous logon)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1A00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223071","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223071","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223071","severity":"medium","group_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223071r960879","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"76de0088-7acb-41fa-b08b-687353698d41","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D44465FE24E406AD672761ECAFF78183F7636180\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Configuring History' is NOT Enabled: (40 Days)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History\r\nValue Name:\tDaysToKeep (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223072","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223072","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223072","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"19f29be2-057d-416b-b51a-48ba164ab825","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 29DCC0C9F36A4E54B1F5761073ADA271B08813EF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tSecurity_zones_map_edit (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223073","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223073","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223073","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1e75ce32-ff3e-4d6b-bb24-3c41eaeeb7c0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0CB8BD8B70E80CBF35E4D9F7C3D98F4786BF561A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tSecurity_options_edit (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223074","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223074","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223074","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"bdb48bc4-e558-4edb-87a4-d10288f39871","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C71B19C292E9E23768D68C060E8206EA250B3995\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tSecurity_HKLM_only (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223075","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223075","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223075","severity":"medium","group_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a453978d-5cb3-4a2b-bb47-f21cbf426c5f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5104B465C2C5B32BFCCA34975013F81A44EE239E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\r\nValue Name:\tDisableSecuritySettingsCheck (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223076","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223076","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223076","severity":"medium","group_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"8f1cc2df-a1c7-4e37-834a-0dba88651582","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 418107DFA8978607F0A45A6625000338EA3FEB94\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download\r\nValue Name:\tRunInvalidSignatures (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223077","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223077","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223077","severity":"medium","group_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"72759d11-fb26-41fa-b4a5-cb043954909b","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 93039DC4694D08FF63850E63C0786CD695709404\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tIsolation64Bit (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223078","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223078","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223078","severity":"low","group_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"9d5a78f6-707d-40a8-9d96-8eca51f01bfa","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1173A642F16141C8387E179F04283BFBB7261C5D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Check for server certificate revocation' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tCertificateRevocation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223079","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223079","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223079","severity":"medium","group_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Advanced Page -> 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"ccis":["CCI-001749"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"4a70b003-9159-45fd-a40b-7cd5021a4ff2","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 906C94ACE6202E7C7F9E9C6A7128F293CE6470BE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download\r\nValue Name:\tCheckExeSignatures (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223080","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223080","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223080","severity":"medium","group_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"db5b836b-29e8-40c4-937d-7221c6eb71a4","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A391C196FABBA14C71B31289138C95A97D20B9BB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap\r\nValue Name:\tUNCAsIntranet (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223081","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223081","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223081","severity":"medium","group_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"2feacda9-6d98-4098-be77-4138b1cc34a5","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1C73FA4778FD61ED6AD73CACE32EBC6E2C9B05EF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2102 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223082","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223082","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223082","severity":"medium","group_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"eb404c4d-bfea-46a1-aae6-9b1352b28207","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8053F09AEFC8A856B4E20CBD3F13240FD846E0A0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2102 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223083","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223083","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223083","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"8b2db08d-9124-4139-841b-8e1812082e4b","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C8A4E4B814979CE7E12111CD42564E13E6394E02\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Scriptlets' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1209 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223084","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223084","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223084","severity":"medium","group_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"08afb21c-2556-4372-8304-7982ede2e42f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F05496521BEE4A4B0DAE80BE3EE639BD52F0ED29\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Automatic prompting for file downloads' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2200 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223085","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223085","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223085","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"2e04f45b-6489-4376-9bf7-ff80fa2d083b","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F55616976F8EB4C0E2CDE811081941DCFE64A20C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223086","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223086","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223086","severity":"medium","group_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page ->Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1a8f9ad5-8d83-4bd5-9ebe-fd043eb84e5a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B14AA89B957B5C4E81E43CA7124C6173A388F27A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0\r\nValue Name:\t270C (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223087","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223087","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223087","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"b1e2d46c-1730-4020-9bab-336533c02b9a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F8FEDE533DB4930256BD3BA125CB251D92FEF39\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223088","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223088","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223088","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223088r960963","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Intranet Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a00b2113-7b81-4d30-87d3-4057e7898f1d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D2463B9E8EFA5F8CE31A0FB926B060FE9890091E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223089","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223089","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223089","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"ca66a702-32d5-4275-93e1-8655c6e94ce0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B9E45A5B6CED5EB3D471445EA87108D035C650E2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223090","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223090","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223090","severity":"medium","group_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963","rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a55218d8-b4a1-4a7a-a4b9-f43d8829a4cb","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1C94FB1E21F84763FAF9325A380E50DB563B9528\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Java permissions' is NOT Enabled: (Disable Java)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1C00 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223091","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223091","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223091","severity":"medium","group_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"9f1dd7ed-004f-404d-8cc1-6b53f971e161","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AC023E4AB056F3BB0C54BEAC69A4DC7906D1632A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow loading of XAML files' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2402 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223092","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223092","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223092","severity":"medium","group_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223092r961863","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"5a32f9f5-06fc-46c2-b50e-48b08a8dac89","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E21E788CA190F08C42DAF43E813EAA6A21217CF7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow loading of XAML files' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2402 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223093","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223093","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223093","severity":"medium","group_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"6987b512-a08f-448c-813b-92532094c689","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3D935BBEFDDE859AE93C5253A70B72700A4AB73E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on Protected Mode' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2500 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223094","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223094","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223094","severity":"medium","group_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"abda4d64-34a0-4985-bfb5-fd7e1d1d20d0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AF553F5A44473737E066F165CF1EC5E90697B882\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on Protected Mode' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2500 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223095","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223095","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223095","severity":"medium","group_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"32f94c12-4ced-4d23-b20e-b5b0b087e70c","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 912FDFFCB80E3D9F11CD2705ABCACAB388919D5A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Use Pop-up Blocker' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1809 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223096","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223096","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223096","severity":"medium","group_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"004fb019-8bcc-4cb3-ad26-c5d3cdeb190f","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BBEC7B84FE5D985CC4F2BF3E745482365AC3823A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Use Pop-up Blocker' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1809 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223097","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223097","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223097","severity":"medium","group_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"711c2ddc-41b5-4210-a9f3-a64fbe365f3c","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 632530CEA853D9CD06CC2EE482E8CF24FE66B7C0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2101 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223098","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223098","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223098","severity":"medium","group_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"d822052d-93f0-438a-8035-082a701fceeb","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B3351C28649014A799F1F2147B8EB9995162C70\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2101 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223099","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223099","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223099","severity":"medium","group_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223099r960963","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"49040263-c42a-47ac-a75b-eeabe85c94a6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E3E3E2979A461698C211E54A5A097E5FF506CC0C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow binary and script behaviors' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2000 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223100","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223100","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223100","severity":"medium","group_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"a10adf37-74a3-4d22-90c0-c59f7ec84b01","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E2CA702B6059C61DEC001AD750F0B482149BC910\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Automatic prompting for file downloads' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2200 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223101","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223101","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223101","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"2ae8265c-6ed2-4e3c-a2ce-fe8d78307180","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9BE687CCA78EEBB1AB333C90122E219ECF6AD406\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223102","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223102","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223102","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083","rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"d07b093a-3303-4e18-9696-0baf3a67fac3","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DCD1C31A29A96081411BF134161FEFA0D0E5928\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223103","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223103","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223103","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Consistent Mime Handling -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"99f80122-b12e-4650-91ef-d0aa43c97373","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C7548D477EFDDA9004FB0F1EA4597FEBC9F58EF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223104","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223104","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223104","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083","rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"5df30285-4b9f-4aca-8498-5baaf1c74e08","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2FD76748E80AF02867DAC90607220A12AA8252A6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223105","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223105","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223105","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59581","V-46717"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"e3bdc048-9144-419b-a3f9-7c7748f5e94e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B261D893B0B5AC3E12A8E695E24ED44B3B6FA5E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223106","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223106","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223106","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223106r961083","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"cdfe9f1d-847e-482d-a754-ac044a2d3f19","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 483D963F18565FE760EF96FAF9537A0E8322CFF8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223107","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223107","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223107","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"538400b9-aab6-4bc1-af94-ec316768565a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C8709D62DE5CCEE48B112F2438CF404C5A53BB4F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223108","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223108","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223108","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"33befec1-958d-49d1-8dd8-1942e3378ab7","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AC524E5F6C0ACDC2B2C0923F812EFA2C2C03B28D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223109","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223109","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223109","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> MK Protocol Security Restriction -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1560a875-8a99-46d4-b363-a81417312d6e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 295C151E9FF4C5C5785A29F8F98027F15CEF31EE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223110","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223110","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223110","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"cf8030f6-39e3-447c-864b-411fa8e29cf1","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B7D88FBCF183F65137ADC0C05412882B445C02B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223111","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223111","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223111","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223111r961131","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"69fafeef-1ea8-4ddb-9f44-6bcaf9f0cc82","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B80D7ED2DD66E21BD9F68D3A601D9E4C45BBAFEC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223112","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223112","title":"SRG-APP-000233","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223112","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Protection From Zone Elevation -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"77b22b67-b0d1-44cf-af54-8c40969dcdd0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6D201A8D451FA28490176A57FC538450E5C496AA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223113","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223113","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223113","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"99fa94ab-093a-477f-9b49-fba17f784423","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6E9462A60353EB57BE1C06E5B2B215FCD5963EAB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223114","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223114","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223114","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"3fb684b9-d8ed-45ca-bb50-4883c027477c","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7518670E1AEAB7267179B4130D6DFCFC3EEDFB68\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223115","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223115","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223115","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223115r960963","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict File Download -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"55a824a6-da4b-43ef-bb43-eb325d5aa1fe","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 69A62A32E016BA7E0C9D0C8CB0AB8BC3571AD42D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223116","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223116","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223116","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223116r960963","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1701c40f-58cc-4382-97ab-8d1d4da54c06","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7D78BBF7157DFB1EE816674E3BD5BBB6B572CE2E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223117","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223117","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223117","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1ced7921-649c-4fa7-8428-d43f56b22599","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DEEC9351957D62C9A83930A58F6F685E7A7C0F92\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223118","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223118","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223118","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Scripted Window Security Restrictions -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"49965874-495a-4212-96ac-ebd1323cbefb","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BC278F11729F33A15387CBBEA1BF2DBBB74EF36A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223119","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223119","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223119","severity":"medium","group_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"7a302c51-af14-4177-8feb-bae6e27031d0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4319139A0C8183F6C6E9A1B89CC046264C818578\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2004 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223120","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223120","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223120","severity":"medium","group_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"6bc3a1f5-296f-4c13-912f-3f0db2c25ba9","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8AAA8E706082D9683B3F86D24D18A619018A02FF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2001 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223121","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223121","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223121","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223121r960963","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"62d041b4-49e0-4e4b-aa43-79f84a298526","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C5E4638278768E6BD93AC2FBF6CA2F2F9C962D06\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Scripting of Java applets' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1402 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223122","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223122","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223122","severity":"medium","group_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"dac9732e-1c6e-4243-ac60-ab63e4e891fd","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 7D57F0A4FA5385FF91D078CAEEB5043A9279E4C4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable AutoComplete for forms' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tUse FormSuggest (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223123","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223123","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223123","severity":"medium","group_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"07594c4f-be0b-48b5-9a9e-97322189f401","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E7595F32D7ADFC0F0D121E60E15198207FB710DC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Crash Detection' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions\r\nValue Name:\tNoCrashDetection (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223124","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223124","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223124","severity":"medium","group_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"cb9cb430-f136-4794-8461-8d8e7c73f41a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: F95A41D51F91850C7FAF21AB3D9A26300C6BDC73\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tFormSuggest Passwords\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tFormSuggest PW Ask\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223125","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223125","title":"SRG-APP-000206","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223125","severity":"medium","group_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"ccis":["CCI-001166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"0e069ddf-0449-414a-abf6-6f47f5f1a8f6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FD85295C3C28F6CE266DFBBABD6939020F3784A0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter' is NOT Enabled: (On)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\r\nValue Name:\tEnabledV9 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223126","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223126","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223126","severity":"medium","group_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223126r960879","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"031decd5-653e-4606-a3c6-29e0213dae38","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 447E67EE903B540C7264A05755FEEDA44B90964E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\r\nValue Name:\tClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223127","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223127","title":"SRG-APP-000089","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223127","severity":"medium","group_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Delete Browsing History -> 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"eec2f5ef-aa4b-4abc-9834-9ba2ce7ce659","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3D877E190110B5F5E91DAA3D87B9DB1BAFFC7A90\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\r\nValue Name:\tCleanHistory (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223128","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223128","title":"SRG-APP-000080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223128","severity":"medium","group_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","rule_id":"SV-223128r960864","rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Privacy -> 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Privacy -> 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"d56fde1f-5b24-4f22-a0de-58044a5345d5","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 72A387EA29356DB1E3EB4F3F71FA9152744A4D80\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy\r\nValue Name:\tEnableInPrivateBrowsing (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223129","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223129","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223129","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"dfd92a9d-0fd8-4d34-bee5-946082d4b7d0","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EA8287212EDF569E3933E9F9D011C4AA4F978BCC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1206 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223130","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223130","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223130","severity":"medium","group_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223130r960963","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"ef2c4427-86d3-402f-8200-16032d4384ed","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8C789DDCDB5E787A0134AB4AA4A1B246F2DFB010\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t160A (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223131","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223131","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223131","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"41a920c4-932f-426c-910e-6c7e3c2698ef","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F09852A8496EE133E2BC578150DBC20B24E5CAAB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223132","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223132","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223132","severity":"medium","group_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"23728be7-174d-430a-aed2-ccd4266a36a6","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A96EB9B6E9B6661133BC2745275604932A9312F9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' is NOT Enabled: (Prompt)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1806 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223133","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223133","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223133","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"82ddde32-a98d-4b01-9fe0-6e57eca959c4","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 83EC77CFC0FA4881EB8397572583F3683EAD3202\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\texplorer.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223134","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223134","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223134","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"774a2e6a-7879-4bb1-a403-08d8fd448b6e","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 47CDCC737BC037B70C26C3C4107BF0EB6FED0154\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t120b (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223135","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223135","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223135","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features-> Notification Bar-> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"7473ad92-b7e6-4daf-93c7-faedf659192d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F5C257A9B120E836F8472994BFBD6639E0CADC57\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tiexplore.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223136","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223136","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223136","severity":"medium","group_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223136r960963","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"8f0c242a-4211-4a24-9689-87b1d8b70def","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 09DA4EFA8FAA10BD5BD7A644CC0ACDD99966B1FE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t1409 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223137","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223137","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223137","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223137r960963","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"11a8e8dc-576b-4a8f-9d47-80011a471950","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 450437BF0DCEB7E154C74EBA5A0279B6C7C83427\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1206 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223138","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223138","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223138","severity":"medium","group_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"0cac2914-2a9e-4547-a6ac-8f9a87fe8800","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F3460AE384E97885A92EF4490E0251B84F9753B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t160A (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223139","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223139","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223139","severity":"medium","group_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1c648388-594f-4f02-8761-bf392e7fa575","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B380CBB30A2E2C65CEB30100AEC2DFFA54A8E18\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1806 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223140","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223140","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223140","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"6519914b-0611-44e7-9631-b1d89dc72ede","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0BA791EA6E706210230211B4CEE2E75CAE62186B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t120b (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223141","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223141","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223141","severity":"medium","group_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone -> 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"099f6fb8-6d23-4776-b32d-d2076c9d2ffa","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0A7F6362AA0B71D38E0A8C57E0D088F9BE73D9BB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' is NOT Enabled: (Enable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1409 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223142","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223142","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223142","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Security Features -> Restrict ActiveX Install -> 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"7d3097a7-3310-4e72-b3ec-b5d880cd28f9","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4D8FC4013738F26C536FE7780E17E7831FF007E7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Internet Explorer Processes' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\t(Reserved) (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223143","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223143","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223143","severity":"medium","group_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223143r960963","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"e66b7bbf-b2b4-4d34-965f-b870e93b56fc","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F3D88EF49B891E85CCA5D74F2AB23FA6E17E2C4B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow updates to status bar via script' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2103 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223144","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223144","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223144","severity":"medium","group_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"f72cbf6d-2eb9-46f8-ba6e-b6e0550660e7","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C6E67725DEBE7EF37CC5B27CC3926986C5ACB6EA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2004 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223145","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223145","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223145","severity":"medium","group_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223145r961863","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"1237aede-6a6b-4482-89b6-78e621037113","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E318EA6CB3E120BCFCA38D1977493F801A0F988B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2001 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223146","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223146","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223146","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223146r960963","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"8ffac08c-fca8-4db3-a0f5-ea8fa641f285","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 929603E15E98A83E2A091ADBB4B24A4CD460FF13\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Scriptlets' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t1209 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223147","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223147","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223147","severity":"medium","group_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer -> Internet Control Panel -> Security Page -> Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"5b80c060-a3af-4a27-a65b-ed634f9ff717","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 622FC6FE53842CFF06AA0D4B65D05FF619BA592D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow updates to status bar via script' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\r\nValue Name:\t2103 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223148","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223148","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223148","severity":"medium","group_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"ea20adab-bbb8-4321-92c6-e5f30a405548","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B3C0AD73E4B358A357A29F9B3B45A8AB40EF23A1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tDisableEPMCompat (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223149","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223149","title":"SRG-APP-000039","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223149","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Internet Explorer-> Internet Control Panel-> Security Page-> Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"7541c570-5ac7-4cb0-97c6-07434155389a","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5C8E876DDD7417234E10DC4183BDC15864D41279\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' is NOT Enabled: (Disable)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\r\nValue Name:\t2709 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-250540","group_tree":[{"id":"V-250540","title":"SRG-APP-000416","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-250540","severity":"medium","group_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Advanced Page >> \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Internet Control Panel >> Advanced Page >> \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"fc017742-a80d-4e56-b91b-a835f96abf4d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BA86F0DC3F438EFCF65108B90C9BA9CBFBB1EFBD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Encryption Support' is NOT Enabled: (Use TLS1.1, Use TLS 1.2)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tSecureProtocols (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-250541","group_tree":[{"id":"V-250541","title":"SRG-APP-000416","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-250541","severity":"medium","group_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Internet Explorer >> Security Features >> \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"b7ba1223-af5b-46dd-a7a6-26e6fd63991d","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7EF0D0A4BF42658F88A2CC3D273B3601BAE1875C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is NOT Enabled: (No Sites)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\r\nValue Name:\tEnableSSL3Fallback (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-252910","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252910","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252910","severity":"high","group_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1192839_rule","rule_id":"SV-252910r1192839","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","fix_text":"Disable the Internet Explorer 11 application. Open PowerShell as an Administrator and run the command (this is irreversible):\r\n\r\ndism /online /Remove-Capability /CapabilityName:Browser.InternetExplorer~~~~0.0.11.0\r\n\r\nRestart the system for the changes to take effect.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor with the exception of some operating system versions under extended support (Ex: Windows Server 2019).\r\n\r\nTo determine the status of Internet Explorer 11 on the system, open PowerShell as an Administrator and run the command:\r\n\r\ndism /online /get-capabilityinfo /capabilityname:Browser.InternetExplorer~~~~0.0.11.0\r\n\r\nWithin the returned results, if \"State : Installed\", this is a finding.\r\n\r\nWithin the returned results, if \"State : Not Present\", this is not a finding.\r\n\r\nIf the host operating system is supported under an extended support agreement, and \"State : Installed\", this is not a finding.\r\n\r\nIf nothing related to Internet Explorer is returned, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Internet_Explorer_11_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"4095","uuid":"2d316869-a02f-4c15-a7ca-6a542f69782c","stig_uuid":"dd821ceb-2e23-4b35-937e-332577f51bf0","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-IE11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 603A47D18D8A57208A02669747CA37D36DFEC449\r\n~~~~~\r\nOperating Caption: Microsoft Windows 11 Pro\r\nOperating Product Name: Windows 10 Pro 25H2\r\nOperating System Version: 10.0.26200\r\n\r\nInternet Explorer 11 is no longer supported on this operating system. [finding]\r\n\r\nReference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/lifecycle/faq/internet-explorer-microsoft-edge"}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:18:59.9221803-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-Office365_Checks","version":"1.2026.5.14"}},"stig_name":"Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus","stig_id":"MS_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG","release_info":"Release: 5 Benchmark Date: 01 Apr 2026","version":"3","uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","reference_identifier":"4099","size":139,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-223280","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223280","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223280","severity":"medium","group_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Access files from the Internet.","rule_id_src":"SV-223280r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223280r961050","rule_version":"O365-AC-000001","rule_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Access files from the Internet.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if “Enable all macros” is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to “Enable Content”, users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. If the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108737","V-99633"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"c59ca347-7a34-4767-977c-0717f14ca41f","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 094B6D7D4C518E808D6A4C8F77E70CD8D5183185\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\r\nValue Name:\tblockcontentexecutionfrominternet (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223281","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223281","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223281","severity":"medium","group_title":"Trust Bar Notifications for unsigned application add-ins in Access must be disabled and blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223281r1016166_rule","rule_id":"SV-223281r1016166","rule_version":"O365-AC-000002","rule_title":"Trust Bar Notifications for unsigned application add-ins in Access must be disabled and blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value NoTBPromptUnsignedAddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf users enable this policy setting, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf users do not configure this policy setting, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108739","V-99635"],"ccis":["CCI-001749","CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"fc45fbe6-e844-48d4-bfb0-91d61d418aee","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 694FD2054452EEAB2EB2BBC61FAED2DB4435A6D8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Trust Center Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\r\nValue Name:\tNoTBPromptUnsignedAddin (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223282","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223282","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223282","severity":"medium","group_title":"VBA macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Access.","rule_id_src":"SV-223282r1082349_rule","rule_id":"SV-223282r1082349","rule_version":"O365-AC-000003","rule_title":"VBA macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Access.","fix_text":"Set User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Access 2016 >> Application Settings >> Security >> Trust Center >> VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD = 2 or REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist, or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros. If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed/approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108741","V-99637"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"68dbb7f4-fd42-47d8-ac79-6ca41e9c102b","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: A22D67E6BCA67D6692B1F3435054F23F6B9B5A11\r\n~~~~~\r\n'VBA Macro Notification Settings' is NOT Enabled: (Disable all except digitally signed macros)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\r\nValue Name:\tvbawarnings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223284","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223284","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223284","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Macro Runtime Scan Scope must be enabled for all documents.","rule_id_src":"SV-223284r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223284r961092","rule_version":"O365-CO-000001","rule_title":"The Macro Runtime Scan Scope must be enabled for all documents.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016>> Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" to \"Enable for all documents\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016>> Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" is set to \"Enable for all documents\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \r\n\r\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\r\n\r\nIf the value for macroruntimescanscope is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.\r\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting specifies for which documents the VBA Runtime Scan feature is enabled.\r\n\r\nIf the feature is disabled for all documents, no runtime scanning of enabled macros will be performed.\r\n\r\nIf the feature is enabled for low trust documents, the feature will be enabled for all documents for which macros are enabled except:\r\n - Documents opened while macro security settings are set to \"Enable All Macros\"\r\n - Documents opened from a Trusted Location\r\n - Documents that are Trusted Documents\r\n - Documents that contain VBA that is digitally signed by a Trusted Publisher\r\n\r\nIf the feature is enabled for all documents, then the above class of documents are not excluded from the behavior.\r\n\r\nThis protocol allows the VBA runtime to report to the Anti-Virus system certain high-risk code behaviors it is about to execute and allows the Anti-Virus to report back to the process if the sequence of observed behaviors indicates likely malicious activity so the Office application can take appropriate action.\r\n\r\nWhen this feature is enabled, affected VBA projects' runtime performance may be reduced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108745","V-99641"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"eac4e1db-927c-4d30-b57e-449d3ba8792a","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: CEF44B3B1CB47D45D1F52332EF711B5346FCEA1E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Macro Runtime Scan Scope' is NOT Enabled: (Enable for all documents)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\r\nValue Name:\tmacroruntimescanscope (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223285","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223285","title":"SRG-APP-000429","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223285","severity":"high","group_title":"Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files must be protected.","rule_id_src":"SV-223285r1067544_rule","rule_id":"SV-223285r1067544","rule_version":"O365-CO-000002","rule_title":"Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files must be protected.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value DRMEncryptProperty is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether metadata is encrypted in Office Open XML files that are protected by Information Rights Management (IRM). If this policy setting is enabled, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word encrypt metadata stored in rights-managed Office Open XML files and override any configuration changes on users' computers. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 2016 applications cannot encrypt metadata in rights-managed Office Open XML files, which can reduce security. If this policy setting is not configured when Information Rights Management (IRM) is used to restrict access to an Office Open XML document, any metadata associated with the document is not encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108747","V-99643"],"ccis":["CCI-002476"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"3c844c45-a32c-4b8f-bb01-8273d0087318","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: B54385A540CDB67FF7D17D9C4AD4D1D0FAC51C92\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\r\nValue Name:\tDRMEncryptProperty (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223286","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223286","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223286","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Office client must be prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.","rule_id_src":"SV-223286r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223286r960963","rule_version":"O365-CO-000003","rule_title":"The Office client must be prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Server Settings >> Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links to \"Enabled\".  ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Server Settings >> Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links is set to \"Enabled\".\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \r\n\r\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\portal\r\n\r\nIf the value for linkpublishingdisabled is REG_DWORD = \"1\", this is not a finding.\r\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can poll Office servers to retrieve lists of published links. \r\n\r\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot poll an Office server for published links. \r\n\r\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of Office 365 ProPlus applications can see and use links to Microsoft SharePoint Server sites from those applications. Published links can be configured to Office applications during initial deployment, and can add or change links as part of regular operations. These links appear on the My SharePoint Sites tab of the Open, Save, and Save As dialog boxes when opening and saving documents from these applications. Links can be targeted so they only appear to users who are members of particular audiences. \r\n\r\nNote: This policy setting applies to Microsoft SharePoint Server specifically. It does not apply to Microsoft SharePoint Foundation.\r","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108749","V-99645"],"ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"2216b966-7900-46eb-9220-3cc482908a26","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: F52280ECBE57BB96FC500D876231C617360C7318\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\portal\r\nValue Name:\tlinkpublishingdisabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223287","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223287","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223287","severity":"medium","group_title":"Custom user interface (UI) code must be blocked from loading in all Office applications.","rule_id_src":"SV-223287r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223287r961863","rule_version":"O365-CO-000004","rule_title":"Custom user interface (UI) code must be blocked from loading in all Office applications.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Global Options >> Customize >> Disable UI extending from documents and templates to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Global Options >> Customize >> Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\n\nIf the value noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument is REG_DWORD = 1 for all installed Office programs, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications load any custom user interface (UI) code included with a document or template. Office 365 ProPlus allows developers to extend the UI with customization code that is included in a document or template. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot load any UI customization code included with documents and templates. \n\nIf this policy setting is not configured or disabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications load any UI customization code included with a document or template when opening it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108751","V-99647"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"fc682152-e7ee-44f9-aa5b-f29a2cd094cb","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: D7A3C2FCBB825CA5C98C3FDDD47E431EFA116602\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable UI extending from documents and templates' is NOT Enabled: (Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\access\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\excel\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\infopath\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\outlook\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\powerpoint\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\project\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\publisher\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\visio\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\word\r\nValue Name:\tnoextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223288","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223288","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223288","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX Controls must be initialized in Safe Mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-223288r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223288r961779","rule_version":"O365-CO-000005","rule_title":"ActiveX Controls must be initialized in Safe Mode.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" to \"Enabled + 6\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" is set to \"Enabled (If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values.)\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value UFIControls is set to REG_DWORD=6, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting specifies the Microsoft ActiveX initialization security level for all Microsoft Office applications. ActiveX controls can adversely affect a computer directly. In addition, malicious code can be used to compromise an ActiveX control and attack a computer. \n\nTo indicate the safety of an ActiveX control, developers can denote them as Safe for Initialization (SFI). SFI indicates that a control is safe to open and run, and that it is not capable of causing a problem for any computer, regardless of whether it has persisted data values or not. If a control is not marked SFI, it is possible that the control could adversely affect a computer--or it could mean that the developers did not test the control in all situations and are not sure whether it might be compromised in the future. If you enable this policy setting, you can set the ActiveX security level to a number between 1 and 6. These security levels are as follows:\n \n1. Regardless of how the control is marked, load it and use the persisted values (if any). This setting does not prompt the user. \n\n2. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, load in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or use the default (first-time initialization) settings. This level is similar to the default configuration, but does not prompt the user. \n\n3. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n4. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n5. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\n6. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, if a control is marked SFI, the application loads the control in safe mode and uses persisted values (if any). If the control is not marked SFI, the application loads the control in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or uses the default (first-time initialization) settings. In both situations, the Message Bar informs users that the controls have been disabled and prompts them to respond. \n\nImportant: Some ActiveX controls do not respect the safe mode registry setting, and therefore might load persisted data even though you configure this setting to instruct the control to use safe mode. This setting only increases security for ActiveX controls that are accurately marked as SFI. In situations that involve malicious or poorly designed code, an ActiveX control might be inaccurately marked as SFI.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108753","V-99649"],"ccis":["CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"2f2dc22c-4081-4cca-ad47-1650da648a38","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: BE3B2C819A7427561BA16CA0BFD3E3767A83E769\r\n~~~~~\r\n'ActiveX Control Initialization' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\r\nValue Name:\tUFIControls (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223289","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223289","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223289","severity":"medium","group_title":"Macros in all Office applications that are opened programmatically by another application must be opened based upon macro security level.","rule_id_src":"SV-223289r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223289r961092","rule_version":"O365-CO-000006","rule_title":"Macros in all Office applications that are opened programmatically by another application must be opened based upon macro security level.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Automation Security\" to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Automation Security\" is set to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value AutomationSecurity is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether macros can run in an Office 365 ProPlus application that is opened programmatically by another application. If this policy setting is enabled, the user can choose from three options for controlling macro behavior in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word when the application is opened programmatically:\n\n- Disable macros by default ¬- all macros are disabled in the programmatically opened application. \n- Macros enabled (default) - macros can run in the programmatically opened application. This option enforces the default configuration in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. \n- User application macro security level - macro functionality is determined by the setting in the \"Macro Settings\" section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, when a separate program is used to launch Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, or Word programmatically, any macros can run in the programmatically opened application without being blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108755","V-99651"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"16d2d49a-3dce-48d4-b845-ac89553c8152","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: CCFA68D532AD1FE0212F875076313DA90018CA6E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Automation Security' is NOT Enabled: (Use application macro security level)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\r\nValue Name:\tAutomationSecurity (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223290","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223290","title":"SRG-APP-000131","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223290","severity":"medium","group_title":"Trust Bar notifications must be configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223290r1016167_rule","rule_id":"SV-223290r1016167","rule_version":"O365-CO-000007","rule_title":"Trust Bar notifications must be configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\n\nIf the value trustbar is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications notify users when potentially unsafe features or content are detected, or whether such features or content are silently disabled without notification. \n\nThe Message Bar in Office 365 ProPlus applications is used to identify security issues, such as unsigned macros or potentially unsafe add-ins. When such issues are detected, the application disables the unsafe feature or content and displays the Message Bar at the top of the active window. The Message Bar informs the users about the nature of the security issue and, in some cases, provides the users with an option to enable the potentially unsafe feature or content, which could harm the user's computer. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications do not display information in the Message Bar about potentially unsafe content that has been detected or has automatically been blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108757","V-99653"],"ccis":["CCI-001749","CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"4a2cb82e-37f2-492c-a077-afa6288a5b2c","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: EFE4720390E9465E5446902F85F3F5EE46CB6742\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\r\nValue Name:\ttrustbar (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223291","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223291","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223291","severity":"medium","group_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","rule_id_src":"SV-223291r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223291r961128","rule_version":"O365-CO-000008","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value defaultencryption12 is set to REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting enables you to specify an encryption type for password-protected Office 97-2003 files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications will use to encrypt password-protected files in the older Office 97-2003 file formats. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n<Encryption Provider>,<Encryption Algorithm>,<Encryption Key Length>.\nFor example, Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word use Office 97/2000 Compatible encryption, a proprietary encryption method, to encrypt password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108759","V-99655"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"d6075ce7-9a8f-4368-bc33-fc32d16f1a0a","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: C9D8D2193D948EEDF3F1FF0C7F56224E269A072F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files' is NOT Enabled: (Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\r\nValue Name:\tdefaultencryption12 (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223292","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223292","title":"SRG-APP-000231","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223292","severity":"medium","group_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office Open XML files.","rule_id_src":"SV-223292r961128_rule","rule_id":"SV-223292r961128","rule_version":"O365-CO-000009","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office Open XML files.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value OpenXMLEncryption is REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to specify an encryption type for Office Open XML files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications use to encrypt password-protected files in the Office Open XML file formats used by Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n<Encryption Provider>,<Encryption Algorithm>,<Encryption Key Length>\n\nFor example: Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the default CSP is used. The default cryptographic service provider (CSP) is Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider, AES-128, 128-bit.\n\nNote: This policy setting does not take effect unless the registry key \nHKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\<office application name>\\Security\\Crypto\\CompatMode is set to 0. By default the CompatMode registry key is set to 1.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108761","V-99657"],"ccis":["CCI-001199"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"62edd489-5e1a-4c6f-9ce3-262bbdefcdcf","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 686336AD091D439FD63D2364AAAA785749707712\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files' is NOT Enabled: (Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\r\nValue Name:\tOpenXMLEncryption (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223293","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223293","title":"SRG-APP-000340","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223293","severity":"medium","group_title":"Users must be prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.","rule_id_src":"SV-223293r961353_rule","rule_id":"SV-223293r961353","rule_version":"O365-CO-000010","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings >> Trust Center >> Allow mix of policy and user locations to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016\\Security Settings\\Trust Center >> Allow mix of policy and user locations is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value for allow user locations is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations can be defined by users, the Office Customization Tool (OCT), and Group Policy, or if they must be defined by Group Policy alone.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify any location as a trusted location, and a computer can have a combination of user-created, OCT-created, and Group Policy-created trusted locations.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, all trusted locations that are not created by Group Policy are disabled and users cannot create new trusted locations in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the equivalent of setting the policy to Enabled.\n\nNote: InfoPath and Outlook do not recognize trusted locations, and therefore are unaffected by this policy setting.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108763","V-99659"],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"e61785b2-2f2a-4a2d-bd84-7c4d3442211f","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: C0F4585B85B8DC49BEDE77653297D7AE7DB68CCB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow mix of policy and user locations' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\r\nValue Name:\tallow user locations (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223294","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223294","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223294","severity":"medium","group_title":"Office applications must not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.","rule_id_src":"SV-223294r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223294r961863","rule_version":"O365-CO-000012","rule_title":"Office applications must not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Smart Documents (Word, Excel) >> Disable Smart Document's use of manifests to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Smart Documents (Word, Excel) >> Disable Smart Document's use of manifests is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\common\\smart tag\n\nIf the value for neverloadmanifests is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can load an XML expansion pack manifest file with a Smart Document.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108767","V-99663"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"f1818e37-5cde-47e8-9796-0c5e7f83effc","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: CE7DB35E788128AAB792B64ADC204DD926577B0B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Smart Document's use of manifests' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\smart tag\r\nValue Name:\tneverloadmanifests (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223295","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223295","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223295","severity":"medium","group_title":"The load of controls in Forms3 must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223295r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223295r961086","rule_version":"O365-CO-000013","rule_title":"The load of controls in Forms3 must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" to \"Enabled:1\" or set it to \"Disabled.\"   ","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 >> Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" is set to Enabled and 1 from drop down. (For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration.)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\VBA\\Security\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms does not exist, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows the user to control how ActiveX controls in UserForms should be initialized based upon whether they are Safe for Initialization (SFI) or Unsafe for Initialization (UFI). \n \nActiveX controls are Component Object Model (COM) objects and have unrestricted access to users' computers. ActiveX controls can access the local file system and change the registry settings of the operating system. If a malicious user repurposes an ActiveX control to take over a user's computer, the effect could be significant. To help improve security, ActiveX developers can mark controls as SFI, which means that the developer states that the controls are safe to open and run and not capable of causing harm to any computers. If a control is not marked SFI, the control could adversely affect a computer, or the developers may not have tested the control in all situations and are not sure whether their control might be compromised at some future date. SFI controls run in safe mode, which limits their access to the computer. For example, a worksheet control can both read and write files when it is in unsafe mode, but perhaps only read from files when it is in safe mode. This functionality allows the control to be used in very powerful ways when safety was not important, but the control would still be safe for use in a Web page. If a control is not marked as SFI, it is marked UFI, which means that it is capable of affecting a user's computer. If UFI ActiveX controls are loaded, they are always loaded in unsafe mode. \n \nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for loading controls in UserForms: \n \n1. For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration. \n \n2. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using the default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control that supports both safe and unsafe modes, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using safe mode. If the SFI control can only support safe mode, load the control in safe mode. This option is the default configuration in the Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus release. \n \n3. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control with its default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode. \n \n4. For a UFI signed control, load with the default properties of the control. For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode (considered to be the safest mode). \n \nIf  this policy setting is disabled or not configured, the behavior is as if this policy setting is enabled and then select option \"1\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108769","V-99665"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"5997499b-4f10-40b7-8987-b982e8e2f32d","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 1C7D9AEEE28BB647763DA98A05E4D095683CC64C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Load Controls in Forms3' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\vba\\security\r\nValue Name:\tLoadControlsInForms (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223296","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223296","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223296","severity":"medium","group_title":"Add-on Management must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223296r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223296r961086","rule_version":"O365-CO-000014","rule_title":"Add-on Management must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Add-on Management\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Add-on Management\" is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\n\nIf the value for each installed Office Program is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer add-ons are pieces of code, run in Internet Explorer, to provide additional functionality. Rogue add-ons may contain viruses or other malicious code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network. For example, a malicious user can monitor and then use keystrokes that user's type into Internet Explorer. Even legitimate add-ons may demand resources, compromising the performance of Internet Explorer and the operating systems for user computers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108771","V-99667"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"50ef2762-802c-47a1-b6fe-91148a740769","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 898171E00BE1B60C5BE96C72D527685A4EC26FE2\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223297","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223297","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223297","severity":"medium","group_title":"Consistent MIME handling must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223297r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223297r961050","rule_version":"O365-CO-000015","rule_title":"Consistent MIME handling must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Consistent Mime Handling\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Consistent Mime Handling is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_handling\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is set to is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied on to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108773","V-99669"],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"03bc2cd1-83a2-4a49-bf18-26e48fa7296e","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 499B1A1C5D4F1C9549F866F3B469F14A292F2879\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223298","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223298","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223298","severity":"medium","group_title":"User name and password must be disabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223298r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223298r961092","rule_version":"O365-CO-000016","rule_title":"User name and password must be disabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Disable user name and password\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security \"Disable user name and password\" is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) standard allows user authentication to be included in URL strings in the form http://username:password@example.com. A malicious user might use this URL syntax to create a hyperlink that appears to open a legitimate website but actually opens a deceptive (spoofed) website. For example, the URL http://www.wingtiptoys.com@example.com appears to open http://www.wingtiptoys.com but actually opens http://example.com. To protect users from such attacks, Internet Explorer usually blocks any URLs using this syntax.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108775","V-99671"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"948aa8dc-cd5c-4d1b-91ed-3703873d1ec0","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D3D55A13E6C43A96EC1567432FB1F037A4557703\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_HTTP_USERNAME_PASSWORD_DISABLE\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223299","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223299","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223299","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Information Bar must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223299r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223299r961086","rule_version":"O365-CO-000017","rule_title":"The Information Bar must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Information Bar to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Information Bar is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_securityband\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications notify users when potentially unsafe features or content are detected, or whether such features or content are silently disabled without notification. The Message Bar in Office 2016 applications is used to identify security issues, such as unsigned macros or potentially unsafe add-ins. When such issues are detected, the application disables the unsafe feature or content and displays the Message Bar at the top of the active window. The Message Bar informs the users about the nature of the security issue and, in some cases, provides the users with an option to enable the potentially unsafe feature or content, which could harm the user's computer. \n\nIf you enable this policy setting, Office 365 ProPlus applications do not display information in the Message Bar about potentially unsafe content that has been detected or has automatically been blocked. \n\nIf you disable this policy setting, Office 365 ProPlus applications display information in the Message Bar about content that has automatically been blocked. \n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, if an Office 365 ProPlus application detects a security issue, the Message Bar is displayed. However, this configuration can be modified by users in the Trust Center.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108777","V-99673"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"5e4d1844-0ee2-4ec9-b378-033cb47fc2d5","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2E733BAD767E3CA1ED1E05885E2D9B3ADC5764A4\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223300","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223300","title":"SRG-APP-000516","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223300","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223300r961863_rule","rule_id":"SV-223300r961863","rule_version":"O365-CO-000018","rule_title":"The Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Local Machine Zone Lockdown to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_localmachine_lockdown\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page users can use the browser to open. Web pages on a user's local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine zone, making this security zone a prime target for malicious users and code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow pages in the Internet zone to navigate to pages in the Local Machine zone to then run code to elevate privileges. This could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108779","V-99675"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"07849e33-f474-492b-929b-c30e472e73eb","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 09E70807B75630B148A2E80B89E32365EF6EC9C0\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223301","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223301","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223301","severity":"medium","group_title":"The MIME Sniffing safety feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223301r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223301r961050","rule_version":"O365-CO-000019","rule_title":"The MIME Sniffing safety feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature to \"Enabled\" for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Mime Sniffing Safety Feature is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_sniffing\n\nIf the value for all installed Office Programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108781","V-99677"],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"9892face-8ef7-4143-a47f-1a86851f1b0f","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 70CC034CA60068C7BDF83B66ECCCAE6B1F7D6518\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223302","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223302","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223302","severity":"medium","group_title":"Navigate URL must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223302r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223302r961092","rule_version":"O365-CO-000020","rule_title":"Navigate URL must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Navigate URL to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Navigate URL is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_validate_navigate_url\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To protect users from attacks, Internet Explorer usually does not attempt to load malformed URLs. This functionality can be controlled separately for instances of Internet Explorer spawned by Office applications (for example, if a user clicks a link in an Office document or selects a menu option that loads a web page). If Internet Explorer attempts to load a malformed URL, a security risk could occur.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108783","V-99679"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"1862dd25-f1de-4113-aacb-5ef67a845f10","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2034E8730CC61102730190534B00FA0BEF4EC194\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_VALIDATE_NAVIGATE_URL\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223303","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223303","title":"SRG-APP-000179","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223303","severity":"medium","group_title":"Object Caching Protection must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223303r961050_rule","rule_id":"SV-223303r961050","rule_version":"O365-CO-000021","rule_title":"Object Caching Protection must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Object Caching Protection to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Object Caching Protection is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_object_caching\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108785","V-99681"],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"1ebd9c41-7597-4242-b259-c873edab187f","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 68933F980B713EA7D07DA47E5BA613BE46398F33\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_OBJECT_CACHING\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223304","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223304","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223304","severity":"medium","group_title":"Protection from zone elevation must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223304r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223304r960921","rule_version":"O365-CO-000022","rule_title":"Protection from zone elevation must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Protection from Zone Elevation to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Protection from Zone Elevation is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_zone_elevation\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page users can use the browser to open. Web pages on a user's local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine zone, making this security zone a prime target for malicious users and code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow pages in the Internet zone to navigate to pages in the Local Machine zone to then run code to elevate privileges. This could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108787","V-99683"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"84cbbc8a-f971-4744-9c8e-9438c5d91be1","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 313C0E5970F4E318962578B6BE922923146BCD46\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223305","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223305","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223305","severity":"medium","group_title":"ActiveX installation restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223305r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223305r961779","rule_version":"O365-CO-000023","rule_title":"ActiveX installation restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict ActiveX Install to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict ActiveX Install is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_restrict_activexinstall\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls allow unmanaged, unprotected code to run on the user computers. ActiveX controls do not run within a protected container in the browser like the other types of HTML or Microsoft Silverlight-based controls. Disabling or not configuring this setting does not block prompts for ActiveX control installations, and these prompts display to users. This could allow malicious code to become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108789","V-99685"],"ccis":["CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"b6e87d46-026e-46dc-8668-8e3b76a106ec","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0735DBFDF9560E49AF4F7D009D6BA8F9BF493F69\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223306","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223306","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223306","severity":"medium","group_title":"File Download Restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223306r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223306r960921","rule_version":"O365-CO-000024","rule_title":"File Download Restriction must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict File Download to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Restrict File Download is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_restrict_filedownload\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling this setting allows websites to present file download prompts via code without the user specifically initiating the download. User preferences may also allow the download to occur without prompting or interaction with the user. Even if Internet Explorer prompts the user to accept the download, some websites abuse this functionality. Malicious websites may continually prompt users to download a file or present confusing dialog boxes to trick users into downloading or running a file. If the download occurs and it contains malicious code, the code could become active on user computers or the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108791","V-99687"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"7f6c16be-78ff-4c00-9ded-559d9ef4f2db","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ACA13D3AD417433771BF8DD9633534D1FD380BC2\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223307","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223307","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223307","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Save from URL feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223307r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223307r961092","rule_version":"O365-CO-000025","rule_title":"The Save from URL feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Saved from URL to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Saved from URL is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\r\n\r\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\r\n\r\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_unc_savedfilecheck\r\n\r\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Typically, when Internet Explorer loads a web page from a Universal Naming Convention (UNC) share that contains a Mark of the Web (MOTW) comment, indicating the page was saved from a site on the Internet, Internet Explorer runs the page in the Internet security zone instead of the less restrictive Local Intranet security zone. This functionality can be controlled separately for instances of Internet Explorer spawned by Office applications (for example, if a user clicks a link in an Office document or selects a menu option that loads a web page). If Internet Explorer does not evaluate the page for a MOTW, potentially dangerous code could be allowed to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108793","V-99689"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"648801fe-242b-405a-b418-6d38d5425c02","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6DA6DEA50600BDC37B6F23386AC8AEA92167FB1B\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_UNC_SAVEDFILECHECK\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223308","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223308","title":"SRG-APP-000112","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223308","severity":"medium","group_title":"Scripted Windows Security restrictions must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223308r960921_rule","rule_id":"SV-223308r960921","rule_version":"O365-CO-000026","rule_title":"Scripted Windows Security restrictions must be enabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >>Scripted Window Security Restrictions to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) >> Security Settings >> IE Security >> Scripted Window Security Restrictions is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malicious websites often try to confuse or trick users into giving a site permission to perform an action allowing the site to take control of the users' computers in some manner. Disabling or not configuring this setting allows unknown websites to:\n- Create browser windows appearing to be from the local operating system.\n- Draw active windows displaying outside of the viewable areas of the screen capturing keyboard input.\n- Overlay parent windows with their own browser windows to hide important system information, choices, or prompts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108795","V-99691"],"ccis":["CCI-001695"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"db4e3b3e-4809-4b20-bc03-9f35c164f9e8","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B2C393065F3ABC454AA77E4BC5CE17709A71F4F1\r\n~~~~~\r\nInstalled Programs: Access, Excel, OneNote, Outlook, PowerPoint, Publisher, Visio, Word\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tmsaccess.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\texcel.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tonenote.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\toutlook.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tpowerpnt.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tmspub.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\tvisio.exe (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\r\nValue Name:\twinword.exe (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223309","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223309","title":"SRG-APP-000488","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223309","severity":"medium","group_title":"Flash player activation must be disabled in all Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223309r961779_rule","rule_id":"SV-223309r961779","rule_version":"O365-CO-000027","rule_title":"Flash player activation must be disabled in all Office programs.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> Block Flash activation in Office documents >> Enabled >> Block all activation to \"Enabled\" (Block all activation).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> Block Flash activation in Office documents >> Enabled >> Block all activation is set to \"Enabled\" Block all activation.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\COM Compatibility\n\nIf the value for COMMENT is REG_SZ = Block all Flash activation, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the Adobe Flash control can be activated by Office documents. Note that activation blocking applies only within Office processes.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options to control whether and how Flash is blocked from activation:\n\n1. \"Block all activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded, whether directly referenced by the document or indirectly by another embedded object.\n2. \"Block embedding/linking, allow other activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded when directly referenced by the document, but does not prevent activation through another object.\n3. \"Allow all activation\" restores Office's default behavior, allowing the Flash control to be activated.\n\nBecause this setting is not a true Group Policy setting and \"tattoos\" the registry, enabling the \"Allow all activation\" option is the only way to restore default behavior after either of the \"Block\" options has been applied. It is not recommended to configure this setting to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\" after it has been enabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108797","V-99693"],"ccis":["CCI-002460"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"cd46f10b-1757-4631-9660-209acabdb09d","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1302115C4AB04EFDA8DDE5818E6D18C932067AEC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Block Flash activation in Office documents' is NOT Enabled: (Block all activation)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\COM Compatibility\r\nValue Name:\tCOMMENT (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223310","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223310","title":"SRG-APP-000210","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223310","severity":"medium","group_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Excel.","rule_id_src":"SV-223310r961092_rule","rule_id":"SV-223310r961092","rule_version":"O365-EX-000001","rule_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Excel.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value AllowNetworkLocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by selecting the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Disabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list. Instead, it forces the selected application to treat the locations as non-trusted and prevents users from adding new network locations to the list.\n\nIf you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers.\n\nDisabling this policy setting will cause disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. However, it is not recommended to enable this policy setting (as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box itself states), so in practice it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108799","V-99695"],"ccis":["CCI-001170"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"5d4e8b9a-ecab-4e99-81e2-eda43fb629fc","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: BEB1E94FB22A1EA0DD11E99E057E067527EE903B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Trusted Locations on the network' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\r\nValue Name:\tAllowNetworkLocations (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223311","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223311","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223311","severity":"medium","group_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Excel.","rule_id_src":"SV-223311r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-223311r960963","rule_version":"O365-EX-000002","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Excel.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options is selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108801","V-99697"],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"b51991bf-89c1-43cc-a8f6-e23fcff58ba5","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 14BA45710854AE62441D02968F939590958279C9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'VBA macro Notification Settings' is NOT Enabled: (Disable all except digitally signed macros)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\r\nValue Name:\tvbawarnings (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223312","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223312","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223312","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223312r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223312r961086","rule_version":"O365-EX-000003","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlaunch\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch by going to File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> External Content.\n\nFor security reasons, turning on DDE server launch is not recommended.\n\nNote: For DDE server launch to work, Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup must be turned on. Be sure that the “Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup” policy setting is not enabled, because enabling that policy setting turns off DDE server lookup.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server launch is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, DDE server launch is allowed, and users cannot turn off DDE server launch in the Trust Center. For security reasons, this is not recommended.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108803","V-99699"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"81d05ac4-0ac9-4919-bd7a-0297e5212808","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 490B43DEC938DE456D0A83845937ECFFA7401848\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\r\nValue Name:\tdisableddeserverlaunch (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223313","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223313","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223313","severity":"medium","group_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223313r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223313r961086","rule_version":"O365-EX-000004","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> External Content >> Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlookup\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup by going to File >> Options >> Trust Center >> Trust Center Settings >> External Content.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server lookup is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: If you are using Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch, which is not recommended, do not enable this policy setting, because DDE server launch requires DDE server lookup to be on.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108805","V-99701"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"a8d068ac-46a2-49dc-b300-ba75581592fc","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 4CDB2648344F40F2EAAA0AB1E56E777E81742BE2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\r\nValue Name:\tdisableddeserverlookup (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223314","group_tree":[{"id":"V-223314","title":"SRG-APP-000207","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-223314","severity":"medium","group_title":"Open/save of dBase III / IV format files must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-223314r961086_rule","rule_id":"SV-223314r961086","rule_version":"O365-EX-000005","rule_title":"Open/save of dBase III / IV format files must be blocked.","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Microsoft Excel 2016 >> Excel Options >> Security >> Trust Center >> File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value DBaseFiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Office_365_ProPlus_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108807","V-99703"],"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"reference_identifier":"4099","uuid":"d2005eb8-061a-4672-9c2a-fbb13b343eb8","stig_uuid":"69fe962f-3c5a-4cde-adb6-08cf383783e3","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Office365_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 2F307C02E999D5A063CFEF0F96E96DF1ADFC4811\r\n~~~~~\r\n'File Block Settings 'dBase III / IV files'' is NOT Enabled: (Open/Save blocked, use open policy)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\r\nValue Name:\tDBaseFiles (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-223315"