m - System Integrity successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> System >> \"Audit System Integrity\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem >> System Integrity - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5d35cdf4-65d3-4219-9351-04d65e9c8d2e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9CB956D8B61BAD658CBE89D13CAA5C67A83EF99A\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem Integrity:\tSuccess and Failure"},{"group_id_src":"V-253337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253337","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253337","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","rule_id_src":"SV-253337r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-253337r958752","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000500","rule_title":"The Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Application >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"a68df462-bdd8-477f-aa3d-8ff1cf7a7be1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4CCEDD71C3DD2A72A8261B0BF89E7230B6C64FF3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify the maximum log file size (KB)' is NOT Enable: (Maximum Log Size (KB) of 32768 or greater) \r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\r\nValue Name:\tMaxSize (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253338","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253338","severity":"medium","group_title":"The security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.","rule_id_src":"SV-253338r1186375_rule","rule_id":"SV-253338r1186375","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000505","rule_title":"The security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Security >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of a value that will contain one week of audit records or greater.\n\nIf the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this must be documented with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this requirement is not applicable. This must be documented with the information system security officer (ISSO).\n\nThe registry configuration setting below must be set (at least) to a value equal to the size needed to contain one week's worth of audit records in the security event log. The value used below is an example that assumes a typical week’s log size of 5GB.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nNote: The following registry entry is an example; the value must equal at least one week's worth of records.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue:0x49960800 (5120000) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel. System administrators (SAs) must monitor the volume of security event audit records and increase the registry value for the log size as needed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"e265f289-76ec-48f4-8cef-b1102fb26e28","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 62657DB2F8DABFAC43B48FA786B7DD02E07DA7A6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify the maximum log file size (KB)' is NOT Enable: (Maximum Log Size (KB) of 1024000 or greater) \r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\r\nValue Name:\tMaxSize (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253339","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253339","severity":"medium","group_title":"The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","rule_id_src":"SV-253339r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-253339r958752","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000510","rule_title":"The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to send audit records directly to an audit server, this is NA. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"436050f7-6705-4acb-b4c7-c5cad0a3c7f8","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7EF80F1BBB2FFB81616C051545570DB70FC3BC2C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Specify the maximum log file size (KB)' is NOT Enable: (Maximum Log Size (KB) of 32768 or greater) \r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\r\nValue Name:\tMaxSize (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253340","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253340","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253340r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-253340r958434","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000515","rule_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The Application event log may be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"351d5eae-b689-4337-ab80-6a02acab358b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0B65B5EF56F50A08A0E3B69DD4775781B51D4045\r\n~~~~~\r\nPath:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\System32\\Winevt\\Logs\\Application.evtx\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant"},{"group_id_src":"V-253341","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253341","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253341","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253341r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-253341r958434","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000520","rule_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The Security event log may disclose sensitive information or be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"4edb9fca-d676-4661-a6ec-1a7f4ea565e9","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 750A533D09F0AF8D1D4146DFE4CBEAAAD9155DF5\r\n~~~~~\r\nPath:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\System32\\Winevt\\Logs\\Security.evtx\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant"},{"group_id_src":"V-253342","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253342","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253342","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the System event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253342r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-253342r958434","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000525","rule_title":"Windows 11 permissions for the System event log must prevent access by non-privileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx). Standard user accounts or groups must not have access. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory. They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If \"APPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES\" has Special Permissions, this would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The System event log may be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b40902b5-3eb8-41e4-9c4a-342b7a24b9c2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C6363847B15F91231F7F4AD248984DE1F0580D02\r\n~~~~~\r\nPath:\t\t\tC:\\WINDOWS\\System32\\Winevt\\Logs\\System.evtx\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant"},{"group_id_src":"V-253344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253344","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253344","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Other Policy Change Events Failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-253344r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253344r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000555","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Other Policy Change Events Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change>> \"Audit Other Policy Change Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change >> Other Policy Change Events - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Policy Change Events contains events about EFS Data Recovery Agent policy changes, changes in Windows Filtering Platform filter, status on Security policy settings updates for local Group Policy settings, Central Access Policy changes, and detailed troubleshooting events for Cryptographic Next Generation (CNG) operations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"e5b79b7e-543f-4abf-bc32-50aea2f19ba3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F56F16F326C68982724597F5F5B02BC434238E4\r\n~~~~~\r\nOther Policy Change Events:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253345","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253345","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253345","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Successes.","rule_id_src":"SV-253345r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253345r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000560","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Other Logon/Logoff Events\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Other Logon/Logoff Events - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Logon/Logoff Events determines whether Windows generates audit events for other logon or logoff events. Logon events are essential to understanding user activity and detecting potential attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"adce0850-8ca9-4357-b39e-d2a538b04d19","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CABA85C8829C709BD0D0A73E1DEEBA10C3E2E598\r\n~~~~~\r\nOther Logon/Logoff Events:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253346","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253346","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253346","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-253346r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253346r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000565","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit other Logon/Logoff Events Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Logon/Logoff >> \"Audit Other Logon/Logoff Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff >> Other Logon/Logoff Events - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other Logon/Logoff Events determines whether Windows generates audit events for other logon or logoff events. Logon events are essential to understanding user activity and detecting potential attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"9ea61876-5cc6-4d4e-ab35-17ef2a204602","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CABA85C8829C709BD0D0A73E1DEEBA10C3E2E598\r\n~~~~~\r\nOther Logon/Logoff Events:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253347","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253347","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253347","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Detailed File Share Failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-253347r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253347r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000570","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Detailed File Share Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit Detailed File Share\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nObject Access >> Detailed File Share - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Detailed File Share allows the user to audit attempts to access files and folders on a shared folder.\nThe Detailed File Share setting logs an event every time a file or folder is accessed, whereas the File Share setting only records one event for any connection established between a client and file share. Detailed File Share audit events include detailed information about the permissions or other criteria used to grant or deny access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"4457a933-d0df-473d-9b86-a50c598aca9d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3326721F7C25E3869580FCBF78A3A088DD17E606\r\n~~~~~\r\nDetailed File Share:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253348","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253348","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253348","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Successes.","rule_id_src":"SV-253348r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253348r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000575","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change >> Audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change >> MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change determines whether the operating system generates audit events when changes are made to policy rules for the Microsoft Protection Service (MPSSVC.exe).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"6f64858d-ad7e-4311-808d-6d2a792d5ab1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 492A5D5E71E4E69AB97029E631BE44CAF2515ECC\r\n~~~~~\r\nMPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253349","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253349","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253349","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-253349r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-253349r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000580","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change Failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Policy Change >> Audit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Use the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change >> MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit MPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change determines whether the operating system generates audit events when changes are made to policy rules for the Microsoft Protection Service (MPSSVC.exe).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"aea3c850-be7b-4b06-b1ce-6503b6b10d0d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 492A5D5E71E4E69AB97029E631BE44CAF2515ECC\r\n~~~~~\r\nMPSSVC Rule-Level Policy Change:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-253350","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253350","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253350","severity":"medium","group_title":"Camera access from the lock screen must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253350r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253350r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000005","rule_title":"Camera access from the lock screen must be disabled.","fix_text":"If the device does not have a camera, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> \"Prevent enabling lock screen camera\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the device does not have a camera, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenCamera\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling camera access from the lock screen could allow for unauthorized use. Requiring logon will ensure the device is only used by authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"cfc792ca-27d0-44ed-b46d-844d85cc715c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D0C7AEF32BE6D9DCFCD9CF529D88AFFF1A9AB201\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe following cameras were detected:\r\n\r\nName:\t\tIntegrated Webcam\r\nPnP Class:\tCamera\r\nStatus:\t\tOK\r\n\r\n'Prevent enabling lock screen camera' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\r\nValue Name:\tNoLockScreenCamera (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253351","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253351","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253351","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must cover or disable the built-in or attached camera when not in use.","rule_id_src":"SV-253351r1106508_rule","rule_id":"SV-253351r1106508","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000007","rule_title":"Windows 11 must cover or disable the built-in or attached camera when not in use.","fix_text":"If the camera is not disconnected or covered, the following registry entry is required.\n \nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistryPath\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\CapabilityAccessManager\\ConsentStore\\webcam\n\nValue Name: Value                                                                            Value Data: Deny","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the device or operating system does not have a camera installed, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nThis requirement is not applicable to mobile devices (smartphones and tablets), where the use of the camera is a local authorizing official (AO) decision.\n\nThis requirement is not applicable to dedicated VTC suites located in approved VTC locations that are centrally managed.\n\nFor an external camera, if there is not a method for the operator to manually disconnect camera at the end of collaborative computing sessions, this is a finding.\n\nFor a built-in camera, the camera must be protected by a camera cover (e.g. laptop camera cover slide) when not in use. If the built-in camera is not protected with a camera cover, or if the built-in\ncamera is not disabled in the bios, this is a finding.\n\nIf the camera is not disconnected or covered, the following registry entry is required:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistryPath\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\CapabilityAccessManager\\ConsentStore\\webcam\n\nValue Name: Value                                                                             Value Data: Deny\n\nIf \"Value Name\" is set to a value other than \"Deny\" and the collaborative computing device has not been authorized for use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nFailing to disconnect from collaborative computing devices (i.e. cameras) can result in subsequent compromises of organizational information. Providing easy methods to physically disconnect from such devices after a collaborative computing session helps to ensure that participants actually carry out the disconnect activity without having to go through complex and tedious procedures.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049, SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"35fa4972-0a43-4740-b7d8-280b4b538b21","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: A22F8D832760B0A8360EC3F4D2B3610053214AC7\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe following cameras were detected:\r\n\r\nName:\t\tIntegrated Webcam\r\nPnP Class:\tCamera\r\nStatus:\t\tOK\r\n\r\nRegistry is configured but Value is not 'Deny' which means camera is accessible to apps.  If this system is dedicated for VTC and in an approved VTC location that is centrally managed, mark this check as N/A.  Otherwise, confirm camera is disconnected, disabled in BIOS, covered, or has approval for use.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\CapabilityAccessManager\\ConsentStore\\webcam\r\nValue Name:\tValue\r\nValue:\t\tAllow [Expected Deny]\r\nType:\t\tREG_SZ"},{"group_id_src":"V-253352","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253352","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253352","severity":"medium","group_title":"The display of slide shows on the lock screen must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253352r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253352r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000010","rule_title":"The display of slide shows on the lock screen must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> \"Prevent enabling lock screen slide show\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel. Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"152dbae3-cb42-457a-b75b-399682b98700","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BC57140B48B81520A1A524E4A10E0B28AF2D1E0C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent enabling lock screen slide show' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\r\nValue Name:\tNoLockScreenSlideshow (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253353","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253353","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253353","severity":"medium","group_title":"IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.","rule_id_src":"SV-253353r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253353r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000020","rule_title":"IPv6 source routing must be configured to highest protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIpSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"00dc7052-a388-4e5c-941f-5e6e451696d0","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CDB8923F081C1A3ABE0EA9269A440413DCD7BB40\r\n~~~~~\r\n'MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)' is NOT Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tDisableIpSourceRouting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253354","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253354","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253354","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.","rule_id_src":"SV-253354r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253354r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000025","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5798eec9-54b6-47c8-9612-4fe5ed0e087c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AF001DE66FB574E6EF4D0A08ED02CB8EF99FEA45\r\n~~~~~\r\n'MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)' is NOT Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tDisableIPSourceRouting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253355","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253355","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253355","severity":"low","group_title":"The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.","rule_id_src":"SV-253355r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253355r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000030","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly.  When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"fa763db2-97ee-489a-bf9a-fc86cc75b10c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DB18BB882764AED3E8D1679D819A30DCAD0C84FD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tEnableICMPRedirect (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253356","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253356","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253356","severity":"low","group_title":"The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","rule_id_src":"SV-253356r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-253356r958902","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000035","rule_title":"The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack. The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the servers WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"4d7f5165-e61e-4dfd-9594-5091c297d5e3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A91659B5B5C72AE5C3157ED7EC46CACE3D1DA3AF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tNoNameReleaseOnDemand (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253357","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253357","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253357","severity":"medium","group_title":"Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253357r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253357r958518","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000037","rule_title":"Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems.\n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for built-in administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5fbdd0ed-685a-4949-9986-a44c67d119f0","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253358","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253358","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253358","severity":"medium","group_title":"WDigest Authentication must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253358r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253358r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000038","rule_title":"WDigest Authentication must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThe patch referenced in the policy title is not required for Windows 11.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name: UseLogonCredential\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS) exposing them to theft. WDigest is disabled by default in Windows 11. This setting ensures this is enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"1e71be4a-e829-43c8-8639-2706f073c4b8","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 743712A435CC16581B1DAF1608AEC76CE0DE04CF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\r\nValue Name:\tUseLogonCredential (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253359","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253359","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253359","severity":"medium","group_title":"Run as different user must be removed from context menus.","rule_id_src":"SV-253359r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253359r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000039","rule_title":"Run as different user must be removed from context menus.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Remove \"Run as Different User\" from context menus\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding.\nThe policy configures the same Value Name, Type and Value under four different registry paths.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Paths: \n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\batfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\cmdfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\exefile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\mscfile\\shell\\runasuser\\\n\nValue Name: SuppressionPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00001000 (4096)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The \"Run as different user\" selection from context menus allows the use of credentials other than the currently logged on user. Using privileged credentials in a standard user session can expose those credentials to theft. Removing this option from context menus helps prevent this from occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"aabce928-e7f0-4b8d-bf8d-6817ed576cbc","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A141C96C84C0738A2BC430EB57178CBDFE1E3E63\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Remove \"Run as Different User\" from context menus' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\batfile\\shell\\runasuser\r\nValue Name:\tSuppressionPolicy\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 4096]\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 'REG_DWORD']\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\cmdfile\\shell\\runasuser\r\nValue Name:\tSuppressionPolicy\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 4096]\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 'REG_DWORD']\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\exefile\\shell\\runasuser\r\nValue Name:\tSuppressionPolicy\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 4096]\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 'REG_DWORD']\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\mscfile\\shell\\runasuser\r\nValue Name:\tSuppressionPolicy\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 4096]\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound) [Expected 'REG_DWORD']"},{"group_id_src":"V-253360","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253360","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253360","severity":"medium","group_title":"Insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253360r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253360r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000040","rule_title":"Insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Lanman Workstation >> \"Enable insecure guest logons\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders. Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"821c3a5b-ec9f-4b49-ace7-b9a92d378a29","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 52F4C22D3B21AE91CCE2395C0BA7529CF6E9887C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable insecure guest logons' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\r\nValue Name:\tAllowInsecureGuestAuth (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253361","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253361","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253361","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet connection sharing must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253361r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253361r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000044","rule_title":"Internet connection sharing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Connections >> \"Prohibit use of Internet Connection Sharing on your DNS domain network\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name: NC_ShowSharedAccessUI\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet connection sharing makes it possible for an existing internet connection, such as through wireless, to be shared and used by other systems essentially creating a mobile hotspot. This exposes the system sharing the connection to others with potentially malicious purpose.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"dea2b2ac-69ef-4bbf-bd22-212a32aba01e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CBE62529F718ADACC22D74421645F6C3A582A1D3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prohibit use of Internet Connection Sharing on your DNS domain network' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\r\nValue Name:\tNC_ShowSharedAccessUI (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253362","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253362","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253362","severity":"medium","group_title":"Hardened UNC Paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","rule_id_src":"SV-253362r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253362r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000050","rule_title":"Hardened UNC Paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Provider >> \"Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths:\" (click the \"Show\" button to display).\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths specified in Hardened UNC paths before allowing access them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c85665d4-3b35-428c-80cb-9b704280711a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253363","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253363","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253363","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prioritize ECC Curves with longer key lengths first.","rule_id_src":"SV-253363r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-253363r971535","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000052","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prioritize ECC Curves with longer key lengths first.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> SSL Configuration Settings >> \"ECC Curve Order\" to \"Enabled\" with \"ECC Curve Order:\" including the following in the order listed:\n\nNistP384\nNistP256","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Configuration\\SSL\\00010002\\\n\nValue Name: EccCurves\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: NistP384 NistP256","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. By default Windows uses ECC curves with shorter key lengths first. Requiring ECC curves with longer key lengths to be prioritized first helps ensure more secure algorithms are used.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"30e819b0-84e4-430f-a9c8-d528e6079393","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E6785073857B173F1D0CCD9FF22ACEFA5168CBD0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'ECC Curve Order' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Configuration\\SSL\\00010002\r\nValue Name:\tEccCurves (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253364","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253364","title":"SRG-OS-000481-GPOS-00481","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253364","severity":"medium","group_title":"Simultaneous connections to the internet or a Windows domain must be limited.","rule_id_src":"SV-253364r958358_rule","rule_id":"SV-253364r958358","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000055","rule_title":"Simultaneous connections to the internet or a Windows domain must be limited.","fix_text":"The default behavior for \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" is \"Enabled\".\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Windows Connection Manager >> \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" to \"Enabled\".  Under \"Options\", set \"Minimize Policy Options\" to \"3 = Prevent Wi-Fi When on Ethernet\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior for \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" is \"Enabled\".\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: fMinimizeConnections\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Multiple network connections can provide additional attack vectors to a system and must be limited. The \"Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain\" setting prevents systems from automatically establishing multiple connections. When both wired and wireless connections are available, for example, the less preferred connection (typically wireless) will be disconnected.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"33c8c320-7ffe-410b-986c-d26b93abf093","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2CC82450F3E63BDE8C8216F1B76FAA000A3676E2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Minimize the number of simultaneous connections to the Internet or a Windows Domain' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\r\nValue Name:\tfMinimizeConnections (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253365","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253365","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253365","severity":"medium","group_title":"Connections to non-domain networks when connected to a domain authenticated network must be blocked.","rule_id_src":"SV-253365r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253365r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000060","rule_title":"Connections to non-domain networks when connected to a domain authenticated network must be blocked.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Windows Connection Manager >> \"Prohibit connection to non-domain networks when connected to domain authenticated network\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: fBlockNonDomain\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Multiple network connections can provide additional attack vectors to a system and must be limited. When connected to a domain, communication must go through the domain connection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d6b32429-885e-4363-82aa-818c18bafd7d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EEF173BDA96DA372539936EAE0858EFF4C2F048B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prohibit connection to non-domain networks when connected to domain authenticated network' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WcmSvc\\GroupPolicy\r\nValue Name:\tfBlockNonDomain (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253366","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253366","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253366","severity":"medium","group_title":"Wi-Fi Sense must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253366r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253366r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000065","rule_title":"Wi-Fi Sense must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> WLAN Service >> WLAN Settings>> \"Allow Windows to automatically connect to suggested open hotspots, to networks shared by contacts, and to hotspots offering paid services\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\WcmSvc\\wifinetworkmanager\\config\\\n\nValue Name: AutoConnectAllowedOEM\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Wi-Fi Sense automatically connects the system to known hotspots and networks that contacts have shared. It also allows the sharing of the system's known networks to contacts. Automatically connecting to hotspots and shared networks can expose a system to unsecured or potentially malicious systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"76aa6873-cf7e-45a8-a193-00ea6b478795","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CEF1E0C5DE191B7CB3BAFA2042C69B87019E19A3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Windows to automatically connect to suggested open hotspots, to networks shared by contacts, and to hotspots offering paid services' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\WcmSvc\\wifinetworkmanager\\config\r\nValue Name:\tAutoConnectAllowedOEM (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253367","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253367","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253367","severity":"medium","group_title":"Command line data must be included in process creation events.","rule_id_src":"SV-253367r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-253367r958422","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000066","rule_title":"Command line data must be included in process creation events.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Audit Process Creation >> \"Include command line in process creation events\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"7ccc4043-e987-4a7a-858b-18b49a789aa4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D34551E45441B6C0562443AA6B7C078153202070\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Include command line in process creation events' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\r\nValue Name:\tProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253368","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253368","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253368","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.","rule_id_src":"SV-253368r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253368r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000068","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host. Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of non-exportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials. Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"bbe333b0-a63e-40dd-a24c-820571cf1c5d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8644BF5C398A72DC5A6655A7765EB97293B2ED5D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\r\nValue Name:\tAllowProtectedCreds (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253369","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253369","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253369","severity":"medium","group_title":"Virtualization-based Security must be enabled on Windows 11 with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","rule_id_src":"SV-253369r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253369r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000070","rule_title":"Virtualization-based Security must be enabled on Windows 11 with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","fix_text":"Virtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On virtualization-based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected for \"Select Platform Security Level:\".\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link.\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard-requirements","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm virtualization-based Security is enabled and running with Secure Boot or Secure Boot and DMA Protection.\n\nFor those devices that support virtualization-based security (VBS) features, including Credential Guard or protection of code integrity, this must be enabled. If the system meets the hardware and firmware dependencies for enabling VBS but it is not enabled, this is a CAT III finding.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard virtualization-based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is finding.\n\nIf \"Device Guard Required Security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values. However due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1 (Secure Boot only) or 3 (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard-requirements","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization-based Security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features, Credential Guard and virtualization-based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level with DMA protection providing additional memory protection. DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"36a66029-cd65-418b-9a20-b5eeb148ec27","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E33AAE86A2F6CAE2DA7C344622773DF635E37CAC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequiredSecurityProperties:\t\t0\r\nVirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus:\t2"},{"group_id_src":"V-253370","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253370","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253370","severity":"high","group_title":"Credential Guard must be running on Windows 11 domain-joined systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253370r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253370r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000075","rule_title":"Credential Guard must be running on Windows 11 domain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Virtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nFor VDIs with persistent desktops, this may be downgraded to a CAT II only where administrators have specific tokens for the VDI. Administrator accounts on virtual desktops must only be used on systems in the VDI; they may not have administrative privileges on any other systems such as servers and physical workstations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On virtualization-based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" selected for \"Credential Guard Configuration:\".\n\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/access-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm Credential Guard is running on domain-joined systems.\n\nFor those devices that support Credential Guard, this feature must be enabled. Organizations need to take the appropriate action to acquire and implement compatible hardware with Credential Guard enabled.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\nEnter the following:\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"1\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\nIf \"virtualization-based Services Running\" does not list \"Credential Guard\", this is finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: LsaCfgFlags\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. This authentication information, which was stored in the Local Security Authority (LSA) in previous versions of Windows, is isolated from the rest of operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"7421562a-73af-4971-84d7-a9f120886ae3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253371","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253371","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253371","severity":"medium","group_title":"Virtualization-based protection of code integrity must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253371r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253371r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000080","rule_title":"Virtualization-based protection of code integrity must be enabled.","fix_text":"Virtualization-based security currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On virtualization-based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" or \"Enabled without lock\" selected for \"virtualization-based Protection of Code Integrity:\".\n\n\"Enabled with UEFI lock\" is preferred as more secure, however it cannot be turned off remotely through a group policy change if there is an issue.\n\n\"Enabled without lock\" will allow this to be turned off remotely while testing for issues.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Confirm virtualization-based protection of code integrity.\n\nFor those devices that support the virtualization-based security (VBS) feature for protection of code integrity, this must be enabled. If the system meets the hardware, firmware and compatible device driver dependencies for enabling virtualization-based protection of code integrity but it is not enabled, this is a CAT II finding.\n\nVirtualization-based security currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\nEnter the following:\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"2\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\nIf \"Virtualization-based Security Services Running\" does not list \"Hypervisor enforced Code Integrity\", this is finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: HypervisorEnforcedCodeIntegrity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock), or 0x00000002 (2) (Enabled without lock)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization-based protection of code integrity enforces kernel mode memory protections as well as protecting Code Integrity validation paths. This isolates the processes from the rest of the operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"26791a9d-25f4-4e3b-957d-a78268d56f42","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5F4E099EF2C954B30030F30EB5362FBC4A5CABBE\r\n~~~~~\r\nSecurityServicesRunning:\t\t2"},{"group_id_src":"V-253372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253372","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253372","severity":"medium","group_title":"Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers.","rule_id_src":"SV-253372r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253372r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000085","rule_title":"Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers.","fix_text":"Ensure that Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy is set to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Early Launch Antimalware >> \"Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy\" to \"Enabled with \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy is to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"7\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1, 3, or 8 \n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"Bad\" and would be a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy is to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\"). By being launched first by the kernel, ELAM ( Early Launch Antimalware) is ensured to be launched before any third-party software, and is therefore able to detect malware in the boot process and prevent it from initializing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"85ed5c75-9136-4a4e-9925-6fdedfa2f8a6","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2524A6D4DF4A8C6C7291A18E399C03580AFD516E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy' is NOT Enabled: (Good, unknown and bad but critical)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\r\nValue Name:\tDriverLoadPolicy (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253373","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253373","severity":"medium","group_title":"Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253373r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253373r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000090","rule_title":"Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Group Policy >> \"Configure registry policy processing\" to \"Enabled\" and select the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures that the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"132addee-1d4a-4044-914c-c0fb2d1b2664","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 24B16AE36C1F57C99A6A51CC0B050418F72596D6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure registry policy processing' is NOT Enabled: (Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\r\nValue Name:\tNoGPOListChanges (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253374","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253374","severity":"medium","group_title":"Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.","rule_id_src":"SV-253374r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253374r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000100","rule_title":"Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system. This setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"23e64f94-7ec0-483a-b28e-198ab98710ec","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8AE17489E1547C1CACEA372DEFE64DCEF8A61368\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\r\nValue Name:\tDisableWebPnPDownload (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253375","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253375","severity":"medium","group_title":"Web publishing and online ordering wizards must be prevented from downloading a list of providers.","rule_id_src":"SV-253375r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253375r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000105","rule_title":"Web publishing and online ordering wizards must be prevented from downloading a list of providers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off Internet download for Web publishing and online ordering wizards\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoWebServices\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system. This setting prevents Windows from downloading a list of providers for the Web publishing and online ordering wizards.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0ba3d383-4f02-45eb-98fa-8cad43b5174f","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 32E1ACC166FCEBBA097D775F0CF21D61FE8066D3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Internet download for Web publishing and online ordering wizards' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoWebServices (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253376","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253376","severity":"medium","group_title":"Printing over HTTP must be prevented.","rule_id_src":"SV-253376r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253376r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000110","rule_title":"Printing over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off printing over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system. This setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"bd9a0963-1d10-48c6-a72f-89325b1278b9","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 704D15F5B1FFEE43E63D03F70F3724FDF83662BE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off printing over HTTP' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\r\nValue Name:\tDisableHTTPPrinting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253377","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253377","severity":"medium","group_title":"Systems must at least attempt device authentication using certificates.","rule_id_src":"SV-253377r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253377r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000115","rule_title":"Systems must at least attempt device authentication using certificates.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nThe default behavior for \"Support device authentication using certificate\" is \"Automatic\".\n\nTo correct this, configured the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Kerberos >> \"Support device authentication using certificate\" to \"Not Configured or \"Enabled\" with either option selected in \"Device authentication behavior using certificate:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nThe default behavior for \"Support device authentication using certificate\" is \"Automatic\".\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DevicePKInitEnabled\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using certificates to authenticate devices to the domain provides increased security over passwords. By default systems will attempt to authenticate using certificates and fall back to passwords if the domain controller does not support certificates for devices. This may also be configured to always use certificates for device authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c41b3c5b-d48c-42ce-9435-d5eb1c2c3879","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253378","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253378","severity":"medium","group_title":"The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","rule_id_src":"SV-253378r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253378r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000120","rule_title":"The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> \"Do not display network selection UI\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing into Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2a0e80ad-07e2-4baf-bdf6-8cba2a7e5ea5","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E719F3C93F745C4451A933D092B0A7B23B66A7F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not display network selection UI' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\r\nValue Name:\tDontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253379","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253379","severity":"medium","group_title":"Local users on domain-joined computers must not be enumerated.","rule_id_src":"SV-253379r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253379r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000130","rule_title":"Local users on domain-joined computers must not be enumerated.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> \"Enumerate local users on domain-joined computers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateLocalUsers\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The username is one part of logon credentials that could be used to gain access to a system. Preventing the enumeration of users limits this information to authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5cfa527d-8d8a-4544-92ab-477acbdd0c1a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253380","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253380","severity":"medium","group_title":"Users must be prompted for a password on resume from sleep (on battery).","rule_id_src":"SV-253380r1051049_rule","rule_id":"SV-253380r1051049","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000145","rule_title":"Users must be prompted for a password on resume from sleep (on battery).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> \"Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: DCSettingIndex\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures the user is prompted for a password on resume from sleep (on battery).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"632995c5-aa63-4fe4-b17a-bcbdd6a86d25","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1919220CEE0E2F3A71AD61AC498978D6C1387EE1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery)' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\r\nValue Name:\tDCSettingIndex (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253381","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253381","severity":"medium","group_title":"The user must be prompted for a password on resume from sleep (plugged in).","rule_id_src":"SV-253381r1051050_rule","rule_id":"SV-253381r1051050","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000150","rule_title":"The user must be prompted for a password on resume from sleep (plugged in).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> \"Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: ACSettingIndex\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures the user is prompted for a password on resume from sleep (plugged in).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5bd64edb-ab88-4f11-afe8-bebeda83b246","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A48B93F0B553229F015D55968D2354F42F622000\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in)' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\r\nValue Name:\tACSettingIndex (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253382","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253382","severity":"high","group_title":"Solicited Remote Assistance must not be allowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253382r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-253382r1137695","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000155","rule_title":"Solicited Remote Assistance must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Remote Assistance >> \"Configure Solicited Remote Assistance\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fAllowToGetHelp\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote assistance allows another user to view or take control of the local session of a user. Solicited assistance is help that is specifically requested by the local user. This may allow unauthorized parties access to the resources on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2145f9f2-14eb-4440-bbca-ed52a91bb1a2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D254853D58AF9A2152E7FD1ACCF521C6CAAAD1F7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Solicited Remote Assistance' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tfAllowToGetHelp (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253383","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253383","severity":"medium","group_title":"Unauthenticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.","rule_id_src":"SV-253383r971545_rule","rule_id":"SV-253383r971545","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000165","rule_title":"Unauthenticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Remote Procedure Call >> \"Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Authenticated\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteClients\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring RPC to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server will prevent anonymous connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ca8b67ab-82f7-4387-a02c-181ecdf4eb88","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 109F9ED2FB9C78D36D3CCDE9158A3A523E89E688\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients' is NOT Enabled: (Authenticated)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\r\nValue Name:\tRestrictRemoteClients (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253384","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253384","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253384","severity":"low","group_title":"The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253384r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253384r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000170","rule_title":"The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Runtime >> \"Allow Microsoft accounts to be optional\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MSAOptional\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of credentials and the system must be maintained within the enterprise. Enabling this setting allows enterprise credentials to be used with modern style apps that support this, instead of Microsoft accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"a64d26ee-73d1-4770-8668-7d60e646d0c2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F79980E640F4939CFA82481D89F993012DF8C8E7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Microsoft accounts to be optional' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tMSAOptional (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253385","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253385","severity":"low","group_title":"The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","rule_id_src":"SV-253385r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253385r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000175","rule_title":"The Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Application Compatibility >> \"Turn off Inventory Collector\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system. This setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"3e24e8d5-a61b-4005-9857-41b1b781b9c6","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D5A8E0215A30F122F9A6F1D42E52F03FAA2CCF96\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Inventory Collector' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\r\nValue Name:\tDisableInventory (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253386","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253386","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253386","severity":"high","group_title":"Autoplay must be turned off for non-volume devices.","rule_id_src":"SV-253386r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-253386r958804","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000180","rule_title":"Autoplay must be turned off for non-volume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Disallow Autoplay for non-volume devices\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as media is inserted in the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. This setting will disable autoplay for non-volume devices (such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ed575307-d332-4a2b-95c8-96cecb9f396b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5768822E3B48968199193C5E8994DD5A199000DF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disallow Autoplay for non-volume devices' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoAutoplayfornonVolume (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253387","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253387","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253387","severity":"high","group_title":"The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.","rule_id_src":"SV-253387r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-253387r958804","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000185","rule_title":"The default autorun behavior must be configured to prevent autorun commands.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Set the default behavior for AutoRun\" to \"Enabled:Do not execute any autorun commands\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutorun\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autorun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Configuring this setting prevents autorun commands from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"42f0a8a9-a563-4507-91e5-d3178763a518","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B588F3951992F678CCEE393E2A80C4BADFB5766\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Set the default behavior for AutoRun' is NOT Enabled: (Do not execute any autorun commands)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoAutorun (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253388","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253388","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253388","severity":"high","group_title":"Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.","rule_id_src":"SV-253388r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-253388r958804","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000190","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled for all drives.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> \"Turn off AutoPlay\" to \"Enabled:All Drives\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)\n\nNote: If the value for NoDriveTypeAutorun is entered manually, it must be entered as \"ff\" when Hexadecimal is selected, or \"255\" with Decimal selected. Using the policy value specified in the Fix section will enter it correctly.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing autoplay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Autoplay begins reading from a drive as soon as media is inserted in the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. By default, autoplay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives. If this policy is enabled, autoplay can be disabled on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"a0a8b942-516e-4abe-9fd8-2d2532d9846b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BFBBB841692E2DE52E34244F1AB53BCD5C8B5C4C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off AutoPlay' is NOT Enabled: (All Drives)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoDriveTypeAutoRun\r\nValue:\t\t0x0000009e (158) [Expected ff]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253389","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253389","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253389","severity":"medium","group_title":"Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Windows 11.","rule_id_src":"SV-253389r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253389r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000195","rule_title":"Enhanced anti-spoofing for facial recognition must be enabled on Windows 11.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Biometrics >> Facial Features >> \"Configure enhanced anti-spoofing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Biometrics\\FacialFeatures\\\n\nValue Name: EnhancedAntiSpoofing\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enhanced anti-spoofing provides additional protections when using facial recognition with devices that support it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"18e05321-eaac-4a7f-bf1c-2e5dadd8c510","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A7A842BE6B04F6877F41FAC18E335736F214F41A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Use enhanced anti-spoofing when available' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Biometrics\\FacialFeatures\r\nValue Name:\tEnhancedAntiSpoofing (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253390","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253390","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253390","severity":"low","group_title":"Microsoft consumer experiences must be turned off.","rule_id_src":"SV-253390r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253390r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000197","rule_title":"Microsoft consumer experiences must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Turn off Microsoft consumer experiences\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWindowsConsumerFeatures\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft consumer experiences provides suggestions and notifications to users, which may include the installation of Windows Store apps. Organizations may control the execution of applications through other means such as allowlisting. Turning off Microsoft consumer experiences will help prevent the unwanted installation of suggested applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b05009bd-9c68-4ee8-843f-492b671cac3b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 42AD257D1DCB4C6454D25837E20DE688553AE51E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Microsoft consumer experiences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\r\nValue Name:\tDisableWindowsConsumerFeatures (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253391","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253391","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253391","severity":"medium","group_title":"Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","rule_id_src":"SV-253391r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253391r958518","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000200","rule_title":"Administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Credential User Interface >> \"Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user. This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"54b7cedd-56fc-4ed0-a5c8-d9df98811f93","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A3E4F2CDFAB20DF7125577CDE9DA137D617AA80A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\r\nValue Name:\tEnumerateAdministrators (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253392","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253392","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253392","severity":"medium","group_title":"Enhanced diagnostic data must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.","rule_id_src":"SV-253392r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253392r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000204","rule_title":"Enhanced diagnostic data must be limited to the minimum required to support Windows Analytics.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Limit optional diagnostic data for Windows Analytics\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enable Desktop Analytics collection\" selected in \"Options:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If \"Enhanced\" level is enabled for telemetry, this must be configured. If \"Security\" or \"Basic\" are configured, this is NA. (See WN11-CC-000205).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: LimitEnhancedDiagnosticDataWindowsAnalytics\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Enhanced\" level for telemetry includes additional information beyond \"Security\" and \"Basic\" on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c2a7c325-960a-41b1-82d2-ab772c867f3f","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E13FA5E265EACD8A2ABA50AE5E7498F4CE4E324D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Limit Enhanced diagnostic data to the minimum required by Windows Analytics' is NOT Enabled: (Enable Windows Analytics collection)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\r\nValue Name:\tLimitEnhancedDiagnosticDataWindowsAnalytics (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253393","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253393","title":"SRG-OS-000205-GPOS-00083","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253393","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.","rule_id_src":"SV-253393r958564_rule","rule_id":"SV-253393r958564","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000205","rule_title":"Windows Telemetry must not be configured to Full.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Builds >> \"Allow Diagnostic Data\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Send required diagnostic data\" selected in \"Options:\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (Security)\n0x00000001 (1) (Basic)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Security\" option for Telemetry configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender and telemetry client settings. \"Basic\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services. \"Enhanced\" includes additional information on how Windows and apps are used and advanced reliability data. Windows Analytics can use a \"limited enhanced\" level to provide information such as health data for devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"98b613fc-3266-4c29-a974-2298f12a9007","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EB37E2E3C4752440D7AD2B4C6D6C5F52A49C6328\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Telemetry' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\r\nValue Name:\tAllowTelemetry (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253394","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253394","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253394","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","rule_id_src":"SV-253394r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253394r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000206","rule_title":"Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> \"Download Mode\" to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\nBypass (100)\nGroup (2)\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nSimple (99)\n\n.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n0x00000064 (100) - Bypass mode, Delivery Optimization not used (Bypass)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.\n\nStandalone systems (configured in Settings):\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\DeliveryOptimization\\Config\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - Off\n0x00000001 (1) - LAN","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows 11 allows Windows Update to obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the Internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process, however to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"f8ecb055-c12b-456d-8774-ef8f1908ee45","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 690ADD6C852D4C6C47F4431E13651E188F62657D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Download Mode' is NOT Enabled: (Any option except 'Internet')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\r\nValue Name:\tDODownloadMode (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253395","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253395","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253395","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Microsoft Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253395r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253395r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000210","rule_title":"The Microsoft Defender SmartScreen for Explorer must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected. \n\nWindows 11 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Explorer.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems, for other systems this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nAnd\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ShellSmartScreenLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: Block","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will warn or prevent users from running potentially malicious programs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2b0fc8b7-426f-4e83-98ff-e2ec59b3280a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7ECCA11981ADD5D6767F8EE189AE27413AF69E14\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen' is NOT Enabled: (Warn and prevent bypass)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\r\nValue Name:\tEnableSmartScreen (Not found)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\r\nValue Name:\tShellSmartScreenLevel (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253396","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253396","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253396","severity":"medium","group_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253396r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-253396r958928","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000215","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) provides additional protection by performing checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running. This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ca4cef54-d3b8-40da-b8fb-c9d8757c5e3a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B4B6945D3FB691AA9D0314536FEAB5D126FFE60E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoDataExecutionPrevention (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253397","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253397","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253397","severity":"low","group_title":"File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253397r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-253397r958902","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000220","rule_title":"File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt. Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"8f9b21d2-bf9c-4294-86f0-d8a90a321ff4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 43BDC5AD85EF066EFC53ABCBEABF0CA16E17776A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off heap termination on corruption' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tNoHeapTerminationOnCorruption (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253398","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253398","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253398","severity":"medium","group_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","rule_id_src":"SV-253398r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253398r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000225","rule_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for file explorer.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will limit the set of folders applications can open when run in protected mode. Restricting files an application can open, to a limited set of folders, increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"44079e5a-4101-48c5-a939-93fca070ca71","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FC03998619B1ED8F2068C047328AB5C357967269\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off shell protocol protected mode' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\r\nValue Name:\tPreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253399","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253399","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253399","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.","rule_id_src":"SV-253399r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253399r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000252","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to disable Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting >> \"Enables or disables Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA for Windows 11 LTSC. \n                \nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\GameDVR\\\n\nValue Name: AllowGameDVR\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting is intended for use with games; however, it could potentially record screen shots of other applications and expose sensitive data. Disabling the feature will prevent this from occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"7b2cde6e-c4cc-46bf-b0c1-d7209a8ea29e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9635E00238FC65BCD9336E2EC3E899F4057BFA1F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enables or disables Windows Game Recording and Broadcasting' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\GameDVR\r\nValue Name:\tAllowGameDVR (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253400","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253400","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253400","severity":"medium","group_title":"The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253400r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253400r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000255","rule_title":"The use of a hardware security device with Windows Hello for Business must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Hello for Business >> \"Use a hardware security device\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Virtual desktop implementations currently may not support the use of TPMs. For virtual desktop implementations where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecurityDevice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) to store keys for Windows Hello for Business provides additional security. Keys stored in the TPM may only be used on that system while keys stored using software are more susceptible to compromise and could be used on other systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0ee797e5-88d9-4787-99ac-7753c7dc2773","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F012CFFC57A351E464AEFAC393053F18C23EFEA3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Use a hardware security device' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\r\nValue Name:\tRequireSecurityDevice (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253401","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253401","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253401","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.","rule_id_src":"SV-253401r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253401r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to require a minimum pin length of six characters or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> PIN Complexity >> \"Minimum PIN length\" to \"6\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\PINComplexity\\\n\nValue Name: MinimumPINLength\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 6 (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows allows the use of PINs as well as biometrics for authentication without sending a password to a network or website where it could be compromised. Longer minimum PIN lengths increase the available combinations an attacker would have to attempt. Shorter minimum length significantly reduces the strength.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0237d1c3-e147-4368-a2d7-8b86595e9548","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 533906598BCCB5A8FF1396A14616480ECFD72C78\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Minimum PIN length' is NOT Enabled: (6 or greater)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\PassportForWork\\PINComplexity\r\nValue Name:\tMinimumPINLength (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253402","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253402","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253402","severity":"medium","group_title":"Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.","rule_id_src":"SV-253402r1051051_rule","rule_id":"SV-253402r1051051","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000270","rule_title":"Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Connection Client >> \"Do not allow passwords to be saved\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"13b60aff-a8e4-403d-b90b-763e9908ed6c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F12E5255A6ECF54634FF9201454053FE7B245F39\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not allow passwords to be saved' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tDisablePasswordSaving (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253403","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253403","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253403","severity":"medium","group_title":"Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253403r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-253403r1137695","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000275","rule_title":"Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Device and Resource Redirection >> \"Do not allow drive redirection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers to Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d2f3fa3f-2d4f-441e-9d38-e0e95511a8ea","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CE2A210B8EAB2C63AB3448E5FC13E0218F40B824\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not allow drive redirection' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tfDisableCdm (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253404","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253404","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253404","severity":"medium","group_title":"Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","rule_id_src":"SV-253404r1051052_rule","rule_id":"SV-253404r1051052","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000280","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Always prompt for password upon connection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"43a51d31-ed1f-41ba-9530-0e2038aa3c87","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 544CB6E70BA31F9BEC887E118620C2D4F07CDD70\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Always prompt for password upon connection' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tfPromptForPassword (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253405","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253405","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253405","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","rule_id_src":"SV-253405r991554_rule","rule_id":"SV-253405r991554","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000285","rule_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security \"Require secure RPC communication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man in the middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man in the middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c5b85c6b-6473-4080-950c-de8c42a316c2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 284ABFB9CD752DC4A9A71D87A2CC9F2CAEF254AC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Require secure RPC communication' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tfEncryptRPCTraffic (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253406","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253406","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253406","severity":"medium","group_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","rule_id_src":"SV-253406r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-253406r958408","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000290","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> \"Set client connection encryption level\" to \"Enabled\" and \"High Level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000068"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5e202e40-cbb4-4f94-ab32-5d8350d241ff","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ADF92DA6D86CB21B0CEAAC7AFFC42EE7B9206034\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Set client connection encryption level' is NOT Enabled: (High Level)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\r\nValue Name:\tMinEncryptionLevel (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253407","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253407","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253407","severity":"medium","group_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","rule_id_src":"SV-253407r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253407r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000295","rule_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure. This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"302cac9c-5381-4f56-86a7-e4dabbd4c19f","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 97DCB04894129BD699894F1185542674E9C5F896\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent downloading of enclosures' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\r\nValue Name:\tDisableEnclosureDownload (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253408","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253408","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253408","severity":"medium","group_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.","rule_id_src":"SV-253408r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253408r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000300","rule_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must not be used.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"6e303114-beb2-4b24-a767-703419a24ab4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CAFDB6EFEF3AE827760FF9CDBD416D01E01EB814\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\r\nValue Name:\tAllowBasicAuthInClear (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253409","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253409","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253409","severity":"medium","group_title":"Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.","rule_id_src":"SV-253409r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253409r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000305","rule_title":"Indexing of encrypted files must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Search >> \"Allow indexing of encrypted files\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data. This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"3af3e74b-ebb5-461f-b48e-6b62137152f3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8727851B54D90F959D62E2C4E094D5E42025C6F1\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow indexing of encrypted files' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\r\nValue Name:\tAllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253410","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253410","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253410","severity":"medium","group_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","rule_id_src":"SV-253410r1051053_rule","rule_id":"SV-253410r1051053","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000310","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Allow user control over installs\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001812","CCI-003980"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"68a37c2f-48ce-4238-a308-ca3c47f918eb","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E52BF348859F7B2E6CF3C751FC5B69AF5598BDA3\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow user control over installs' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\r\nValue Name:\tEnableUserControl (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253411","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253411","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253411","severity":"high","group_title":"The Windows Installer feature \"Always install with elevated privileges\" must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253411r1051054_rule","rule_id":"SV-253411r1051054","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000315","rule_title":"The Windows Installer feature \"Always install with elevated privileges\" must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001812","CCI-003980"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"fd95603f-b5bc-4f02-b86e-afefed4dc1d7","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5A4B8AC2893F312F9722793A8D5C2DD8223AEB5E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Always install with elevated privileges' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\r\nValue Name:\tAlwaysInstallElevated (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253412","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253412","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253412","severity":"medium","group_title":"Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","rule_id_src":"SV-253412r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253412r991589","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000320","rule_title":"Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0 (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system. Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"96bb2d8b-34e6-42cd-8e10-7e70421e0a26","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C47CF55372BD83C1DC67A83A7151FAF09F7DCBEB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\r\nValue Name:\tSafeForScripting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253413","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253413","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253413","severity":"medium","group_title":"Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253413r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-253413r991591","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000325","rule_title":"Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> \"Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart. Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b3676e5f-1135-4b48-b5aa-1bd93bf94606","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 79C064E3908A24801297557ED1526B015BF07C96\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tDisableAutomaticRestartSignOn (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253414","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253414","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253414","severity":"medium","group_title":"PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 11.","rule_id_src":"SV-253414r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-253414r958422","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000326","rule_title":"PowerShell script block logging must be enabled on Windows 11.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"39b6622b-e96a-4697-b906-1f54b73efbec","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CDEED62267EBEC17921FCC8899D9C839AD57FE4C\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\r\nValue Name:\tEnableScriptBlockLogging (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253415","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253415","title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253415","severity":"medium","group_title":"PowerShell Transcription must be enabled on Windows 11.","rule_id_src":"SV-253415r958420_rule","rule_id":"SV-253415r958420","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000327","rule_title":"PowerShell Transcription must be enabled on Windows 11.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Transcription\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSpecify the Transcript output directory to point to a Central Log Server or another secure location to prevent user access.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\\n\nValue Name: EnableTranscripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell Transcription will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000134"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"bf7b4c2b-ae37-49ef-a633-d4e65e54a00a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BFCBE245B55157F88FB342AB17B8DE1D86C7F462\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on PowerShell Transcription' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\r\nValue Name:\tEnableTranscripting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253416","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253416","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253416","severity":"high","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","rule_id_src":"SV-253416r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-253416r958510","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000330","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c882d803-cdb3-40a8-97a8-480a1878178a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6E5A9265FB9A03E63264BB083443E97DCB75B978\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Basic authentication' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\r\nValue Name:\tAllowBasic (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253417","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253417","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253417","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","rule_id_src":"SV-253417r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-253417r958848","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000335","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"f46553c6-62a9-4dcc-aa01-9302e7c2156e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6CA1B2BE7DF2BC99E6C2E4FD742AB2010CB08293\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow unencrypted traffic' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\r\nValue Name:\tAllowUnencryptedTraffic (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253418","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253418","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253418","severity":"high","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","rule_id_src":"SV-253418r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-253418r958510","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000345","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow Basic authentication\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection. This would only be allowed temporarily for implementation as documented and approved. \n....\nAllowing Basic authentication to be used for the sole creation of Office 365 DoD tenants.\n....\nA documented mechanism and or script that can disable Basic authentication once administration completes. \n....\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administration.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"a16898cb-0925-4072-8ad1-7b56a2a97767","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0253A2570A5EBAE71494A5BFD3F7CDDC335C563F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Basic authentication' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\r\nValue Name:\tAllowBasic (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253419","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253419","title":"SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253419","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","rule_id_src":"SV-253419r958850_rule","rule_id":"SV-253419r958850","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000350","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Allow unencrypted traffic\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"355cd024-426e-447a-9273-655aba6aa409","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: ACBB05F87E930A92E87909D327E7634B612CA596\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow unencrypted traffic' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\r\nValue Name:\tAllowUnencryptedTraffic (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253420","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253420","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253420","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","rule_id_src":"SV-253420r1051055_rule","rule_id":"SV-253420r1051055","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000355","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> \"Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access. Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"9e746a87-8657-476a-881d-27f2dff79921","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DDF50D8E6466E7F995B06ED2BF3D88FC4A553351\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\r\nValue Name:\tDisableRunAs (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253421","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253421","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253421","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","rule_id_src":"SV-253421r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-253421r958510","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000360","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> \"Disallow Digest authentication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowDigest\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Digest authentication is not as strong as other options and may be subject to man-in-the-middle attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"6e69a16e-9a94-4661-aee6-cec6bf27ad5d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 65F8B0DC58C057B99013337651E4397F2896742A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disallow Digest authentication' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\r\nValue Name:\tAllowDigest (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253422","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253422","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253422","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.","rule_id_src":"SV-253422r958400_rule","rule_id":"SV-253422r958400","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000365","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prevent Windows apps from being activated by voice while the system is locked.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice while the system is locked\" to \"Enabled\" with Default for all Apps: set to Force Deny. \n\nThe requirement is NA if the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> App Privacy >> \"Let Windows apps activate with voice\" is configured to \"Enabled\" with Default for all Apps: set to Force Deny.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The setting is NA when the \"Allow voice activation\" policy is configured to disallow applications to be activated with voice for all users.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoiceAboveLock\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nIf the following registry value exists and is configured as specified, requirement is NA: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\\\n\nValue Name: LetAppsActivateWithVoice\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing Windows apps to be activated by voice from the lock screen could allow for unauthorized use. Requiring logon will ensure the apps are only used by authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000056"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"34112b69-b8d8-40e4-bab7-a4a8edd49271","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 942C773B8F421D719CCA817553463E4A9D08839E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Let Windows apps activate with voice' is NOT configured to 'Enabled' with 'Default for all Apps:' set to 'Force Deny'.\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\r\nValue Name:\t(NotFound)\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\n'Let Windows apps activate with voice while the system is locked' is NOT configured to 'Enabled' with 'Default for all Apps:' set to 'Force Deny'.\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppPrivacy\r\nValue Name:\t(NotFound)\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253423","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253423","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253423","severity":"medium","group_title":"The convenience PIN for Windows 11 must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253423r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253423r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000370","rule_title":"The convenience PIN for Windows 11 must be disabled.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Set \"Turn on convenience PIN sign-in\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\n\nValue Name: AllowDomainPINLogon\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy controls whether a domain user can sign in using a convenience PIN to prevent enabling (Password Stuffer).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b9c5a384-9bfb-42be-9d5e-335ec7fe46a2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CCDA2EDFB36A6126B30947C0C3BDCE60DC3A2CF2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn on convenience PIN sign-in' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\r\nValue Name:\tAllowDomainPINLogon (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253424","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253424","title":"SRG-OS-000031-GPOS-00012","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253424","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Ink Workspace must be configured to disallow access above the lock.","rule_id_src":"SV-253424r958404_rule","rule_id":"SV-253424r958404","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000385","rule_title":"Windows Ink Workspace must be configured to disallow access above the lock.","fix_text":"Disable the convenience PIN sign-in. \n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Ink Workspace >> Set \"Allow Windows Ink Workspace\" to \"Enabled and set Options \"On, but disallow access above lock\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsInkWorkspace\n\nValue Name: AllowWindowsInkWorkspace\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue data: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This action secures Windows Ink, which contains applications and features oriented toward pen computing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000060"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"81028169-7209-48fb-a122-f8f25f86feca","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C9D49E0EE8B266EDF9A1F0274F067ED60436C2FC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow Windows Ink Workspace' is NOT Enabled: (On, but disallow access above lock)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsInkWorkspace\r\nValue Name:\tAllowWindowsInkWorkspace (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253425","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253425","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253425","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prevent users from receiving suggestions for third-party or additional applications.","rule_id_src":"SV-253425r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253425r958478","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to prevent users from receiving suggestions for third-party or additional applications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates. >> Windows Components >> Cloud Content >> \"Do not suggest third-party content in Windows spotlight\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\\\n\nValue Name: DisableThirdPartySuggestions\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows spotlight features may suggest apps and content from third-party software publishers in addition to Microsoft apps and content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"59468d2b-4258-478e-8293-f4b68bb8e9f1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 2406D71EEB9217153668BC41A090BCB490671323\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not suggest third-party content in Windows spotlight' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CloudContent\r\nValue Name:\tDisableThirdPartySuggestions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253426","title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00216","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253426","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253426r991580_rule","rule_id":"SV-253426r991580","rule_version":"WN11-EP-000310","rule_title":"Windows 11 Kernel (Direct Memory Access) DMA Protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Kernel DMA Protection >> \"Enumeration policy for external devices incompatible with Kernel DMA Protection\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enumeration Policy\" set to \"Block All\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Kernel DMA Protection\n\nValue Name: DeviceEnumerationPolicy\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Kernel DMA Protection to protect PCs against drive-by Direct Memory Access (DMA) attacks using PCI hot plug devices connected to Thunderbolt 3 ports. Drive-by DMA attacks can lead to disclosure of sensitive information residing on a PC, or even injection of malware that allows attackers to bypass the lock screen or control PCs remotely.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"35ff8d76-9138-4578-a43c-4cf79e66096d","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B0BD59A69889E66199FB8BEF70114252AEBCFF07\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enumeration policy for external devices incompatible with Kernel DMA Protection' is NOT Enabled: (Block All)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Kernel DMA Protection\r\nValue Name:\tDeviceEnumerationPolicy (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253427","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253427","severity":"medium","group_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","rule_id_src":"SV-253427r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-253427r958448","rule_version":"WN11-PK-000005","rule_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates.\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5                                               \nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Root CA certificates are installed as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nThe certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6 OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nNotAfter: 1/24/2053\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates.\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041\n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nValid to: Friday, January 24, 2053\n","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root Certificate Authorities (CAs). The DoD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d755502c-c18d-43e2-a4c0-861d73a423e8","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F7A45B0C5104B6C14E089329546AAB749C65687E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\tD73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\r\nNotAfter:\t\t12/30/2029\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse\r\n\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\tB8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\r\nNotAfter:\t\t7/25/2032\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse\r\n\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\t4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\r\nNotAfter:\t\t6/14/2041\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse\r\n\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\tD37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\r\nNotAfter:\t\t1/24/2053\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse"},{"group_id_src":"V-253428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253428","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253428","severity":"medium","group_title":"The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253428r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-253428r958448","rule_version":"WN11-PK-000010","rule_title":"The External Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the ECA Root CA certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nECA Root CA 4\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the ECA Root CA certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*ECA*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=ECA Root CA 4, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates.\n\nFor each of the ECA Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the ECA Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nECA Root CA 4\nThumbprint: 73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure websites protected with External Certificate Authority (ECA) server certificates are properly validated, the system must trust the ECA Root CAs. The ECA root certificates will ensure the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the External CAs. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"66fc050d-a1fe-4ada-a285-e5bd3ff873b5","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A2DE8E7ED057D0504EDBDDD63507A5CA39E0EA3\r\n~~~~~\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=ECA Root CA 4, OU=ECA, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\t73E8BB08E337D6A5A6AEF90CFFDD97D9176CB582\r\nNotAfter:\t\t12/30/2029\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse"},{"group_id_src":"V-253429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253429","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253429","severity":"medium","group_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253429r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-253429r958448","rule_version":"WN11-PK-000015","rule_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.  \n                                           \nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Interoperability cross-certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Untrusted Certificates.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 \n           \nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: AC06108CA348CC03B53795C64BF84403C1DBD341\nNotAfter: 1/22/2022 \n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA....\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA....\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint : 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to: Saturday, November 16, 2024","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2cea22ee-58f3-496e-9d48-acfff661a0a1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 51B747EE3B125A77FBCDF81558A9EC90778C1040\r\n~~~~~\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nIssuer:\t\tCN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\t49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\r\nNotAfter:\t\t11/16/2024\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse"},{"group_id_src":"V-253430","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253430","title":"SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253430","severity":"medium","group_title":"The US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253430r1081058_rule","rule_id":"SV-253430r1081058","rule_version":"WN11-PK-000020","rule_title":"The US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM                                         \nIssued To: DOD Root CA 6\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026 \n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate is installed on unclassified systems as an Untrusted Certificate.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 A\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", then click \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", then click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", then click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", then click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA...\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: Thumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM                                       \nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026 9:56:22 AM","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DOD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DOD Root CAs, the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"33099ae4-a16f-44d1-8824-41424e44b2a8","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E517778DDA1048A631EF937AF38A78F38059344\r\n~~~~~\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nIssuer:\t\tCN=US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\t9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\r\nNotAfter:\t\t7/18/2025\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse\r\n\r\nSubject:\t\tCN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nIssuer:\t\tCN=US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\r\nThumbprint:\tD471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\r\nNotAfter:\t\t7/18/2026\r\nInstalled:\t\tFalse"},{"group_id_src":"V-253431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253431","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253431","severity":"medium","group_title":"Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.","rule_id_src":"SV-253431r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253431r958726","rule_version":"WN11-RG-000005","rule_title":"Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive.\n\nThe default permissions of the higher level keys are noted below.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nMicrosoft has also given read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 11 to the following SID.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the default registry permissions for the keys note below of the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE hive.\n\nIf any non-privileged groups such as Everyone, Users or Authenticated Users have greater than Read permission, this is a finding.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\nRight click on the registry areas noted below.\nSelect \"Permissions...\" and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nOther subkeys under the noted keys may also be sampled. There may be some instances where non-privileged groups have greater than read permission.\n\nMicrosoft has given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in later versions of Windows 11 to the following SID, this is currently not a finding.\n\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681\n\nIf the defaults have not been changed, these are not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system. Changing the system's registry permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2c5eca31-0688-4eb1-9809-6a707384d96b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F41DF91D7CC77F1175BF0448AD630C47A04AA77\r\n~~~~~\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SECURITY\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant\r\n\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant\r\n\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\r\nOverallState:\tExpected permissions in place\r\nCompliance:\tCompliant"},{"group_id_src":"V-253433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253433","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253433","severity":"medium","group_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253433r958504_rule","rule_id":"SV-253433r958504","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000010","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Guest account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled. This account is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted. This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"92919ef2-e8e0-4a73-b13d-bc29fc8350b1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E229FD61CB0610311094C96569616A27DDDBA532\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Accounts: Guest account status' is Disabled\r\n\r\nEnableGuestAccount: 0"},{"group_id_src":"V-253434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253434","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253434","severity":"medium","group_title":"Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.","rule_id_src":"SV-253434r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253434r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000015","rule_title":"Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required. Password policies must prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system. However, if a local account with a blank password did exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c1a4fc76-99d1-41ce-bf3f-cf80e3977687","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F07B360565F79EBB7F79AFA38FCA328C91939ACE\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tLimitBlankPasswordUse\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253435","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253435","severity":"medium","group_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253435r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253435r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000020","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is set to \"Administrator\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"98993be6-bb45-4106-8972-59e60559eadc","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 85D13DFDF3798E9295EE1896DB998600620661BA\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Accounts: Rename administrator account' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nNewAdministratorName: Administrator [Expected: Not Administrator]"},{"group_id_src":"V-253436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253436","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253436","severity":"medium","group_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253436r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253436r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000025","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is set to \"Guest\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password. This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"e8d3a1f9-acc6-4f7c-842d-232b91b5283c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 770E216AA652E0696338D68C41C56D1D58B90B2B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Accounts: Rename guest account' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nNewGuestName: Guest [Expected: Not Guest]"},{"group_id_src":"V-253437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253437","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253437","severity":"medium","group_title":"Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253437r958442_rule","rule_id":"SV-253437r958442","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000030","rule_title":"Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. This setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"20c9801f-d03a-4606-be4f-7938feff87f8","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2FF066921ABC61EDFD7BC99DEC99C224BB6EF125\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tSCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253438","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253438","severity":"medium","group_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253438r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253438r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000035","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"78f354ff-54f3-4fd9-9c37-dd59d2299e72","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 73B0CB76432B45F17579B0DAF3E2C89D7C19B617\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tRequireSignOrSeal\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253439","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253439","severity":"medium","group_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted.","rule_id_src":"SV-253439r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253439r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000040","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ff345559-4113-4a2e-9495-9cd6eba562be","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FCD367983895A5151D77F0C9D35466F435E7A9A6\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tSealSecureChannel\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253440","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253440","severity":"medium","group_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253440r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253440r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000045","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"1b9c4c21-ad80-41a9-ac6b-480af5f2825c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BD918449E0B274DFED6DE644F0A856551A9A2115\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tSignSecureChannel\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253441","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253441","severity":"low","group_title":"The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","rule_id_src":"SV-253441r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253441r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000050","rule_title":"The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Disable machine account password changes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access. Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for the system. A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"87a0c8ef-2012-437d-9771-021ce7d6f3dd","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 847D71D94EE94719180ADF0CE54D158629052DAC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Disable machine account password changes' is Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tDisablePasswordChange\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253442","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253442","severity":"low","group_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","rule_id_src":"SV-253442r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253442r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000055","rule_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Maximum machine account password age\" to \"30\" or less (excluding 0 which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"(remove)This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30) (or less, excluding 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have. This setting must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"094bf113-c10f-44a4-819b-057839196c04","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4388BE43FB4AD4566FA5A6F1F28E59C9E19986AB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Maximum machine account password age' is Enabled: (30 or less but not 0)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tMaximumPasswordAge\r\nValue:\t\t0x0000001e (30)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253443","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253443","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to require a strong session key.","rule_id_src":"SV-253443r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253443r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000060","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: This setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel. Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"9eb5100d-ab9f-4f1f-8276-9099afb130f5","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C7F6FBC4145B742186AF10479E678A616224CE9\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tRequireStrongKey\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253444","title":"SRG-OS-000279-GPOS-00109","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253444","severity":"medium","group_title":"The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.","rule_id_src":"SV-253444r958636_rule","rule_id":"SV-253444r958636","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000070","rule_title":"The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit\" to \"900\" seconds\" or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended. The screen saver must be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected. This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000279-GPOS-00109, SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001133","CCI-002361"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"3d84c024-05d7-47c6-ac39-851af7b266d3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DB57F3C3AD3CFB42F62980857BFD24425987F286\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit' is NOT Enabled: (900 or less but not 0)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tInactivityTimeoutSecs (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253445","title":"SRG-OS-000024-GPOS-00007","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253445","severity":"medium","group_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","rule_id_src":"SV-253445r958392_rule","rule_id":"SV-253445r958392","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000075","rule_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" to the following.\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: \nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000024-GPOS-00007, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088, SRG-OS-000024-GPOS-00007","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000044","CCI-000048","CCI-000050"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"aa448fd4-82e4-46bc-98c6-f9a38d218d8e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AF183293FD3DE851EEB6DDBF60A3BD08FD4A4F76\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Interactive logon: Message text for users attempting to log on' is NOT Configured Properly\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tLegalNoticeText\r\nValue:\r\n\r\nType:\t\tREG_SZ"},{"group_id_src":"V-253446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253446","title":"SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253446","severity":"low","group_title":"The Windows message title for the legal notice must be configured.","rule_id_src":"SV-253446r958586_rule","rule_id":"SV-253446r958586","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000080","rule_title":"The Windows message title for the legal notice must be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\" to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or a site-defined equivalent.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN11-SO-000075.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title above\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\" or a site-defined equivalent, this is a finding.\n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN11-SO-000075.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"08714e8a-4b5e-442e-921f-6d5278e6c683","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 92119FD2AB1A3359F1C15AFDA6F73D2269E785AB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Interactive logon: Message title for users attempting to log on' is NOT Configured Properly\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tLegalNoticeCaption\r\nValue:\t\t(blank)\r\nType:\t\tREG_SZ"},{"group_id_src":"V-253447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253447","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253447","severity":"low","group_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","rule_id_src":"SV-253447r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253447r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000085","rule_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case domain controller is not available)\" to \"10\" logons or less.\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (10 logons to cache).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 10 (or less)\n\nThis setting only applies to domain-joined systems, however, it is configured by default on all systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system. This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable. Even though the credential cache is well-protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b4ec669e-8e68-4740-a0f0-5a2210fca0d3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A628238FD7525A54C409E785D61B4BA63F551ACD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Interactive logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case domain controller is not available)' is Enabled: (10 or less)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\r\nValue Name:\tCachedLogonsCount\r\nValue:\t\t10\r\nType:\t\tREG_SZ"},{"group_id_src":"V-253448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253448","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253448","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","rule_id_src":"SV-253448r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253448r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000095","rule_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: SCRemoveOption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nThis can be left not configured or set to \"No action\" on workstations with the following conditions. This must be documented with the ISSO.\n-The setting cannot be configured due to mission needs, or because it interferes with applications.\n-Policy must be in place that users manually lock workstations when leaving them unattended.\n-The screen saver is properly configured to lock as required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked. Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"eda779f4-7ca5-4ccd-808f-6bca6d908c24","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F966963036F422139920B0CD0E76DC2DE1882559\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior' is NOT Lock Workstation or Force Logoff\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\r\nValue Name:\tSCRemoveOption\r\nValue:\t\t0 [Expected 1 or 2]\r\nType:\t\tREG_SZ"},{"group_id_src":"V-253449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253449","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253449","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","rule_id_src":"SV-253449r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253449r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000100","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"481ae904-a31a-4b1e-8ac4-3a89a7a64343","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F84899419C47FE6394568B192BE7F37A1C1E827A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always)' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tRequireSecuritySignature\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0) [Expected 1]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253450","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253450","severity":"medium","group_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","rule_id_src":"SV-253450r987796_rule","rule_id":"SV-253450r987796","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000110","rule_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain text) password authentication. Sending plain text passwords across the network, when authenticating to an SMB server, reduces the overall security of the environment. Check with the vendor of the SMB server to see if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000197"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"e19ad7ac-a726-4048-ae6a-17b3dd5ab305","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F5B36F5E7183183D1BFF1DE1105D47E7E11B0600\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Microsoft network client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers' is Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tEnablePlainTextPassword\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253451","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253451","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","rule_id_src":"SV-253451r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-253451r958908","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000120","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will only communicate with an SMB client that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"9d444dfe-9da5-4d23-8a64-056400762026","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F0F659038FCF0945533CD5D66128637F56B0BD7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tRequireSecuritySignature\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0) [Expected 1]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253452","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253452","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253452r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253452r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000140","rule_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system. Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d8347060-6cc1-4b2d-8a65-cde8b3c83171","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D5F1A4DB0DA0BA38AB9A3F9E311322454E83E8E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation' is Disabled\r\n\r\nLSAAnonymousNameLookup: 0"},{"group_id_src":"V-253453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253453","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253453","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.","rule_id_src":"SV-253453r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253453r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000145","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous log on users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b90164cb-8b33-4759-a34e-ae03ae7734df","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F6523F57FA82EC2CB76019943CD18BA9AB5DDAB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tRestrictAnonymousSAM\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253454","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253454","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","rule_id_src":"SV-253454r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-253454r1137695","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000150","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"f26705be-748e-41d3-80e1-5e2f0f15c5f2","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 972B6D5E8826CB4460622AE68522C4443075C49B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tRestrictAnonymous\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253455","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253455","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253455r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253455r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000160","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted. If this setting is enabled, then anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group. Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"62f08aa1-dd68-4a49-8467-a0ea09b86a96","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A404131AE0D681979434FE136A9A4478279D9362\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users' is Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tEveryoneIncludesAnonymous\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253456","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253456","severity":"high","group_title":"Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.","rule_id_src":"SV-253456r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-253456r1137695","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000165","rule_title":"Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous access to named pipes or shares provides the potential for unauthorized system access. This setting restricts access to those defined in \"Network access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" and \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\", both of which must be blank under other requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"7483ddf0-44ec-46e0-958d-d749ae2c3c13","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 73BC0D12AECBC97F3ED5D61D513BF0E30DBF1B5A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tRestrictNullSessAccess\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253457","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253457","severity":"medium","group_title":"Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.","rule_id_src":"SV-253457r1081060_rule","rule_id":"SV-253457r1081060","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000167","rule_title":"Remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) must be restricted to Administrators.","fix_text":"Navigate to the policy Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM\".\n\nSelect \"Edit Security\" to configure the \"Security descriptor:\".\n\nAdd \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\" if it is not already listed (this is the default).\n\nSelect \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\".\n\nSelect \"Allow\" for \"Remote Access\" in \"Permissions for \"Administrators\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nThe \"Security descriptor:\" must be populated with \"O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA) for the policy to be enforced.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA)\n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows SAM stores users' passwords. Restricting remote rpc connections to the SAM to Administrators helps protect those credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d39f8f07-7791-41d0-917e-8bae23fc41e5","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: C5CD963BB2DCBFE7F252912C4B24F99BC43543EC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM' is NOT Configured\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tRestrictRemoteSAM (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253458","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253458","severity":"medium","group_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","rule_id_src":"SV-253458r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253458r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000180","rule_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c6506312-f9fa-46df-9e23-20b2a3ef47b0","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 31A0E375E74574A0EB91D374AC4BF2C005190F99\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\r\nValue Name:\tallownullsessionfallback (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253459","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253459","severity":"medium","group_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","rule_id_src":"SV-253459r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253459r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000185","rule_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol.  This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems. Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5a75a534-18e9-4e2b-8fbc-4603cf33e706","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B0434F2E38F32ED1F3DB1A57471514D00036236B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\r\nValue Name:\tAllowOnlineID (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253460","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253460","severity":"medium","group_title":"Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","rule_id_src":"SV-253460r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-253460r971535","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000190","rule_title":"Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\" to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure. This setting configures a minimum encryption type for Kerberos, preventing the use of the DES and RC4 encryption suites.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"432730c9-6f6b-4d87-88fe-a456092bc8bf","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F22934685E13E15638CC9EBB874B125D681BB3BD\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos' is NOT Enabled: (AES128_HMAC_SHA1, AES256_HMAC_SHA1, and Future encryption types)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\r\nValue Name:\tSupportedEncryptionTypes (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253461","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253461","severity":"high","group_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","rule_id_src":"SV-253461r1051056_rule","rule_id":"SV-253461r1051056","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000195","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords. This setting controls whether or not a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000196","CCI-004062"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"aa71265c-9662-456d-a7dc-c58b36283416","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F3B097CF29FE9C18F2AED93E6BE3F6B2B4E914E\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tNoLMHash\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253462","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253462","severity":"high","group_title":"The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","rule_id_src":"SV-253462r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253462r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000205","rule_title":"The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 5","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts. NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it. It is also used to authenticate logons to stand-alone computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2766f975-c464-4b23-b580-b4668d1e4699","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 74435721A49FEF12A8118D95F0F1288D09293697\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: LAN Manager authentication level' is NOT Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\r\nValue Name:\tLmCompatibilityLevel (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253463","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253463","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.","rule_id_src":"SV-253463r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253463r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000210","rule_title":"The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LDAP client signing requirements\" to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients. This setting must be set to Negotiate signing or Require signing, depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"298569b2-ecac-458a-8859-3de7ff0200ac","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C139F3F2987B84FB171239F626BE43BE792323D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: LDAP client signing requirements' is Negotiate signing\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\r\nValue Name:\tLDAPClientIntegrity\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253464","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253464","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253464","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.","rule_id_src":"SV-253464r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253464r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000215","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"870ee6a1-a3c2-422b-8b57-c18952ca1115","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FD956A0E003D57F79026494656747E287B5243F2\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients' is NOT 'Require NTLMv2 session security' and 'Require 128-bit encryption'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\r\nValue Name:\tNTLMMinClientSec\r\nValue:\t\t0x20000000 (536870912) [Expected 537395200]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253465","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253465","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.","rule_id_src":"SV-253465r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253465r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000220","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"203b899d-e063-4b2b-b253-9f7a39af1886","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AB0EB732923C1A57933AEDD61391D703AC59AA0F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers' is NOT 'Require NTLMv2 session security' and 'Require 128-bit encryption'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\r\nValue Name:\tNTLMMinServerSec\r\nValue:\t\t0x20000000 (536870912) [Expected 537395200]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253466","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253466","severity":"medium","group_title":"The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","rule_id_src":"SV-253466r1137699_rule","rule_id":"SV-253466r1137699","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000230","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: Clients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures that the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing. FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"215f708a-f4fa-40cc-b2a9-dd8f2fa1bc1f","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 74BD8833E3DA77E5E7DF0EBDA6E23ECAB9E246B4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\r\nValue Name:\tEnabled\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0) [Expected 1]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253467","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253467","severity":"low","group_title":"The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.","rule_id_src":"SV-253467r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253467r991589","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000240","rule_title":"The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default DACL that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. If this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing non-admin users to read shared objects, but not modify shared objects that they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ce1ecbec-f32e-44a1-adad-8e87f9e61ac3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0E0C38CC2164A599DCAF81B758B672D25A76B6B7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\r\nValue Name:\tProtectionMode\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253468","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253468","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253468","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-253468r1051057_rule","rule_id":"SV-253468r1051057","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000245","rule_title":"User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"6a115aa7-2fa8-464d-8a13-907e530859fc","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6BEF25A671200B55DC34A900E71CC1FB91702F16\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tFilterAdministratorToken (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253469","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253469","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","rule_id_src":"SV-253469r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253469r958518","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000250","rule_title":"User Account Control must prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Prompt for consent on the secure desktop\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2 (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"f76e111d-96ca-4bfb-89f3-d39a0c216f9e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 810B55BFABA9A88C04EE8099A62D13795A6AD582\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode' is NOT 'Prompt for consent on the secure desktop'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000005 (5) [Expected 2]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253470","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253470","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253470r1106510_rule","rule_id":"SV-253470r1106510","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000251","rule_title":"Windows 11 must use multifactor authentication for local and network access to privileged and nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"For nondomain joined systems, configuring Windows Hello for sign-on options would be suggested based on the organization's needs and capabilities.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf all of the following settings exist and are populated, this is not a finding.\n\n\\HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\Readers\n\\HKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Calais\\SmartCards","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged and nonprivileged functions is greatly increased. \n\nAll domain accounts must be enabled for multifactor authentication with the exception of local emergency accounts. \n\nMultifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication.\n\nFactors include: \n\n1) Something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN);\n\n2) Something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); and\n\n3) Something a user is (e.g., biometric).\n\nA privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user.\n\nNetwork access is defined as access to an information system by a user (or a process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the internet).\n\nLocal access is defined as access to an organizational information system by a user (or process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a direct connection without the use of a network.\n\nThe DoD CAC with DoD-approved PKI is an example of multifactor authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000765"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2493b1a4-7964-4572-8239-3a765bde7d36","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253471","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253471","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253471","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.","rule_id_src":"SV-253471r1051058_rule","rule_id":"SV-253471r1051058","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000255","rule_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny elevation requests for standard users.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. Denying elevation requests from standard user accounts requires tasks that need elevation to be initiated by accounts with administrative privileges. This ensures correct accounts are used on the system for privileged tasks to help mitigate credential theft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0669a9d3-4b73-440a-860d-7ebb2c612b69","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6E996495329657D77980925C2CB32AD00DB079B8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users' is NOT 'Automatically deny elevation requests'\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tConsentPromptBehaviorUser\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1) [Expected 0]\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253472","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253472","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","rule_id_src":"SV-253472r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253472r958518","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000260","rule_title":"User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"503db840-dca4-427e-99ea-5369b13f3ead","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BFFC99F9B07BD105322A54EE4A623F1F3438AEFC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tEnableInstallerDetection\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253473","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253473","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","rule_id_src":"SV-253473r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253473r958518","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000265","rule_title":"User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0998da02-8fd1-4aad-b3d9-c96ad89eb909","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6571A60A1867AB9E01591880C73BE0B30634C145\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tEnableSecureUIAPaths\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253474","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253474","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","rule_id_src":"SV-253474r1051059_rule","rule_id":"SV-253474r1051059","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000270","rule_title":"User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting enables UAC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"835e576b-4fe9-408a-b38d-404c3566889a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0F32DB66BBF25820A20EA8B4329482B08E9AFE1A\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tEnableLUA\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253475","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253475","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253475","severity":"medium","group_title":"User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","rule_id_src":"SV-253475r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-253475r958518","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000275","rule_title":"User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures non-UAC compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"352af3b5-d118-4eda-bfe7-9a506c8edff7","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FAECF72E4AD7B453B7C3012D20F05D511BFF4E31\r\n~~~~~\r\n'User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations' is Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\r\nValue Name:\tEnableVirtualization\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000001 (1)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-253476","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253476","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253476","severity":"medium","group_title":"Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.","rule_id_src":"SV-253476r1051060_rule","rule_id":"SV-253476r1051060","rule_version":"WN11-SO-000280","rule_title":"Passwords for enabled local Administrator accounts must be changed at least every 60 days.","fix_text":"Change the enabled local Administrator account password at least every 60 days. \n\nWindows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password. Domain-joined and nondomain-joined systems can configure this to occur more frequently. LAPS will change the password every 30 days by default. \n\nMore information is available at:\nhttps://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/by-popular-demand-windows-laps-available-now/ba-p/3788747\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/laps/laps-overview#windows-laps-supported-platforms-and-azure-ad-laps-preview-status","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If there are no enabled local Administrator accounts, this is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the password last set date for the enabled local Administrator account.\n\nOn the standalone or domain-joined workstation:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-LocalUser -Name * | Select-Object *\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is greater than \"60\" days old for the local Administrator account for administering the computer/domain, this is a finding.\n\nVerify LAPS is configured and operational. \n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> LAPS >> Password Settings >> Set to enabled. Password Complexity, large letters + small letters + numbers + special, Password Length 14, Password Age 60. If not configured as shown, this is a finding. \n\nVerify LAPS Operational logs >> Event Viewer >> Applications and Services Logs >> Microsoft >> Windows >> LAPS >> Operational. Verify LAPS policy process is completing. If it is not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the password. A local Administrator account is not generally used and its password may not be changed as frequently as necessary. Changing the password for enabled Administrator accounts on a regular basis will limit its exposure.\n\nWindows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000199","CCI-004066"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"bd73a69d-e741-4b24-b746-9af2fd0de659","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 252B472BBA349819366AD7CE5614D691007FA489\r\n~~~~~\r\nEnabled local administrator accounts with a password older than 60 days:\r\n---------------------------\r\nAccount:\t\t\trich.admin\r\nSID:\t\t\t\tS-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nEnabled:\t\t\tTrue\r\nPassword Last Set:\t03/22/2019 16:16:04 (2679 days ago)\r\n\r\nAccount:\t\t\tsunst\r\nSID:\t\t\t\tS-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1005\r\nEnabled:\t\t\tTrue\r\nPassword Last Set:\t06/09/2023 09:21:35 (1139 days ago)\r\n\r\n\r\nLAPS Configuration:\r\n---------------------------\r\nPolicy Name:\tPassword Settings | Password Complexity\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\LAPS\r\nValue Name:\tPasswordComplexity\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nValue Type:\t(NotFound)\r\nConfigured:\tFalse [finding]\r\n\r\nPolicy Name:\tPassword Settings | Password Length\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\LAPS\r\nValue Name:\tPasswordLength\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nValue Type:\t(NotFound)\r\nConfigured:\tFalse [finding]\r\n\r\nPolicy Name:\tPassword Settings | PasswordAge (Days)\r\nPath:\t\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\LAPS\r\nValue Name:\tPasswordAgeDays\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nValue Type:\t(NotFound)\r\nConfigured:\tFalse [finding]"},{"group_id_src":"V-253477","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253477","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253477","severity":"low","group_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","rule_id_src":"SV-253477r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-253477r958478","rule_version":"WN11-UC-000015","rule_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Start Menu and Taskbar >> Notifications >> \"Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Toast notifications that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel. Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"27e25b75-b39c-41da-98e6-9b8688cb834b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 737A8BEA3C749E7CDD49AB1256A1E0DBC65CCB00\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\r\nValue Name:\tNoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253478","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253478","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253478","severity":"medium","group_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","rule_id_src":"SV-253478r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-253478r991589","rule_version":"WN11-UC-000020","rule_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nTo correct this, configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Attachment Manager >> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d5ca5e56-f8f1-4287-a3c3-50e258de323e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nUsername: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin\r\nUserSID: S-1-5-21-3749662952-72805060-911958546-1003\r\nResultHash: 04E54C06259C381C222A28EC3B785FB7FEC79F5D\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Do not preserve zone information in file attachments' is Not Configured in group policy which is acceptable per the STIG.\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKCU:\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\r\nValue Name:\tSaveZoneInformation (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-253479","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253479","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253479","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253479r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253479r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000005","rule_title":"The \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"51203f8f-3ec5-450b-bd5c-0cacc8bb01d1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3CEE40B379C0CDD18F07AD1CDF8E350E96EB8DF9\r\n~~~~~\r\nAccess Credential Manager as a trusted caller:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253480","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253480","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Access this computer from the network\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.","rule_id_src":"SV-253480r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253480r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000010","rule_title":"The \"Access this computer from the network\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Remote Desktop Users groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators  \nRemote Desktop Users","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nRemote Desktop Users\n\nIf a domain application account such as for a management tool requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account, managed at the domain level, must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length and frequency of changes as defined in the Windows Server STIGs.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and must be limited to those that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"28371463-8f85-48a9-9449-bc1d1ea1a7d3","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CC6540092CD9DB29442AC1D7052727E4C5D8C9C4\r\n~~~~~\r\nAccess this computer from the network:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nBUILTIN\\Backup Operators\r\nBUILTIN\\Users\r\nEveryone"},{"group_id_src":"V-253481","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253481","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253481","severity":"high","group_title":"The \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253481r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253481r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000015","rule_title":"The \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access. Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b2fc69b7-b4ab-43cb-98bd-da662921b9f0","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7C385C465E401636E50740B6969EA921AF0B5672\r\n~~~~~\r\nAct as part of the operating system:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253482","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253482","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253482","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Allow log on locally\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Users groups.","rule_id_src":"SV-253482r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253482r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000025","rule_title":"The \"Allow log on locally\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Users groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on locally\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nUsers","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"56e27c38-556b-4050-a957-1f12c2d2cec6","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: AD227460E94898211842C8FBDBBB40263B75C519\r\n~~~~~\r\nAllow log on locally:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nBUILTIN\\Backup Operators\r\nBUILTIN\\Users\r\nGuest"},{"group_id_src":"V-253483","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253483","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253483","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Back up files and directories\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253483r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253483r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000030","rule_title":"The \"Back up files and directories\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Back up files and directories\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.\"","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"33cf2a2b-1829-48e7-96e7-b307ed72e462","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5BC573CCA4D85FB20DF00E6F810AA8300CDDA865\r\n~~~~~\r\nBack up files and directories:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nBUILTIN\\Backup Operators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253484","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253484","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253484","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Change the system time\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators and Local Service.","rule_id_src":"SV-253484r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253484r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000035","rule_title":"The \"Change the system time\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators and Local Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Change the system time\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Change the system time\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Change the system time\" user right can change the system time, which can impact authentication, as well as affect time stamps on event log entries.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"1775a633-dbd8-4516-95d4-7098acac6f5b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 9CECF2E46987C02F319ED31DE8CF64658D419DB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nChange the system time:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\LOCAL SERVICE\r\nNT SERVICE\\autotimesvc"},{"group_id_src":"V-253485","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253485","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253485","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Create a pagefile\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253485r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253485r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000040","rule_title":"The \"Create a pagefile\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a pagefile\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b80b7ee9-618c-45b8-9fc0-4869bb671eee","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 08A23C17206721C8560CE48A3B33766E5935F657\r\n~~~~~\r\nCreate a pagefile:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253486","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253486","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253486","severity":"high","group_title":"The \"Create a token object\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253486r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253486r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000045","rule_title":"The \"Create a token object\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a token object\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"358af38e-8ac7-4ea2-bf2c-6bacd1e1fe04","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1983C6E7953F5C6CBA7C0AF2CAFF801FCD90EEC0\r\n~~~~~\r\nCreate a token object:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253487","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253487","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253487","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Create global objects\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","rule_id_src":"SV-253487r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253487r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000050","rule_title":"The \"Create global objects\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create global objects\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nSERVICE","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"7d93e25d-5c82-4171-bf34-2926216de976","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C792FBE78CAFDECDF1B9919ACD0740BFB32D7F69\r\n~~~~~\r\nCreate global objects:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\LOCAL SERVICE\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\NETWORK SERVICE\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\SERVICE"},{"group_id_src":"V-253488","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253488","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253488","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253488r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253488r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000055","rule_title":"The \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create permanent shared objects\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"88e89882-25fd-4cf2-b30e-c55b5e195ecf","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3BD0D3CCC880F9280F873A2618C17F46A05E3BB4\r\n~~~~~\r\nCreate permanent shared objects:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253489","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253489","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253489","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Create symbolic links\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253489r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253489r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000060","rule_title":"The \"Create symbolic links\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create symbolic links\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the workstation has an approved use of Hyper-V, such as being used as a dedicated admin workstation using Hyper-V to separate administration and standard user functions, \"NT VIRTUAL MACHINES\\VIRTUAL MACHINE\" may be assigned this user right and is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could potentially expose the system to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"5535cba5-4748-4cdb-819d-e7c1c7808bf4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 67121F8409A70B288AE5F84F92F453A3B3BA5809\r\n~~~~~\r\nCreate symbolic links:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nNT VIRTUAL MACHINE\\Virtual Machines"},{"group_id_src":"V-253490","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253490","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253490","severity":"high","group_title":"The \"Debug programs\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253490r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253490r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000065","rule_title":"The \"Debug programs\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Debug programs\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Debug Programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug Programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components. This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"090b1455-d308-4dcc-9ffd-005041cb4780","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B9EB39A9A6BF5A968761E5CA63239880B2F2C6F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nDebug Programs:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253491","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253491","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253491","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253491r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253491r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000070","rule_title":"The \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"ee9c5afd-3c9d-49a3-8a3f-efe8319642ce","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: B3A395A8D68256622951BAEDB4EC35BE2895D545\r\n~~~~~\r\nDeny access to this computer from the network:\r\n\r\nGuest"},{"group_id_src":"V-253492","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253492","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253492","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right on domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253492r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253492r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000075","rule_title":"The \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right on domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on as a batch job\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admin Group\nDomain Admin Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admin Group\nDomain Admin Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d3e09cfb-a748-4aef-aec4-5a1832ccad79","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253493","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253493","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253493","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on Windows 11 domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253493r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253493r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000080","rule_title":"The \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on Windows 11 domain-joined workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts.","fix_text":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on as a service\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems, for standalone systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" right , this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" right defines accounts that are denied log on as a service.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"376156bc-647f-4a29-a183-198cce8a5884","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-253494","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253494","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253494","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Deny log on locally\" user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253494r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253494r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000085","rule_title":"The \"Deny log on locally\" user right on workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on locally\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"2912b79f-b800-45f2-a0d6-fd0e923fe000","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: BB4C14C3B9F1A8459D589DE94C1B8B10EBC799E6\r\n~~~~~\r\nDeny log on locally:\r\n\r\nGuest"},{"group_id_src":"V-253495","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253495","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253495","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right on Windows 11 workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","rule_id_src":"SV-253495r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-253495r1137691","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000090","rule_title":"The \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right on Windows 11 workstations must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems and unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to include the following:\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, assign the Everyone group this right to prevent all access.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following groups or accounts are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" right, this is a finding:\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, the \"Everyone\" group can replace all of the groups listed below.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nPrivileged Access Workstations (PAWs) dedicated to the management of Active Directory are exempt from denying the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups. (See the Windows Privileged Access Workstation STIG for PAW requirements.)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is a built-in security group used to assign user rights and permissions to all local accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nIf Remote Desktop Services is not used by the organization, the Everyone group must be assigned this right to prevent all access.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213","CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"772c940b-2dd4-42cc-ac24-b601d39a488e","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 346D0E091CBF4A60A84EF6223F8D528D9730A1E0\r\n~~~~~\r\nDeny log on through Remote Desktop Services:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253496","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253496","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253496","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253496r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253496r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000095","rule_title":"The \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could potentially allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"d80d1ddb-1fea-4a87-b2c9-1f780054df5c","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5FCFD4987BCCD02AD18BBA1D3284AC238A9EB1D2\r\n~~~~~\r\nEnable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253497","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253497","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253497","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253497r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253497r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000100","rule_title":"The \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system which could result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"dd5ec2c5-d04f-435f-b4a3-4dd327a9ffb7","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3587FB64DDB334B0A3FD3FB7D165D5F44310EDED\r\n~~~~~\r\nForce shutdown from a remote system:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253498","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253498","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253498","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","rule_id_src":"SV-253498r1138526_rule","rule_id":"SV-253498r1138526","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000110","rule_title":"The \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nRESTRICTED SERVICES\\PrintSpoolerService\nSERVICE","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nLOCAL SERVICE\nNETWORK SERVICE\nRESTRICTED SERVICES\\PrintSpoolerService\nSERVICE","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf. An attacker could potentially use this to elevate privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"a1c89b00-0011-44e8-bb43-3e7c54c3cda1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EEBD7AB1353D4593F41E5C986CE3A8132212ADAB\r\n~~~~~\r\nImpersonate a client after authentication:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\LOCAL SERVICE\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\NETWORK SERVICE\r\nNT AUTHORITY\\SERVICE\r\nRESTRICTED SERVICES\\PrintSpoolerService"},{"group_id_src":"V-253499","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253499","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253499","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253499r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253499r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000120","rule_title":"The \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Load and unload device drivers\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right allows device drivers to dynamically be loaded on a system by a user. This could potentially be used to install malicious code by an attacker.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"8025b280-78f8-40de-9a9b-07205a05983b","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 114B3BD6F8B77E4D965F60AE2D934558935E1753\r\n~~~~~\r\nLoad and unload device drivers:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253500","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253500","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253500","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Lock pages in memory\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","rule_id_src":"SV-253500r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253500r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000125","rule_title":"The \"Lock pages in memory\" user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Lock pages in memory\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"8d2da2a0-44b0-42d4-be8c-405be505e9c4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 5571A900CFBBB6A9A42239AB25FC83EA63DC7E02\r\n~~~~~\r\nLock pages in memory:\r\n\r\nNo objects assigned to this right."},{"group_id_src":"V-253501","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253501","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253501","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253501r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-253501r958434","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000130","rule_title":"The \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Manage auditing and security log\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the organization has an \"Auditors\" group the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right can manage the security log and change auditing configurations. This could be used to clear evidence of tampering.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000171"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"05eb6d73-373b-44ee-8100-de6d91fbcd55","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: FABC86CBBB1E8892FD3EE390D283C77A4858E477\r\n~~~~~\r\nManage auditing and security log:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253502","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253502","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253502","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253502r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253502r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000140","rule_title":"The \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Modify firmware environment values\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right can change hardware configuration environment variables. This could result in hardware failures or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"0a2393fd-fc2f-4376-af72-55fee46f8b3a","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 0061C891396E814EB1AC2BA95579649714C5D12F\r\n~~~~~\r\nModify firmware environment values:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253503","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253503","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253503r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253503r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000145","rule_title":"The \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right can manage volume and disk configurations. They could potentially delete volumes, resulting in data loss or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"8b3773b6-472b-4435-9555-a23e95be3f61","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F9B7D4B6314EE59322699A4E4BE4C03FE6B9FB0E\r\n~~~~~\r\nPerform volume maintenance tasks:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253504","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253504","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253504","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Profile single process\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253504r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253504r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000150","rule_title":"The \"Profile single process\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Profile single process\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Profile single process\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Profile single process\" user right can monitor non-system processes performance. An attacker could potentially use this to identify processes to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"e566aab8-41b7-44fe-818c-c87c404c00c1","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7CC2A14D9519395B1EFE4702EBFBFCD70BB3696D\r\n~~~~~\r\nProfile single process:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253505","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253505","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253505","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Restore files and directories\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253505r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253505r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000160","rule_title":"The \"Restore files and directories\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Restore files and directories\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Restore files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Restore files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data. It could also be used to over-write more current data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"c8849533-ff51-4e73-8cc5-3ad4e42df2cd","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A94CCD86A8BCF14E0E7F86CC6AEE309962DDCBE0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRestore files and directories:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators\r\nBUILTIN\\Backup Operators"},{"group_id_src":"V-253506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-253506","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-253506","severity":"medium","group_title":"The \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","rule_id_src":"SV-253506r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-253506r958726","rule_version":"WN11-UR-000165","rule_title":"The \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" to only include the following groups or accounts:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than the following are granted the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right can take ownership of objects and make changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"eb9389de-8304-4966-aac4-9f66585b37ee","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7D91822F330DCB4225BF351C8C4567133778968C\r\n~~~~~\r\nTake ownership of files or other objects:\r\n\r\nBUILTIN\\Administrators"},{"group_id_src":"V-256893","group_tree":[{"id":"V-256893","title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-256893","severity":"medium","group_title":"Internet Explorer must be disabled for Windows 11.","rule_id_src":"SV-256893r958552_rule","rule_id":"SV-256893r958552","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000391","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be disabled for Windows 11.","fix_text":"For Windows 11 semi-annual channel, remove or disable the IE11 application. \n\nTo disable IE11 as a standalone browser:\n\nSet the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Disable Internet Explorer 11 as a standalone browser\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Never\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if IE11 is installed or enabled on Windows 11 semi-annual channel.\n\nIf IE11 is installed or not disabled on Windows 11 semi-annual channel, this is a finding.\n\nIf IE11 is installed on an unsupported operating system and is enabled or installed, this is a finding.\n\nFor more information, visit: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/lifecycle/faq/internet-explorer-microsoft-edge#what-is-the-lifecycle-policy-for-internet-explorer-","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Internet Explorer 11 (IE11) is not supported on Windows 11 semi-annual channel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"b795bdc1-3c9b-453c-b986-2846b8da76d5","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F88764E5F947E95FAD5F5CA4A16E1C74984009B7\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Internet Explorer 11 as a standalone browser' is NOT Enabled: ('Never [0]')\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\r\nValue Name:\tNotifyDisableIEOptions (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-257592","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257592","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257592","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must not have portproxy enabled or in use.","rule_id_src":"SV-257592r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-257592r991589","rule_version":"WN11-00-000395","rule_title":"Windows 11 must not have portproxy enabled or in use.","fix_text":"Contact the Administrator to run \"netsh interface portproxy delete\" with elevation. Remove any enabled portproxies that may be configured.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Check the registry key for existence of proxied ports:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\PortProxy\\.\n\nIf the key contains v4tov4\\tcp\\ or is populated v4tov4\\tcp\\, this is a finding.\n\nRun \"netsh interface portproxy show all\".\n\nIf the command displays any results, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Having portproxy enabled or configured in Windows 10 could allow a man-in-the-middle attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"6070425f-3f68-418a-84fe-4fa8d4866526","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 06CB41494A81F1868231ECCA62AF7839834012CB\r\n~~~~~\r\n'HKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\PortProxy\\v4tov4\\tcp' does not exist\r\n\r\n'netsh interface portproxy show all' returned no output"},{"group_id_src":"V-257770","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257770","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257770","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must have command line process auditing events enabled for failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-257770r958412_rule","rule_id":"SV-257770r958412","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000585","rule_title":"Windows 11 must have command line process auditing events enabled for failures.","fix_text":"Go to Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >>Security Settings>> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Detailed Tracking >> Set \"Audit Process Creation\" to \"Failure\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Ensure Audit Process Creation auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policy >> Detailed Tracking >> Audit Process Creation. \n\nIf \"Audit Process Creation\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When this policy setting is enabled, the operating system generates audit events when a process fails to start and the name of the program or user that created it.\n\nThese audit events can assist in understanding how a computer is being used and tracking user activity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"397e2166-5521-44c9-a4a8-974042cae471","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 47EC89D257115BA9AD42CC2F12E1E724F80EFED2\r\n~~~~~\r\nProcess Creation:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-268317","group_tree":[{"id":"V-268317","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-268317","severity":"medium","group_title":"Copilot must be disabled for Windows 11.","rule_id_src":"SV-268317r1135320_rule","rule_id":"SV-268317r1135320","rule_version":"WN11-00-000125","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled for Windows 11.","fix_text":"Open PowerShell as an administrator. Run the following command:\n\nGet-AppxPackage -AllUsers *CoPilot* | Remove-AppxPackage -AllUsers","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run the following PowerShell command as an administrator:\n\nGet-AppxPackage -AllUsers | Where-Object { $_.Name -like \"*Copilot*\" }\n\nIf Microsoft.Copilot displays, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"93d13f00-826c-431a-966b-8a3cd3765c10","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E7F5A06B04EE94EC2D5ED9C9A932CB453DE8775A\r\n~~~~~\r\nMicrosoft.copilot found [finding]:\r\n\r\nName:\t\t\tMicrosoft.Copilot\r\nPublisher:\t\t\tCN=Microsoft Corporation, O=Microsoft Corporation, L=Redmond, S=Washington, C=US\r\nVersion:\t\t\t150.0.4078.65\r\nPackageFullName:\tMicrosoft.Copilot_150.0.4078.65_neutral__8wekyb3d8bbwe\r\nInstallLocation:\t\tC:\\Program Files\\WindowsApps\\Microsoft.Copilot_150.0.4078.65_neutral__8wekyb3d8bbwe"},{"group_id_src":"V-268318","group_tree":[{"id":"V-268318","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-268318","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 systems must use either Group Policy or an approved Mobile Device Management (MDM) product to enforce STIG compliance.","rule_id_src":"SV-268318r1135322_rule","rule_id":"SV-268318r1135322","rule_version":"WN11-CC-000063","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must use either Group Policy or an approved Mobile Device Management (MDM) product to enforce STIG compliance.","fix_text":"Configure the Windows 11 system to use either Group Policy or an approved MDM product to enforce STIG compliance.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the Windows 11 system is receiving policy from either group Policy or an MDM with the following steps:\n\nFrom a command line or PowerShell:\n\ngpresult /R\nOS Configuration: Member Workstation\n\nIf the system is not being managed by GPO, ask the administrator to indicate which MDM is managing the device.\n\nFrom PowerShell: Get-Service -Name \"IntuneManagementExtension\"\n\nIf the Windows 11 system is not receiving policy from either group Policy or an MDM, this is a finding.\n\nThis is NA for standalone, nondomain-joined systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without Windows 11 systems being managed, devices could be rogue and become targets of an attacker.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"da7edbce-5952-401d-89a0-c592bd135d27","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-278926","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278926","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278926","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit file system failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-278926r1135296_rule","rule_id":"SV-278926r1135296","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000581","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit file system failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"531f2f82-cf63-4dec-954f-fffc0bb8d8d4","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 700F68F22FD5E019A2F0DBDCEB088DE1826FB746\r\n~~~~~\r\nFile System:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-278927","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278927","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278927","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit file system successes.","rule_id_src":"SV-278927r1135299_rule","rule_id":"SV-278927r1135299","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000582","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit file system successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_11__STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5471","uuid":"bfffb41c-c9b2-4fa2-8349-cb06657319ff","stig_uuid":"9417b45a-cc73-4ef8-8de9-659e60c46780","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Windows11_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 700F68F22FD5E019A2F0DBDCEB088DE1826FB746\r\n~~~~~\r\nFile System:\tNo Auditing"},{"group_id_src":"V-278928","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278928","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278928","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit handle manipulation failures.","rule_id_src":"SV-278928r1135302_rule","rule_