e this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Outbound connections are allowed on a private network, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection. This allows normal outbound communication, which could be restricted as necessary with additional rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54890","V-17429"],"ccis":["CCI-001094"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"cf7bb406-f201-4289-9d5b-f0d24b49a8bb","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 054BE6EF632A9C63EE7501F28A9CDE83465734A5\r\n~~~~~\r\nPrivate Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultOutboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultOutboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)"},{"group_id_src":"V-241999","group_tree":[{"id":"V-241999","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-241999","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for private network connections.","rule_id_src":"SV-241999r922948_rule","rule_id":"SV-241999r922948","rule_version":"WNFWA-000017","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for private network connections.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Size limit (KB)\" to \"16,384\" or greater.\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh command may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile logging maxfilesize 16384\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. The firewall log file size for a private connection will be set to ensure enough capacity is allocated for audit data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54903","V-17435"],"ccis":["CCI-000140"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"d5567bf5-7d84-4d70-acc7-87101ce63cf5","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A9F3D3EE3A3FE8C561B0DAE224EF50D9328C36DC\r\n~~~~~\r\nPrivate Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogFileSize\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogFileSize\r\nValue:\t\t0x00001000 (4096)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242000","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242000","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242000","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a private network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242000r922950_rule","rule_id":"SV-242000r922950","rule_version":"WNFWA-000018","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a private network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Log dropped packets\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile logging droppedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging droppedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of dropped packets for a private network connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail of potential issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54904","V-17436"],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"713cbbbd-44a2-452b-9de6-d166f0c25e9a","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 088809799DC665E75B1F4F891DCC8636EF6DC74E\r\n~~~~~\r\nPrivate Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogDroppedPackets\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogDroppedPackets\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242001","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242001","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242001","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a private network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242001r922952_rule","rule_id":"SV-242001r922952","rule_version":"WNFWA-000019","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a private network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Private Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Logged successful connections\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set privateprofile logging allowedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging allowedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Private Profile is not enabled (see V-17416), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of successful connections for a private network connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail if issues are discovered.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54905","V-17437"],"ccis":["CCI-001462"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"f0353e4e-7010-4414-b5ef-9ca3a8c85b7a","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F7BF4FA513357AE68B46BCBB9E9CB20C6C4EFF4\r\n~~~~~\r\nPrivate Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PrivateProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogSuccessfulConnections\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\StandardProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogSuccessfulConnections\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242002","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242002","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242002","severity":"high","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must block unsolicited inbound connections when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242002r922954_rule","rule_id":"SV-242002r922954","rule_version":"WNFWA-000020","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must block unsolicited inbound connections when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> State, \"Inbound connections\" to \"Block (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultInboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Unsolicited inbound connections may be malicious attempts to gain access to a system. Unsolicited inbound connections, for which there is no rule allowing the connection, will be blocked on a public network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54906","V-17438"],"ccis":["CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"d2a51ff5-01bf-4658-bf39-6df098c47f92","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F5EC460752B3F33787ED1401C0EA10AE3D575555\r\n~~~~~\r\nPublic Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultInboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultInboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)"},{"group_id_src":"V-242003","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242003","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242003","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must allow outbound connections, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242003r922956_rule","rule_id":"SV-242003r922956","rule_version":"WNFWA-000021","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must allow outbound connections, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> State, \"Outbound connections\" to \"Allow (default)\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,allowoutbound\".\n\nBoth inbound and outbound parameters must be specified to execute this command.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  DefaultOutboundAction\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Outbound connections are allowed on a public network, unless a rule explicitly blocks the connection. This allows normal outbound communication, which could be restricted as necessary with additional rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54908","V-17439"],"ccis":["CCI-001094"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"e9859359-13de-4aa5-b681-c1596b4b9262","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 4873F37C166A3A0EF127F15BA0C14BD900C17069\r\n~~~~~\r\nPublic Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultOutboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\r\nValue Name:\tDefaultOutboundAction\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)"},{"group_id_src":"V-242004","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242004","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242004","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security local firewall rules must not be merged with Group Policy settings when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242004r922958_rule","rule_id":"SV-242004r922958","rule_version":"WNFWA-000024","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security local firewall rules must not be merged with Group Policy settings when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> Settings (select Customize) >> Rule merging, \"Apply local firewall rules:\" to \"No\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nIf the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nVerify the registry value below.\n\nIf this registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  AllowLocalPolicyMerge\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Local firewall rules will not be merged with Group Policy settings on a public network to prevent Group Policy settings from being changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54917","V-17442"],"ccis":["CCI-001190"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"9c430247-09ff-4992-a26e-220a14fd42db","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-242005","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242005","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242005","severity":"medium","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security local connection rules must not be merged with Group Policy settings when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242005r922960_rule","rule_id":"SV-242005r922960","rule_version":"WNFWA-000025","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security local connection rules must not be merged with Group Policy settings when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> Settings (select Customize) >> Rule merging, \"Apply local connection security rules:\" to \"No\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nIf the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nVerify the registry value below.\n\nIf this registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\\n\nValue Name:  AllowLocalIPsecPolicyMerge\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Local connection rules will not be merged with Group Policy settings on a public network to prevent Group Policy settings from being changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54918","V-17443"],"ccis":["CCI-001190"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"21c2b86a-25ef-41e3-81ef-cbf65491b5b0","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."},{"group_id_src":"V-242006","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242006","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242006","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for public network connections.","rule_id_src":"SV-242006r922962_rule","rule_id":"SV-242006r922962","rule_version":"WNFWA-000027","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security log size must be configured for public network connections.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Size limit (KB)\" to \"16,384\" or greater.\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh command may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile logging maxfilesize 16384\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogFileSize\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00004000 (16384) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. The firewall log file size for a public network connection will be set to ensure enough capacity is allocated for audit data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54921","V-17445"],"ccis":["CCI-000140"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"1bc306fe-1434-49a3-9887-4d52be40f26d","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 461A4F265AE2405A51C4F73F44EE5375D130A1B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nPublic Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogFileSize\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogFileSize\r\nValue:\t\t0x00001000 (4096)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242007","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242007","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242007","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242007r922964_rule","rule_id":"SV-242007r922964","rule_version":"WNFWA-000028","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log dropped packets when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Log dropped packets\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile logging droppedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging droppedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogDroppedPackets\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of dropped packets for a public network connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail of potential issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54922","V-17446"],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"84811e10-ff71-4f58-9c33-928ebbce6257","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 56984F4EF96540E7AFDBFF74671142DC54A7EA12\r\n~~~~~\r\nPublic Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogDroppedPackets\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogDroppedPackets\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242008","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242008","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242008","severity":"low","group_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a public network.","rule_id_src":"SV-242008r922966_rule","rule_id":"SV-242008r922966","rule_version":"WNFWA-000029","rule_title":"Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security must log successful connections when connected to a public network.","fix_text":"The preferred method of configuring the firewall settings is with a policy, particularly in a domain environment.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security >> Windows Defender Firewall Properties (this link will be in the right pane) >> Public Profile tab >> Logging (select Customize), \"Logged successful connections\" to \"Yes\".\n\nIn addition to using policies, systems may also be configured using the firewall GUI or Netsh commands. These methods may be more appropriate for standalone systems.\n\nThe configuration settings in the GUI are the same as those specified in the policy above. Microsoft Defender Firewall Properties will be a link in the center pane after opening Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security.\n\nThe following Netsh commands may also be used to configure this setting:\n\n\"Netsh advfirewall set publicprofile logging allowedconnections enable\".\nor\n\"Netsh advfirewall set allprofiles logging allowedconnections enable\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the firewall's Public Profile is not enabled (see V-17417), this requirement is also a finding.\n\nIf the following policy-based registry value exists and is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the policy-based registry value does not exist, verify the following registry value. If it is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\\\n\nValue Name:  LogSuccessfulConnections\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack. To be effective, it must be enabled and properly configured. Logging of successful connections for a public network connection will be enabled to maintain an audit trail if issues are discovered.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-54923","V-17447"],"ccis":["CCI-001462"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"e3056769-e9bd-4e7e-85c1-df9c7bcf63f7","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3E87745D776E7FE1BE160BC53264C139D2A325F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nPublic Profile is Enabled\r\n\r\nNo compliant setting found:\r\n---------------------------\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsFirewall\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogSuccessfulConnections\r\nValue:\t\t(NotFound)\r\nType:\t\t(NotFound)\r\n\r\nRegistry Path:\tHKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SharedAccess\\Parameters\\FirewallPolicy\\PublicProfile\\Logging\r\nValue Name:\tLogSuccessfulConnections\r\nValue:\t\t0x00000000 (0)\r\nType:\t\tREG_DWORD"},{"group_id_src":"V-242009","group_tree":[{"id":"V-242009","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-242009","severity":"medium","group_title":"Inbound exceptions to the firewall on domain workstations must only allow authorized remote management hosts.","rule_id_src":"SV-242009r922967_rule","rule_id":"SV-242009r922967","rule_version":"WNFWA-000100","rule_title":"Inbound exceptions to the firewall on domain workstations must only allow authorized remote management hosts.","fix_text":"Ensure firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.\n\nFirewall rules can be complex and should be thoroughly tested before applying in a production environment.\n\nOne method for restricting inbound connections is to only allow exceptions for a specific scope of remote IP addresses. For any inbound rules that allow connections from other systems, configure the Scope for Remote IP addresses to those of authorized management systems and remote management hosts. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet, or range. Apply the rule to all firewall profiles.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for servers and non domain workstations.\n\nVerify firewall exceptions for inbound connections on domain workstations only allow authorized management systems and remote management hosts.\n\nReview inbound firewall exception rules in Microsoft Defender Firewall with Advanced Security. Firewall rules can be complex and should be reviewed with the firewall administrator.\n\nOne method for restricting inbound connections is to only allow exceptions for a specific scope of remote IP addresses.\n\nIf allowed inbound exceptions are not limited to authorized management systems and remote management hosts, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Windows_Defender_Firewall_with_Advanced_Security_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing inbound access to domain workstations from other systems may allow lateral movement across systems if credentials are compromised. Limiting inbound connections only from authorized remote management systems will help limit this exposure.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-55086","V-36440"],"ccis":["CCI-000067"],"reference_identifier":"5363","uuid":"ea1f8027-8438-4926-86ed-94729fd1c2e8","stig_uuid":"50953bc4-21dd-4c67-8588-c0b756084b52","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsFirewall_Checks) found this to be NOT APPLICABLE on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B250DCA6A1CAE59A8146BC33A4738F54215DA7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nSystem is a 'Standalone Workstation' so this requirement is NA."}]},{"evaluate-stig":{"time":"2026-07-22T17:20:26.6868099-06:00","module":{"name":"Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks","version":"1.2026.6.9"}},"stig_name":"Mozilla Firefox Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Mozilla Firefox","stig_id":"MOZ_Firefox_STIG","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"6","uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","reference_identifier":"5446","size":34,"rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-251545","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251545","title":"SRG-APP-000456","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251545","severity":"high","group_title":"The installed version of Firefox must be supported.","rule_id_src":"SV-251545r1117151_rule","rule_id":"SV-251545r1117151","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000001","rule_title":"The installed version of Firefox must be supported.","fix_text":"Upgrade the version of the browser to an approved version by obtaining software from the vendor or other trusted source.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run Firefox. Click the ellipsis button >> Help >> About Firefox, and view the version number.\n\nIf the Firefox version is not a supported version, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using versions of an application that are not supported by the vendor is not permitted. Vendors respond to security flaws with updates and patches. These updates are not available for unsupported versions, which can leave the application vulnerable to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"5ae1c358-097e-4428-9c19-a6321b437bf7","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) was unable to determine a Status but found the below configuration on 07/22/2026:\r\nResultHash: B0FE3E5959B87ECF1026F776D5B8D888990DE1E1\r\n~~~~~\r\nApps and Features entries for Firefox:\r\n\r\nName:\tMozilla Firefox (x64 en-US)\r\nVersion:\t153.0\r\nPath:\t\tC:\\Program Files\\Mozilla Firefox"},{"group_id_src":"V-251546","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251546","title":"SRG-APP-000560","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251546","severity":"high","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above.","rule_id_src":"SV-251546r961869_rule","rule_id":"SV-251546r961869","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000002","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Minimum SSL version enabled\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: TLS 1.2   (or TLS 1.3)\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SSLVersionMin</key>\n<string>tls1.2</string>   (or <string>tls1.3</string>)\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.2\"   or (\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.3\")","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"SSLVersionMin\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"tls1.2\" or \"tls1.3\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of versions prior to TLS 1.2 are not permitted. SSL 2.0 and SSL 3.0 contain a number of security flaws. These versions must be disabled in compliance with the Network Infrastructure and Secure Remote Computing STIGs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"3b270987-63ad-4fa0-a5f9-0b9433dcf25c","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 736778E0F27B91EDDB8464BCCA605C637BFD3A96\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Minimum SSL version enabled' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tSSLVersionMin (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251547","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251547","title":"SRG-APP-000177","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251547","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.","rule_id_src":"SV-251547r1067550_rule","rule_id":"SV-251547r1067550","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000003","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>security.default_personal_cert</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <string>Ask Every Time</string>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"security.default_personal_cert\" with a value of \"Ask Every Time\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When a website asks for a certificate for user authentication, Firefox must be configured to have the user choose which certificate to present. Websites within DOD require user authentication for access, which increases security for DOD information. Access will be denied to the user if certificate management is not configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000187"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"1e73d90f-a3c5-46a3-80f8-259ea8600268","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251548","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251548","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251548","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically check for updated versions of installed search plugins.","rule_id_src":"SV-251548r1067552_rule","rule_id":"SV-251548r1067552","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000004","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically check for updated versions of installed search plugins.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>browser.search.update</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.search.update\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Updates must be controlled and installed from authorized and trusted servers. This setting overrides a number of other settings that may direct the application to access external URLs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"e1cf2f28-c670-44f9-970c-6d6a9951f87b","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251549","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251549","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251549","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins.","rule_id_src":"SV-251549r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251549r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000005","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Extensions\nPolicy Name: Extension Update\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>ExtensionUpdate</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"ExtensionUpdate\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"ExtensionUpdate\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Set this to false to disable checking for updated versions of the Extensions/Themes. Automatic updates from untrusted sites puts the enclave at risk of attack and may override security settings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"83ef0b6a-d6f3-4397-87c1-06adf15e262e","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: D3A58861079BE07961783A246249573BB25761B0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Extension Update' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tExtensionUpdate (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251550","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251550","title":"SRG-APP-000278","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251550","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically execute or download MIME types that are not authorized for auto-download.","rule_id_src":"SV-251550r961194_rule","rule_id":"SV-251550r961194","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000006","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically execute or download MIME types that are not authorized for auto-download.","fix_text":"Remove any unauthorized extensions from the auto-download list.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences\" in the browser address bar. \n\nType \"Applications\" in the Find bar in the upper-right corner. \n\nDetermine if any of the following file extensions are listed: HTA, JSE, JS, MOCHA, SHS, VBE, VBS, SCT, WSC, FDF, XFDF, LSL, LSO, LSS, IQY, RQY, DOS, BAT, PS, EPS, WCH, WCM, WB1, WB3, WCH, WCM, AD.\n\nIf the entry exists and the \"Action\" is \"Save File\" or \"Always Ask\", this is not a finding.\n \nIf an extension exists and the entry in the Action column is associated with an application that does/can execute the code, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some files can be downloaded or execute without user interaction. This setting ensures these files are not downloaded and executed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"0bc9f084-a14a-4759-ac3a-36c7bd1b23c6","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"not_a_finding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be NOT A FINDING on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 59EA3F9659C82F35F668FD750C9167DD72A5302C\r\n~~~~~\r\nEvaluate-STIG intended to utilize IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich.admin, but the user has NOT utilized Firefox on this system.\r\n\r\nUser Profile Evaluated: IT-RJOHNSON-LAP\\rich\r\n\r\nNone of the extensions in question are configured."},{"group_id_src":"V-251551","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251551","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251551","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.","rule_id_src":"SV-251551r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251551r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000007","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Form History\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableFormHistory</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFormHistory\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableFormHistory\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To protect privacy and sensitive data, Firefox provides the ability to configure the program so that data entered into forms is not saved. This mitigates the risk of a website gleaning private information from prefilled information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"477bd725-3ba1-43c3-964a-79d50d233210","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F3B3D185C0AF2C6FD711AC050601A9C058F37F25\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Form History' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableFormHistory (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251552","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251552","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251552","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to not use a password store with or without a master password.","rule_id_src":"SV-251552r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251552r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000008","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not use a password store with or without a master password.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nPolicy Name: PasswordManager\r\nPolicy State: Disabled\r\n\r\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\r\nAdd the following:\r\n<key>PasswordManagerEnabled</key>\r\n<false/>\r\n\r\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\r\nAdd the following in the policies section:\r\n\"PasswordManagerEnabled\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firefox can be set to store passwords for sites visited by the user. These individual passwords are stored in a file and can be protected by a master password. Autofill of the password can then be enabled when the site is visited. This feature could also be used to autofill the certificate PIN, which could lead to compromise of DoD information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"3d3cbbeb-c617-4e14-8f91-075e30a83c70","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A44253D301CE226F984665EC39087F788DB55F47\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Password Manager' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPasswordManagerEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251553","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251553","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251553","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to block pop-up windows.","rule_id_src":"SV-251553r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251553r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000009","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to block pop-up windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Popups\nPolicy Name: Block pop-ups from websites\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nPolicy Name: Do not allow preferences to be changed\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nOptional:\nPolicy Name: Allowed Sites\nPolicy State: Enabled\nClick \"Show...\" and enter a list of websites to be allowlisted.\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>PopupBlocking</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Allow</key>\n    <array>\n      <string>http://example.mil</string>\n      <string>http://example.gov</string>\n    </array>\n    <key>Default</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Locked</key>\n    <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"PopupBlocking\": {\n      \"Allow\": [\"http://example.mil/\",\n                \"http://example.gov/\"],\n      \"Default\": true,\n      \"Locked\": true}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"true\", this is a finding.\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Locked\" \"true\", this is a finding.\n\n\"PopupBlocking\" \"Enabled\" may be used to specify an allowlist of sites where pop-ups are desired, this is optional.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Pop-up windows may be used to launch an attack within a new browser window with altered settings. This setting blocks pop-up windows created while the page is loading.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"4abe83fd-0e27-4aeb-afaa-acffc37fa89b","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A675F5A417E61C402C626C6B286FB8E9AB858352\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Block pop-ups from websites' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\PopupBlocking\r\nName:\tDefault (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Do not allow preferences to be changed' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\PopupBlocking\r\nName:\tLocked (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------"},{"group_id_src":"V-251554","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251554","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251554","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.","rule_id_src":"SV-251554r1067554_rule","rule_id":"SV-251554r1067554","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000010","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>dom.disable_window_move_resize</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\" with a value of  \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript can make changes to the browser's appearance. This activity can help disguise an attack taking place in a minimized background window. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from moving and resizing browser windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"cb124a7c-4c9a-46c3-ab59-a5cd042a8602","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251555","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251555","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251555","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows.","rule_id_src":"SV-251555r1067556_rule","rule_id":"SV-251555r1067556","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000011","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>dom.disable_window_flip</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_flip\" with a value of \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"JavaScript can raise and lower browser windows to cause improper input. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from raising and lowering browser windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"c2720748-e9aa-4a5e-8336-1cbb09172f71","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251557","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251557","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251557","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable the installation of extensions.","rule_id_src":"SV-251557r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251557r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000013","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable the installation of extensions.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Addons\nPolicy Name: Allow add-on installs from websites\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>InstallAddonsPermission</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"InstallAddonsPermission\": {\n      \"Default\": false\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"InstallAddonsPermission\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A browser extension is a program that has been installed into the browser to add functionality. Where a plug-in interacts only with a web page and usually a third-party external application (e.g., Flash, Adobe Reader), an extension interacts with the browser program itself. Extensions are not embedded in web pages and must be downloaded and installed in order to work. Extensions allow browsers to avoid restrictions that apply to web pages. \n\nFor example, an extension can be written to combine data from multiple domains and present it when a certain page is accessed, which can be considered cross-site scripting. If a browser is configured to allow unrestricted use of extensions, plug-ins can be loaded and installed from malicious sources and used on the browser.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"cf4d0443-4616-4402-a8ad-ab518bc842d5","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C72352689A417DEF61573A2AB197D6B5D786645\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Allow add-on installs from websites' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\InstallAddonsPermission\r\nName:\tDefault (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251558","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251558","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251558","severity":"medium","group_title":"Background submission of information to Mozilla must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251558r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251558r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000014","rule_title":"Background submission of information to Mozilla must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Telemetry\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableTelemetry</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableTelemetry\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableTelemetry\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Firefox by default sends information about Firefox to Mozilla servers. There should be no background submission of technical and other information from DoD computers to Mozilla with portions posted publicly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"c602de3f-f140-46d0-b474-371d58655b73","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: DCDD6F07D12E606E8ACCBA454FA1D9CA61CC5141\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Telemetry' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableTelemetry (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251559","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251559","title":"SRG-APP-000266","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251559","severity":"low","group_title":"Firefox development tools must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251559r961167_rule","rule_id":"SV-251559r961167","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000015","rule_title":"Firefox development tools must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Developer Tools\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableDeveloperTools</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableDeveloperTools\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableDeveloperTools\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information needed by an attacker to begin looking for possible vulnerabilities in a web browser includes any information about the web browser and plug-ins or modules being used. When debugging or trace information is enabled in a production web browser, information about the web browser, such as web browser type, version, patches installed, plug-ins and modules installed, type of code being used by the hosted application, and any back ends being used for data storage may be displayed. Because this information may be placed in logs and general messages during normal operation of the web browser, an attacker does not have to cause an error condition to gain this information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"b612af96-e6a4-49b4-a3f1-34c0e8ac389e","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 959EFA43F90D94F4336712FE9BB711E8859140AC\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Developer Tools' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableDeveloperTools (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251560","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251560","title":"SRG-APP-000175","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251560","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.","rule_id_src":"SV-251560r1067559_rule","rule_id":"SV-251560r1067559","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000016","rule_title":"Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.","fix_text":"Install the DOD root certificates. Other AO-approved certificates may also be used. Certificates designed for SIPRNet may be used as appropriate.\n\nOn Windows, import certificates from the operating system by using Certificates >> Import Enterprise Roots (Certificates) via policy or Group Policy Object (GPO).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences#privacy\" in the browser window. \n\nScroll down to the bottom and select \"View Certificates...\".\n\nIn the Certificate Manager window, select the \"Authorities\" tab.\n\nScroll through the Certificate Name list to the U.S. Government heading. Look for the entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5.\n\nIf there are entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5, select them individually.\n\nClick \"View\".\n\nVerify the issuer name is \"US Government\".\n\nIf there are no entries for the appropriate DOD root certificates, this is a finding. If other AO-approved certificates are used, this is not a finding. If SIPRNet-specific certificates are used, this is not a finding.\n\nNote: In a Windows environment, use of policy setting \"security.enterprise_roots.enabled=true\" will point Firefox to the Windows Trusted Root Certification Authority Store. This is not a finding. It can also be set via the policy Certificates >> ImportEnterpriseRoots, which can be verified via \"about:policies\".","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The DOD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DOD Certificate Authority (CA).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"78ff1bb9-8503-41aa-ab08-d240485ee043","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-251562","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251562","title":"SRG-APP-000326","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251562","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must prevent the user from quickly deleting data.","rule_id_src":"SV-251562r1156569_rule","rule_id":"SV-251562r1156569","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000018","rule_title":"Firefox must prevent the user from quickly deleting data.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Mozilla >> Firefox.\nPolicy Name: Disable Forget Button\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisableForgetButton</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableForgetButton\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Enter \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableForgetButton\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"There should not be an option for a user to \"forget\" work they have done. This is required to meet nonrepudiation controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"6b59f401-d2e6-413e-b26e-733592af6e29","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 83DD0036EFCC9E4F55C30354F3FC328F808F2E9B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Forget Button' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableForgetButton (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251563","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251563","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251563","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox private browsing must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251563r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251563r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000019","rule_title":"Firefox private browsing must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Private Browsing\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisablePrivateBrowsing</key>\n<true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePrivateBrowsing\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisablePrivateBrowsing\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Private browsing allows the user to browse the internet without recording their browsing history/activity. From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable. Best practice requires that browser history is retained.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"e2f482db-8c76-4baf-90c9-418f329a30d8","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E37943BE21C2994DE12C13B7C5B69F5B6589053B\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Private Browsing' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisablePrivateBrowsing (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251564","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251564","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251564","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox search suggestions must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251564r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251564r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000020","rule_title":"Firefox search suggestions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Search\nPolicy Name: Search Suggestions\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SearchSuggestEnabled</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SearchSuggestEnabled\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"SearchSuggestEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Search suggestions must be disabled as this could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"87c975f8-4cfb-45c5-8401-78c00308259c","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: EE390EAF355EE1108660E1759EC3610889750371\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Search Suggestions' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tSearchSuggestEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251565","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251565","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251565","severity":"low","group_title":"Firefox autoplay must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251565r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251565r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000021","rule_title":"Firefox autoplay must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Permissions\\Autoplay\nPolicy Name: Default autoplay level\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Block Audio and Video\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Permissions</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>Autoplay</key>\n  <dict>\n    <string>block-audio-video</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n \nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Permissions\": {\n  \"Autoplay\": {\n    \"Default\": \"block-audio-video\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Permissions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Autoplay\" with a value of \"Default\" and \"Block-audio-video\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Autoplay allows the user to control whether videos can play automatically (without user consent) with audio content. The user must be able to select content that is run within the browser window.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"48b424ae-9dd0-4e02-bdb9-01db0a6dcd5f","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 3C44A66EC13DFA9A7A3EC0AF684B92F78E407F92\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Default autoplay level' is NOT Enabled (Block Audio and Video)\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Permissions\\Autoplay\r\nName:\tDefault (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251566","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251566","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251566","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox network prediction must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251566r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251566r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000022","rule_title":"Firefox network prediction must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Network Prediction\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>NetworkPrediction</key>\n<false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"NetworkPrediction\": false","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"NetworkPrediction\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If network prediction is enabled, requests to URLs are made without user consent. The browser should always make a direct DNS request without prefetching occurring.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"03e477b6-2e97-4dd9-ba2e-201f6f4c52c3","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 156A79FF67132A4235A04C20AE555177A4A47362\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Network Prediction' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tNetworkPrediction (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251567","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251567","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251567","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox fingerprinting protection must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251567r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251567r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000023","rule_title":"Firefox fingerprinting protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Fingerprinting\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>EnableTrackingProtection</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Fingerprinting</key>\n <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Fingerprinting\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Fingerprinting\"  with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nFingerprinting scripts collect information about browser and device configuration, such as operating system, screen resolution, and other settings. By compiling these pieces of data, fingerprinters create a unique profile that can be used to track the user around the web.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"2aed7ca1-b99e-4d6e-aa3f-94b0ebc75232","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A7A01EF6C4E82EEFBBBE675095571A43E3D31A4\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Fingerprinting' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EnableTrackingProtection\r\nName:\tFingerprinting (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251568","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251568","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251568","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox cryptomining protection must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251568r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251568r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000024","rule_title":"Firefox cryptomining protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Cryptomining\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>EnableTrackingProtection</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Cryptomining</key>\n <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Cryptomining\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Cryptomining\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nCryptomining scripts use a computer's central processing unit to invisibly mine cryptocurrency.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"54671c16-65b8-4fa5-adab-d0c66008d39c","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 8866D582C96A22E5CCC426DCA0FDC1A134D6F391\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Cryptomining' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EnableTrackingProtection\r\nName:\tCryptomining (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251569","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251569","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251569","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251569r1067561_rule","rule_id":"SV-251569r1067561","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000025","rule_title":"Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>browser.contentblocking.category</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <string>strict</string>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.contentblocking.category\" with a value of  \"strict\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Tracking generally refers to content, cookies, or scripts that can collect browsing data across multiple sites.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of nonessential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"f72a826c-fb65-4e65-90a8-ee9457640129","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251570","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251570","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251570","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251570r1067563_rule","rule_id":"SV-251570r1067563","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000026","rule_title":"Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>Preferences</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Value</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Status</key>\n    <string>locked</string>\n  </dict>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n\"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n\"Value\": false,\n\"Status\": \"locked\"\n},","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program makes it easier for users to discover extensions that have been reviewed for security, functionality, and user experience. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"62689406-98cc-47c5-a686-0fe55688754a","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: A589B350ECC9A883B9538FEC31E6AE9C74E52099\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Preferences' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tPreferences (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251571","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251571","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251571","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox deprecated ciphers must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251571r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251571r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000027","rule_title":"Firefox deprecated ciphers must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Disabled Ciphers\nPolicy Name: TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>DisabledCiphers</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA</key>\n    <true/>\n  </dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisabledCiphers\": {\n  \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"DisabledCiphers\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\" with a value of  \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A weak cipher is defined as an encryption/decryption algorithm that uses a key of insufficient length. Using an insufficient length for a key in an encryption/decryption algorithm opens up the possibility (or probability) that the encryption scheme could be broken.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"1bb4f8ad-7eab-4bc9-9be1-dbd18886e234","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: CAF2945ED1E46CEE62531A233FEA73FAFE559BF8\r\n~~~~~\r\n'TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisabledCiphers\r\nName:\tTLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251572","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251572","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251572","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser.","rule_id_src":"SV-251572r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251572r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000028","rule_title":"Firefox must not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\User Messaging\nPolicy Name: Extension Recommendations\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>UserMessaging</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>ExtensionRecommendations</key>\n  <false/>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"UserMessaging\": {\n  \"ExtensionRecommendations\": false\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"UserMessaging\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"ExtensionRecommendations\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program recommends extensions to users as they surf the web.\n\nThe user must not be encouraged to install extensions from the websites they visit. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"2ac587b9-7f40-477b-b00d-b990d83c1c09","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 6201AB072BB14411A823F99A70D20623813E3004\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Extension Recommendations' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\UserMessaging\r\nName:\tExtensionRecommendations (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251573","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251573","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251573","severity":"medium","group_title":"The Firefox New Tab page must not show Top Sites, Sponsored Top Sites, Pocket Recommendations, Sponsored Pocket Stories, Searches, Highlights, or Snippets.","rule_id_src":"SV-251573r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251573r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000029","rule_title":"The Firefox New Tab page must not show Top Sites, Sponsored Top Sites, Pocket Recommendations, Sponsored Pocket Stories, Searches, Highlights, or Snippets.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\r\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\r\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nPolicy Name: Customize Firefox Home\r\nPolicy State: Enabled\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Search\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Top Sites\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Top Sites\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Recommended by Pocket\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Pocket Stories\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Download History\"\r\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Snippets\"\r\nPolicy Value: Check \"Do not allow settings to be changed\"\r\n\r\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\r\nAdd the following:\r\n<key>FirefoxHome</key>\r\n<dict>\r\n<key>Search</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>TopSites</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>SponsoredTopSites</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>Pocket</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>SponsoredPocket</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>Highlights</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>Snippets</key>\r\n  <false/>\r\n<key>Locked</key>\r\n  <true/>\r\n</dict>\r\n\r\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\r\nAdd the following in the policies section:\r\n\"FirefoxHome\": {\r\n  \"Search\": false,\r\n  \"TopSites\": false,\r\n  \"SponsoredTopSites\": false,\r\n  \"Pocket\": false,\r\n  \"SponsoredPocket\": false,\r\n  \"Highlights\": false,\r\n  \"Snippets\": false,\r\n  \"locked\": true\r\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \r\n\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Search\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"TopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredTopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Pocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredPocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Highlights\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Snippets\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\r\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The New Tab page by default shows a list of built-in top sites, as well as the top sites the user has visited.\r\n\r\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\r\n\r\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \r\n\r\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.\r\n\r\nThe new tab page must not actively show user activity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"c2ebb4f7-d6c8-4dc0-a81e-86779ef4eca5","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D615A2F491E06EFF94A192484C5EA69B4DAD25F\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Search' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tSearch (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Top Sites' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tTopSites (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Sponsored Top Sites' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tSponsoredTopSites (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Recommended by Pocket' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tPocket (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Sponsored Pocket Stories' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tSponsoredPocket (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Download History' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tHighlights (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Snippets' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tSnippets (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Do not allow settings to be changed' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\r\nName:\tLocked (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------"},{"group_id_src":"V-251577","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251577","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251577","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251577r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251577r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000033","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DNS Over HTTPS\nPolicy Name: Enabled\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DNSOverHTTPS</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Enabled</key>\n    <false/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DNSOverHTTPS\": {\"Enabled\": false}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DNSOverHTTPS\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"DNS over HTTPS has generally not been adopted in the DoD. DNS is tightly controlled.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include, but are not limited to, advertising software or browser plug-ins not related to requirements or providing a wide array of functionality not required for every mission, but cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"e13c1ba3-806e-4238-9e32-7666945a4373","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 796854AA02CD71280A0AACF499E762280DA74272\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enabled' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DNSOverHTTPS\r\nName:\tEnabled (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251578","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251578","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251578","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox accounts must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251578r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251578r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000034","rule_title":"Firefox accounts must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Firefox Accounts\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisableFirefoxAccounts</key>\n  <true/> \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFirefoxAccounts\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFirefoxAccounts\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disable Firefox Accounts integration (Sync). \n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"b1e3b810-b275-4714-a558-ab9d3c1e4a79","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: C23C8FA8F097638E6362A81687D2175F768F57BF\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Firefox Accounts' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableFirefoxAccounts (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251580","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251580","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251580","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox feedback reporting must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251580r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251580r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000036","rule_title":"Firefox feedback reporting must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Feedback Commands\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisableFeedbackCommands</key>\n  <true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFeedbackCommands\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFeedbackCommands\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disable the menus for reporting sites (Submit Feedback, Report Deceptive Site). \r\n\r\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\r\n\r\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \r\n\r\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"07c718fd-96cc-45e9-a66f-7d5ef3185b2f","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: E917985E5A44EFBFF84C845AAA5659754F7E80C0\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Feedback Commands' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisableFeedbackCommands (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-251581","group_tree":[{"id":"V-251581","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-251581","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox encrypted media extensions must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-251581r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-251581r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000037","rule_title":"Firefox encrypted media extensions must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy Name: Enable Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Lock Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>EncryptedMediaExtensions</key>\n  <dict>\n    <key>Enabled</key>\n    <false/>\n    <key>Locked</key>\n    <true/> \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EncryptedMediaExtensions\": {\n  \"Enabled\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true\n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EncryptedMediaExtensions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" set to \"false\" or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" set to \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enable or disable Encrypted Media Extensions and optionally lock it.\n\nIf \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox does not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) unless the user consents to installing them.\n\nIf \"Locked\" is set to \"true\" and \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox will not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) or ask the user to install them.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"b7146623-9c52-4903-8f26-e2ce9d445a4d","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 64D2D6A3DBDA645DFE67C0F98CDE75CCE2D66E40\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Enable Encrypted Media Extensions' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EncryptedMediaExtensions\r\nName:\tEnabled (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Lock Encrypted Media Extensions' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EncryptedMediaExtensions\r\nName:\tLocked (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------"},{"group_id_src":"V-252881","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252881","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252881","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox must be configured to not delete data upon shutdown.","rule_id_src":"SV-252881r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252881r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000017","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not delete data upon shutdown.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Clear data when browser is closed\nPolicy Name: Cache, Cookies, Download History, Form & Search History, Browsing History, Active Logins, Site Preferences, Offline Website Data\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Locked\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n<key>SanitizeOnShutdown</key>\n<dict>\n  <key>Cache</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Cookies</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Downloads</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>FormData</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>History</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Sessions</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>SiteSettings</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>OfflineApps</key>\n  <false/>\n  <key>Locked</key>\n  <true/>\n</dict>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SanitizeOnShutdown\": {\n  \"Cache\": false,\n  \"Cookies\": false,\n  \"Downloads\": false,\n  \"FormData\": false,\n  \"History\": false,\n  \"Sessions\": false,\n  \"SiteSettings\": false,\n  \"OfflineApps\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true \n}","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"SanitizeOnShutdown\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have {\"Cache\":false,\"Cookies\":false,\"Downloads\":false,\"FormData\":false,\"Sessions\":false,\"History\":false,\"OfflineApps\":false,\"SiteSettings\":false,\"Locked\":true}, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"For diagnostic purposes, data must remain behind when the browser is closed. This is required to meet non-repudiation controls.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"1de8d2fb-406d-4587-a27a-9c977c3adb45","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: F83408AB8289025BA6A1422D573A6198EE73CF74\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Active Logins' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tSessions (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Browsing History' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tHistory (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Cache' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tCache (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Cookies' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tCookies (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Download History' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tDownloads (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Form & Search History' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tFormData (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Locked' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tLocked (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Offline Website Data' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tOfflineApps (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n'Site Preferences' is NOT Disabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\r\nName:\tSiteSettings (Not found)\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------"},{"group_id_src":"V-252908","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252908","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252908","severity":"medium","group_title":"Pocket must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-252908r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252908r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000038","rule_title":"Pocket must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Pocket\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n<key>DisablePocket</key>\n <true/>\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePocket\": true","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \r\n\r\nIf \"DisablePocket\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Mozilla_Firefox_2021_VERSION_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Pocket, previously known as Read It Later, is a social bookmarking service for storing, sharing, and discovering web bookmarks. Data gathering cloud services such as this are generally disabled in the DoD.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5446","uuid":"efe7274b-f89d-414a-a68c-d2ac266991f3","stig_uuid":"a0f85050-15f6-4000-b084-5809368cc566","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-MozillaFirefox_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/22/2026\r\nResultHash: 2DAC824A3DBE2892BF8D8A5A15D9BB808C79C565\r\n~~~~~\r\n'Disable Pocket' is NOT Enabled\r\n\r\nPath:\t\tHKLM:\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\r\nName:\tDisablePocket (Not found)"},{"group_id_src":"V-252909","group_tree":[{"id":"V-252909","title":"SRG-APP-000141","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-252909","severity":"medium","group_title":"Firefox Studies must be disabled.","rule_id_src":"SV-252909r960963_rule","rule_id":"SV-252909r960963","rule_version":"FFOX-00-000039","rule_title":"Firefox Studies must be disabled.","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Na